INSERT INTO `recipe` VALUES (470,'Vanilla Milkshake','vanilla ice cream, whole milk, white sugar, vanilla extract','Place a tall glass in the freezer for 5 minutes so the milkshake stays cold on contact. | Add the vanilla ice cream, whole milk, white sugar, and vanilla extract to a blender jar. | Blend on low for 10 seconds to break up the ice cream, then blend on high for 20–30 seconds until smooth, thick, and glossy; stop and scrape down the sides with a spatula if needed, then blend 5 seconds more. | Pour into the chilled glass immediately; the milkshake should mound slightly before settling and be thick enough to drink through a wide straw.','[\"1½ cups\",\"½ cup\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"½ teaspoon\"]',520,'vanilla-milkshake-recipe.png','A classic milkshake blended until thick and smooth, finished with vanilla and a small amount of sugar.',10,1,6,2,1,43,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',7,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(471,'Buttermilk Pancakes','flour, buttermilk, egg, canola oil, baking powder, white sugar, salt','Set a 20 cm nonstick skillet over medium heat for 3 minutes, until a drop of water sizzles and evaporates quickly; lightly brush the surface with a thin film of canola oil. | Whisk flour, baking powder, white sugar, and salt in a medium bowl for 20 seconds to evenly distribute the leavening. | In a small bowl, whisk buttermilk and egg for 20 seconds until smooth, then pour into the dry ingredients and whisk just until no dry flour remains; let the batter rest 5 minutes until it looks slightly thicker and small bubbles appear on the surface. | Spoon the batter into the hot skillet in 2 rounds (about ¼ cup batter each) and cook 2–3 minutes, until bubbles rise and pop on top and the edges look set and slightly dry. | Flip with a thin spatula and cook 1–2 minutes more, until the second side is golden-brown and the centers spring back when lightly pressed; repeat with the remaining batter, brushing the pan with a little more canola oil only if it looks dry.','[\"½ cup\",\"½ cup\",\"1 large\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',520,'pancakes-recipe.png','Classic stovetop pancakes with a tender crumb and lightly browned edges.',10,1,8,4,1,43,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',18,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(473,'Chicken Caesar Wrap','boneless skinless chicken breast, large flour tortilla, romaine lettuce, chopped, Parmesan cheese, finely grated, mayonnaise, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, finely grated, olive oil, salt, black pepper','Pat the chicken dry with paper towels, then season both sides evenly with the salt and black pepper. | Heat a 25 cm non-stick skillet over medium-high heat until hot (about 190°C surface temp), add 1 tsp olive oil, and swirl to coat. Lay in the chicken and cook 4–5 minutes on the first side until golden brown; flip and cook 3–5 minutes more until the thickest part reaches 74°C and the juices run clear. Transfer to a plate and rest 3 minutes, then slice into thin strips. | In a medium bowl, whisk the mayonnaise, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, Worcestershire sauce, and grated garlic until smooth and glossy; this is the Caesar dressing. | Add the chopped romaine and 1½ tbsp of the Parmesan to the bowl and toss until the leaves look lightly coated and no dressing pools at the bottom. | Warm the tortilla in the same skillet over medium heat for 15–20 seconds per side until pliable with a few light toast marks, then set it on a cutting board. | Pile the dressed romaine down the center of the to','[\"1 small (about 120 g)\",\"1 piece\",\"1½ cups\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"1 clove\",\"2 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',620,'popular-real-lunch-recipe-recipe.png','A classic lunch wrap with warm chicken, crisp romaine, Parmesan, and Caesar dressing wrapped in a toasted tortilla.',8,0,12,6,1,44,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',20,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(474,'Greek Salad','ripe tomato, cut into 2 cm chunks, cucumber, cut into 2 cm chunks, green bell pepper, thinly sliced, red onion, thinly sliced, feta cheese, cut into 1 cm slabs, pitted Kalamata olives, extra-virgin olive oil, red wine vinegar, dried oregano, salt, black pepper','Set out a medium bowl and a cutting board; cut the tomato and cucumber into 2 cm chunks, slice the bell pepper into thin strips, and slice the red onion very thin (use a knife or mandoline carefully). | Add the tomato, cucumber, bell pepper, and red onion to the bowl; add the olives and toss gently for 10 seconds so the vegetables stay chunky and don’t release too much juice. | In a small bowl, whisk the extra-virgin olive oil, red wine vinegar, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper for 15–20 seconds until the dressing looks slightly thickened and evenly mixed. | Pour the dressing over the salad and toss gently with a spoon for about 15 seconds, just until the vegetables look glossy and lightly coated. | Lay the feta slabs on top; let the salad stand at room temperature for 2 minutes so the oregano perfumes the oil, then serve immediately while the vegetables are crisp and the feta holds its shape.','[\"1 medium\",\"½ medium\",\"¼ medium\",\"¼ small\",\"50 g\",\"10 pieces\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',430,'popular-real-salad-recipe-recipe.png','A classic Greek salad with cucumber, tomato, bell pepper, red onion, olives, and feta, dressed with olive oil and oregano.',9,0,5,8,1,44,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',12,'EASY','Greece',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(475,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','chocolate chips, flour, unsalted butter, softened, brown sugar, egg yolk, white sugar, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Heat the oven to 175°C and line a small baking sheet with baking paper. | In a medium bowl, mix the softened unsalted butter, brown sugar, and white sugar with a fork for 45–60 seconds until smooth and glossy. | Mix in the egg yolk and vanilla extract until fully combined and slightly thickened, about 20 seconds. | Add the flour, baking soda, and salt. Stir with a spoon just until no dry flour remains; the dough should look soft and slightly sticky. Fold in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed. | Scoop the dough into 3 mounds (about 1½ tablespoons each) and place them on the baking sheet with at least 5 cm space between. Lightly press each mound to about 1.5 cm thick so they spread evenly. | Bake on the middle rack for 10–12 minutes, until the edges are set and lightly browned but the centers still look slightly underdone and puffy. | Cool on the baking sheet for 10 minutes to finish setting, then transfer to a plate; the cookies should be crisp at the edges and soft in the cen','[\"¼ cup\",\"⅓ cup\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"1\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',430,'popular-real-dessert-recipe-recipe.png','Classic drop cookies with a buttery vanilla dough and melted chocolate chips.',10,3,5,2,1,44,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',27,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(476,'Chana Masala','cooked chickpeas, drained and rinsed, crushed tomatoes, yellow onion, finely chopped, water, olive oil, garlic cloves, minced, fresh ginger, finely grated, lemon juice, ground cumin, ground coriander, garam masala, ground turmeric, ground cayenne pepper, salt','Place a small saucepan over medium heat (about 180°C). Add the olive oil and chopped onion, then cook for 6–8 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon, until the onion is soft and lightly golden at the edges. | Add the minced garlic and grated ginger and cook for 30–45 seconds, stirring constantly, until very fragrant (do not let the garlic brown). | Add the ground cumin, ground coriander, garam masala, turmeric, and cayenne pepper. Stir for 20–30 seconds until the spices smell toasted and the pot looks slightly dry. | Pour in the crushed tomatoes and add the salt. Simmer over medium-low heat for 6–8 minutes, stirring often, until the sauce darkens slightly and thickens enough that a spoon leaves a brief trail on the bottom of the pot. | Add the cooked chickpeas and the water. Bring to a gentle simmer over medium heat, then reduce to low and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the chickpeas are coated and the sauce is glossy and spoon-thick; mash 2–3 tablespoons of chickpeas','[\"1½ cups\",\"½ cup\",\"½ medium\",\"⅓ cup\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"2 cloves\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"¾ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',520,'popular-real-vegetarian-recipe-recipe.png','A North Indian chickpea curry simmered with tomatoes, onion, and warming spices, finished with lemon.',9,0,6,8,1,44,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',30,'EASY','India',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(477,'Spaghetti Carbonara','spaghetti, guanciale, Pecorino Romano cheese, finely grated, egg, egg yolk, black pepper, freshly ground, salt','Bring a medium pot of water to a rolling boil over high heat; salt the water with the salt. Add the spaghetti, stir for 10 seconds, then cook until just al dente (taste: tender but with a firm center), about 8–10 minutes. | While the pasta cooks, cut the guanciale into 1 cm strips. Heat a 25–28 cm skillet over medium heat, add the guanciale, and cook 6–8 minutes, stirring often, until the fat renders and the pieces are crisp and golden; turn off the heat. | In a medium bowl, whisk the egg and egg yolk with the Pecorino Romano and the black pepper until a thick paste forms and no dry cheese remains. | Just before draining, scoop out ⅓ cup (80 ml) of the starchy pasta water. Drain the spaghetti well, then immediately add it to the skillet with the guanciale and toss over low heat for 30 seconds to coat in the rendered fat. | Remove the skillet from the heat. Add the egg-cheese mixture and toss vigorously with tongs for 45–60 seconds, adding pasta water 1 tablespoon at a time until the sa','[\"100 g\",\"50 g\",\"30 g\",\"1 large\",\"1 large\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\"]',760,'popular-real-pasta-dish-recipe.png','A classic Roman pasta made with eggs, Pecorino Romano, guanciale, and black pepper, emulsified into a silky sauce with pasta water.',10,0,11,4,1,44,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',20,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(478,'Spaghetti Carbonara','spaghetti, guanciale, cut into 1 cm strips, egg yolks, Pecorino Romano cheese, finely grated, black pepper, freshly ground, salt','Bring a medium pot of water to a rolling boil over high heat; add the salt and stir. Add the spaghetti and cook, stirring in the first minute, until al dente (about 8–10 minutes, or 1 minute less than the package suggests). | While the pasta cooks, set a large skillet over medium heat (about 170–180°C). Add the guanciale and cook 6–8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the fat renders and the strips turn deep golden with crisp edges; lower heat to low to keep warm without burning. | In a medium bowl, whisk the egg yolks with the grated Pecorino Romano and the black pepper until a thick paste forms. | Just before draining, scoop out ⅓ cup pasta cooking water. Drain the spaghetti well (do not rinse). | Add the hot spaghetti to the skillet with the guanciale and toss 30–45 seconds over low heat until coated in the rendered fat; turn off the heat and wait 20 seconds so the pan is hot but not scorching. | Add the egg-and-cheese mixture and toss vigorously with tongs for 45–60 seconds, add','[\"100 g\",\"60 g\",\"2\",\"30 g\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\"]',780,'popular-real-pasta-dish-recipe.png','Classic Roman pasta with guanciale, egg, Pecorino Romano, and black pepper, finished with a glossy sauce made from the pasta’s heat and a little starchy water.',10,0,13,4,1,44,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',20,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(479,'Chicken Caesar Salad','boneless skinless chicken breast, romaine lettuce, bread croutons, Parmesan cheese, finely grated, mayonnaise, olive oil, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, Dijon mustard, garlic clove, finely grated, salt, black pepper','Pat the chicken breast dry with paper towels, then season all over with ¼ tsp salt and ⅛ tsp black pepper. | Heat a 25 cm skillet over medium-high heat until a drop of water sizzles on contact (about 190°C). Add 1 tsp olive oil and swirl to coat. | Lay the chicken in the skillet and sear 5–6 minutes without moving, until deeply browned. Flip and cook 5–7 minutes more, lowering to medium if it’s browning too fast, until the thickest part reaches 74°C and the juices run clear. Transfer to a plate and rest 5 minutes, then slice into 1 cm strips. | Make the dressing in a medium bowl: whisk mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, Dijon mustard, grated garlic, remaining ¼ tsp salt, remaining ⅛ tsp black pepper, and 15 g of the Parmesan until smooth and glossy. Whisk in the remaining 1 tsp olive oil until lightly loosened. | Chop the romaine into bite-size pieces, add to the bowl with the dressing, and toss with tongs until the leaves look evenly coated but not swimming. | Add croutons','[\"150 g\",\"3 packed cups (about 120 g)\",\"¾ cup (about 35 g)\",\"25 g\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"1 piece\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',690,'popular-real-lunch-recipe-recipe.png','A classic lunch salad of seared chicken, romaine, croutons, and a from-scratch Caesar dressing with Parmesan and lemon.',9,0,16,6,1,44,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',25,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(480,'Chicken Tikka Masala','boneless skinless chicken thigh, canned crushed tomatoes, plain yogurt, heavy cream, onion, unsalted butter, olive oil, garlic clove, fresh ginger, tomato paste, water, garam masala, ground cumin, ground coriander, ground turmeric, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, black pepper, lemon juice','Cut the chicken thigh into 3 cm pieces. In a medium bowl, mix the yogurt, ½ tsp salt, black pepper, ½ tsp paprika, ½ tsp garam masala, cumin, coriander, turmeric, cayenne, lemon juice, 1 grated garlic clove, and the grated ginger until smooth. Add the chicken, toss to coat, and let sit 15 minutes at room temperature. | Heat a 25 cm heavy skillet over medium-high heat until a drop of water sizzles on contact (about 190°C). Add the olive oil. Add the chicken pieces in a single layer and cook 3–4 minutes without moving until browned; flip and cook 2–3 minutes more until mostly cooked through and browned in spots. Transfer to a plate; keep any juices. | Reduce heat to medium. Add the butter to the same skillet; when foaming subsides, add the onion (finely chopped) and cook 6–8 minutes, stirring, until soft and lightly golden. Add the remaining garlic clove (minced) and cook 30 seconds until fragrant. | Stir in the tomato paste and cook 1 minute until it darkens slightly. Add the crushed to','[\"200 g\",\"¾ cup (180 ml)\",\"¼ cup (60 ml)\",\"¼ cup (60 ml)\",\"½ medium (about 80 g)\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"2\",\"1 tsp, finely grated\",\"1 tbsp\",\"¼ cup (60 ml)\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\",\"¾ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"1 tsp\"]',820,'popular-real-chicken-dish-recipe.png','Grilled spiced chicken in a tomato-cream sauce, finished with butter and served straight from the pan.',9,0,12,5,1,44,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',40,'MID_LEVEL','India',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(481,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','chocolate chips, flour, unsalted butter, softened, packed brown sugar, white sugar, egg yolk, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Heat the oven to 175°C and line a small baking sheet with baking paper; set a wire rack nearby for cooling. | In a medium bowl, mash the softened butter with the packed brown sugar and white sugar using a fork or silicone spatula for 60–90 seconds, until smooth and paste-like with no visible butter lumps. | Mix in the egg yolk and vanilla extract for about 30 seconds, until glossy and fully combined. | Add the flour, baking soda, and salt; stir just until no dry flour remains and the dough looks thick and slightly tacky. Fold in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed. | Scoop the dough into 4 mounds (about 1½ tbsp each) and place them spaced out on the baking sheet; lightly press each mound to about 1.5 cm thick so they bake evenly. | Bake on the middle rack for 10–12 minutes, until the edges look set and lightly browned while the centers still look slightly underdone and puffed. | Cool on the baking sheet for 5 minutes (they will finish setting), then transfer to the wire rack a','[\"⅓ cup\",\"½ cup\",\"3 tbsp\",\"3 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',520,'popular-real-dessert-recipe-recipe.png','Classic drop cookies with browned edges and a soft center.',10,4,6,2,1,44,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',27,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(482,'Greek Salad','ripe tomato, cut into 2 cm chunks, cucumber, cut into 2 cm chunks, feta cheese, cut into 2 cm slabs, red onion, thinly sliced, pitted Kalamata olives, extra-virgin olive oil, lemon juice, dried oregano, salt, black pepper','Place the tomato, cucumber, red onion, and olives in a medium bowl; toss gently with a spoon for 10 seconds to combine without crushing the tomato. | In a small bowl, whisk the extra-virgin olive oil, lemon juice, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper for 20–30 seconds until slightly emulsified and glossy. | Pour the dressing over the vegetables and toss gently for 15–20 seconds, until everything is lightly coated and a little liquid collects at the bottom of the bowl. | Lay the feta slabs on top and let the salad stand 3 minutes at room temperature so the feta softens slightly and the flavors meld; serve immediately, spooning some of the dressing and juices over the feta.','[\"1 medium\",\"½ medium\",\"60 g\",\"¼ small\",\"10 pieces\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',430,'popular-real-salad-recipe-recipe.png','A classic Greek salad with tomatoes, cucumber, olives, feta, and an oregano-lemon dressing.',9,0,6,8,1,44,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',12,'EASY','Greece',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(483,'Chicken Pad Thai','dried flat rice noodles, boneless skinless chicken thigh, thinly sliced, egg, bean sprouts, rinsed and drained, garlic cloves, finely minced, roasted unsalted peanuts, coarsely chopped, lime, canola oil, tamarind paste, fish sauce, soy sauce, water, brown sugar, ground dried chili','Soak the rice noodles in a medium bowl covered with just-boiled water for 6–8 minutes, stirring once halfway, until pliable but still a bit firm at the center; drain well and rinse briefly under cool water, then shake off excess water. | In a small bowl, whisk tamarind paste, fish sauce, soy sauce, water, brown sugar, and ground dried chili until the sugar dissolves and the sauce looks uniform. | Heat a 28–30 cm wok or large nonstick skillet over high heat for 1 minute until very hot; add canola oil and swirl for 10 seconds, then add the sliced chicken in a single layer and stir-fry 2–3 minutes until no longer pink and lightly browned at the edges. | Add the minced garlic and stir-fry 15–20 seconds until fragrant but not browned; push the chicken to one side of the pan, crack in the egg on the empty side, and scramble 30–45 seconds until softly set in small curds. | Add the drained noodles and pour in the sauce; toss continuously with tongs over high heat for 1–2 minutes until the nood','[\"80 g\",\"120 g\",\"1 large\",\"1 cup\",\"2\",\"2 tbsp\",\"½\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"3 tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',760,'popular-real-asian-dish-recipe.png','A classic Thai rice-noodle stir-fry with chicken, egg, and a tangy tamarind sauce; keep the pan hot and toss quickly so the noodles stay chewy and the sauce clings.',9,0,13,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'MID_LEVEL','Thailand',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(484,'Chicken Tikka Masala','boneless skinless chicken thighs, crushed tomatoes, coconut milk, yellow onion, finely chopped, canola oil, fresh ginger, finely grated, garlic clove, finely grated, tomato paste, water, ground cumin, ground coriander, paprika, garam masala, ground turmeric, cayenne pepper, salt','Cut the chicken thighs into 3 cm pieces and pat dry with paper towels; season evenly with ¼ tsp of the salt plus the cumin, coriander, paprika, turmeric, and cayenne in a medium bowl until all pieces are well coated. | Heat a 25 cm nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until a drop of water sizzles on contact (about 2 minutes), add 1 tbsp of the canola oil, then spread the chicken in a single layer; sear 3 minutes without moving, then flip and sear 2 minutes more, until lightly browned on the outside (it will not be cooked through); transfer to a plate. | Reduce heat to medium, add the remaining ½ tbsp canola oil, then add the chopped onion and cook 5–6 minutes, stirring, until soft and lightly golden at the edges. | Add the grated ginger and grated garlic and cook 30–45 seconds, stirring constantly, until fragrant; stir in the tomato paste and cook 1 minute until it darkens slightly and sticks to the pan in spots. | Pour in the crushed tomatoes and water, scraping up any browned bits','[\"200 g\",\"1 cup\",\"½ cup\",\"½ small onion\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 clove\",\"1 tbsp\",\"¼ cup\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\",\"¾ tsp\"]',685,'popular-real-chicken-dish-recipe.png','Boneless chicken pieces simmered in a spiced tomato sauce enriched with coconut milk; serve with the thick sauce spooned over the chicken.',9,0,13,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',35,'MID_LEVEL','India',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(485,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','flour, semi-sweet chocolate chips, unsalted butter, softened, brown sugar, packed, white sugar, egg yolk, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Preheat the oven to 175°C and line a small baking sheet with baking paper; place a rack in the middle of the oven. | In a medium bowl, cream the softened butter, brown sugar, and white sugar with a spoon or silicone spatula for about 1 minute, until the mixture looks smooth and slightly lighter. | Add the egg yolk and vanilla extract and mix for 30–45 seconds, until glossy and fully combined with no streaks of yolk. | Sift in the flour, baking soda, and salt, then fold with the spatula just until no dry flour remains; the dough should look soft and thick—do not overmix. | Fold in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed. | Scoop the dough into 2 mounds (about 3 tablespoons each) and place them 8–10 cm apart on the prepared sheet; gently flatten each mound to about 1.5 cm thick so they spread evenly. | Bake for 10–12 minutes, until the edges are set and lightly golden while the centers still look slightly underbaked and soft. | Cool on the baking sheet for 10 minutes to finish setti','[\"½ cup\",\"¼ cup\",\"3 tablespoons\",\"3 tablespoons\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 piece\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',520,'popular-real-dessert-recipe-recipe.png','A classic baked cookie with brown sugar, butter, and chocolate chips. This version is dairy and contains no meat, keeping it kosher-style friendly.',10,4,5,2,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',32,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(486,'Roast Chicken and Potatoes','bone-in chicken thighs, Yukon Gold potato, cut into 3 cm chunks, carrot, cut into 2 cm chunks, yellow onion, cut into 8 wedges, water, olive oil, garlic cloves, peeled and lightly smashed, lemon juice, paprika, dried oregano, black pepper, salt','Preheat the oven to 220°C and place a 20–23 cm oven-safe baking dish on the counter; pat the chicken thighs dry well with paper towels so the skin browns properly. | Add the potato, carrot, and onion to the baking dish; add the water, 1 tablespoon olive oil, ½ teaspoon salt, and ¼ teaspoon black pepper, then toss with a spoon until the vegetables are evenly coated and the water is distributed across the bottom. | In a small bowl, mix the remaining ½ tablespoon olive oil with the lemon juice, paprika, oregano, the remaining ¼ teaspoon salt, and the smashed garlic cloves; rub this mixture all over the chicken, including under any loose skin, then place the chicken skin-side up on top of the vegetables and tuck the garlic cloves into the pan around (not under) the chicken. | Roast on the middle rack for 25 minutes, then rotate the dish and continue roasting 20–25 minutes more, until the chicken skin is deep golden-brown, the juices run clear, and an instant-read thermometer inserted into ','[\"2 pieces\",\"1 medium piece\",\"1 medium piece\",\"½ medium piece\",\"¼ cup\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"2 pieces\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"¾ teaspoon\"]',820,'popular-real-dinner-recipe-recipe.png','Bone-in chicken thighs are roasted with potatoes and carrots, seasoned with garlic, lemon, and paprika; the pan juices are spooned over at the end.',9,0,13,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',60,'EASY','France',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(487,'Spaghetti Carbonara','spaghetti, egg, egg yolk, Pecorino Romano cheese, finely grated, beef pancetta or beef bacon, cut into 1 cm pieces, olive oil, black pepper, freshly ground, salt','Bring a medium pot of well-salted water to a rolling boil over high heat; add the spaghetti and stir for 20 seconds to prevent sticking, then boil until al dente (taste: tender with a firm center), about 9–11 minutes depending on the package. | While the pasta cooks, whisk the egg and egg yolk in a medium heatproof bowl until smooth, then whisk in the grated Pecorino Romano and the black pepper to form a thick paste; set the bowl next to the stove so it’s ready when the pasta finishes. | Heat a 25 cm skillet over medium heat; add the beef pancetta and cook, stirring often, until the fat renders and the pieces are deeply golden and crisp at the edges, 6–8 minutes. Add the olive oil only if the pan looks dry, then remove the skillet from the heat. | Just before draining, scoop out ⅓ cup (80 ml) of the pasta cooking water. Drain the spaghetti well (do not rinse). | Add the hot spaghetti to the skillet with the beef pancetta and toss for 30–45 seconds off the heat, until the pasta is coate','[\"100 g\",\"1 large\",\"1\",\"30 g\",\"60 g\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',820,'popular-real-pasta-dish-recipe.png','A classic Roman pasta with eggs, hard cheese, black pepper, and crispy beef pancetta; made without cream and kept kosher by using beef instead of pork and avoiding any dairy-meat mixing beyond the dairy sauce itself.',10,0,9,4,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(488,'Chicken Tikka Masala','boneless skinless chicken thigh, canned crushed tomatoes, canned coconut milk, yellow onion, finely chopped, canola oil, garlic cloves, finely grated, fresh ginger, finely grated, lemon juice, ground cumin, ground coriander, sweet paprika, garam masala, turmeric, cayenne pepper, salt, black pepper','Cut the chicken thigh into 3 cm pieces on a cutting board. In a medium bowl, mix the lemon juice, ground cumin, ground coriander, sweet paprika, turmeric, cayenne pepper, ¼ tsp of the salt, and the black pepper; add the chicken and toss until evenly coated. Let stand 10 minutes at room temperature. | Heat a 25 cm skillet (preferably cast iron or heavy nonstick) over medium-high heat until very hot, about 2 minutes. Add ½ tbsp canola oil and swirl to coat. Spread the chicken in a single layer and sear 2–3 minutes without moving, until deep brown spots form; flip and sear 2 minutes more until the outside is browned and the chicken is just cooked through (cut a piece open; it should be opaque). Transfer to a plate. | Reduce heat to medium. Add the remaining 1 tbsp canola oil to the same skillet, then add the chopped onion. Cook 6–8 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon, until softened and golden at the edges. | Add the grated garlic and grated ginger and cook 30–45 seconds, stirring const','[\"200 g\",\"¾ cup\",\"½ cup\",\"½ cup\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"2 cloves\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\",\"¾ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',770,'popular-real-chicken-dish-recipe.png','Char-grilled spiced chicken in a tomato-based masala sauce made without dairy, served with its thick, glossy sauce.',10,0,14,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',40,'MID_LEVEL','India',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(489,'Scrambled Eggs on Toast','eggs, bread slices, tomato, butter, milk, salt, black pepper','Slice the tomato into 5 mm rounds and set aside; keep the eggs ready near the stove. | Toast the bread in a toaster or in a 25 cm skillet over medium heat for 2–3 minutes total, flipping once, until golden and crisp at the edges; set on a plate. | Crack the eggs into a bowl, add the milk, salt, and black pepper, and whisk with a fork for 20–30 seconds until no streaks remain. | Heat a 20 cm nonstick skillet over low heat for 1 minute, add the butter, and swirl until fully melted and foamy but not browned. | Pour in the eggs and cook over low heat for 3–5 minutes, stirring constantly with a silicone spatula and scraping the bottom and edges, until the curds are soft and glossy and the eggs are just set (they should look slightly loose but not runny). | Pile the scrambled eggs onto the toast and top with the tomato slices; serve immediately while the eggs are still glossy.','[\"2 large\",\"2 slices\",\"1 medium\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',420,'popular-real-breakfast-recipe-recipe.png','Soft scrambled eggs served over toasted bread with sliced tomato.',10,0,10,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',10,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(490,'Shakshuka','large eggs, canned crushed tomatoes, red bell pepper, diced (about 1 cm), yellow onion, finely diced, olive oil, water, garlic cloves, minced, tomato paste, ground cumin, sweet paprika, salt, black pepper, cayenne pepper','Crack the eggs into two separate small bowls (to avoid shell pieces and to keep the yolks intact), and set aside. | Heat a 20–24 cm nonstick or cast-iron skillet over medium heat (about 175–190°C). Add the olive oil and warm for 30 seconds until it shimmers. | Add the diced onion and cook 4–5 minutes over medium heat, stirring with a wooden spoon, until softened and translucent with light golden edges. | Add the diced red bell pepper and cook 3–4 minutes, stirring, until slightly softened and glossy. | Add the minced garlic and cook 30 seconds over medium heat, stirring constantly, until fragrant (do not let it brown). | Stir in the tomato paste, cumin, sweet paprika, cayenne, salt, and black pepper; cook 30–45 seconds until the mixture darkens slightly and smells toasted. | Add the crushed tomatoes and water, scrape the bottom of the pan, and bring to a steady simmer over medium-high heat. Reduce to medium-low and simmer 8–10 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes, until thick enough that ','[\"2\",\"1 cup\",\"½ piece\",\"½ small\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"¼ cup\",\"2\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',430,'popular-real-israeli-dish-recipe.png','Eggs poached in a spiced tomato and pepper sauce, served straight from the skillet; keep it dairy-free to stay kosher with eggs.',8,0,8,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(491,'Crème Brûlée','heavy cream, egg yolks, sugar, vanilla extract, salt','Preheat the oven to 160°C and place a small oven-safe dish (about 200–250 ml capacity) inside a roasting pan; set a kettle of water to boil, then let it sit 2 minutes so it’s very hot but not violently bubbling. | In a medium bowl, whisk the egg yolks with 2 tablespoons sugar and the salt for 30–45 seconds, until the mixture looks slightly paler and smooth (do not whip to foam). | Heat the heavy cream in a small saucepan over medium heat until it is steaming and tiny bubbles appear around the edges (about 75–80°C), 3–5 minutes; do not let it boil. | While whisking constantly, slowly drizzle the hot cream into the yolk mixture in a thin stream for 1–2 minutes to temper; whisk in the vanilla extract. | Pour the custard through a fine-mesh strainer into the small oven-safe dish to remove any cooked egg bits; skim off any surface bubbles with a spoon for a smoother top. | Pour hot water into the roasting pan until it comes halfway up the sides of the dish; bake on the middle rack for 28–35','[\"¾ cup (180 ml)\",\"2 large\",\"3 tablespoons\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',700,'popular-real-dessert-recipe-recipe.png','A classic baked custard flavored with vanilla and topped with a crackly caramelized sugar crust; this version is dairy-based and contains no meat, fitting kosher separation rules.',9,3,6,2,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',195,'MID_LEVEL','France',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(492,'Shakshuka','canned crushed tomatoes, large eggs, red bell pepper, diced (about 1 cm), yellow onion, finely diced, olive oil, tomato paste, water, garlic cloves, minced, ground cumin, sweet paprika, salt, black pepper, cayenne pepper','Wash the onion and bell pepper well and check they are clean; prepare all chopping. Heat a 20 cm skillet over medium heat for 1 minute, add the olive oil, then add the onion and bell pepper and cook 6–8 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon, until softened and the onion turns translucent with lightly golden edges. | Add the minced garlic and cook 30–45 seconds over medium heat until fragrant (do not let it brown). Stir in the tomato paste, cumin, sweet paprika, salt, black pepper, and cayenne; cook 1 minute, stirring, until the paste darkens slightly. | Pour in the crushed tomatoes and water. Bring to a gentle simmer over medium-high heat, then reduce to medium-low and simmer 8–10 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes, until the sauce thickens and a spoon dragged through leaves a trail that slowly fills in. | With the spoon, make 2 small wells in the sauce. Crack an egg into each well. Cover the skillet with a lid and cook 5–7 minutes on low heat, until the whites are set and opaque and th','[\"1 cup (about 240 ml)\",\"2\",\"½ pepper\",\"½ small onion\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"¼ cup (60 ml)\",\"2\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',430,'popular-real-israeli-dish-recipe.png','A classic Israeli skillet of eggs gently poached in a spiced tomato and pepper sauce, served straight from the pan.',8,0,7,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',30,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(493,'Avocado Toast with Egg','bread slice, ripe avocado, large egg, olive oil, lemon juice, salt, black pepper','Wash the avocado skin and check the flesh as you cut it; if using any produce that is insect-prone, wash well and check. Toast the bread slice in a toaster or in a dry 20 cm nonstick skillet over medium heat for 2–3 minutes total, flipping once, until golden and crisp at the edges. | Scoop the avocado into a small bowl and mash with a fork for 20–30 seconds until mostly smooth with a few small chunks. Mix in the lemon juice, salt, and black pepper; taste and it should be bright and lightly salty. | Heat a 20 cm nonstick skillet over medium heat (about 175–190°C) for 1 minute, then add the olive oil and swirl to coat. Crack in the egg and fry 2–3 minutes until the whites are set and opaque but the yolk is still slightly jiggly; for a firmer yolk, cover the skillet and cook 30–60 seconds more until the yolk dulls slightly. | Spread the mashed avocado evenly over the toast. Slide the egg on top; the whites should be set so it transfers cleanly. Serve immediately while the toast is crisp.','[\"1 slice\",\"½ avocado\",\"1 large egg\",\"2 teaspoons\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',410,'popular-real-breakfast-recipe-recipe.png','Toasted bread topped with mashed avocado and a fried egg, finished with lemon and black pepper. Keep it kosher by using pareve bread and checking any produce as needed.',9,0,7,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',10,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(494,'Greek Salad','ripe tomatoes, cut into 2 cm chunks, cucumber, cut into 2 cm chunks, feta cheese, cut into 2 cm slabs, red bell pepper, cut into 2 cm pieces, red onion, thinly sliced, pitted Kalamata olives, extra-virgin olive oil, lemon juice, dried oregano, salt, black pepper','Wash the tomatoes, cucumber, bell pepper, and onion well, then pat dry; cut the tomatoes and cucumber into 2 cm chunks, cut the bell pepper into 2 cm pieces, and slice the red onion thinly using a cutting board and chef’s knife. | Add the tomatoes, cucumber, bell pepper, red onion, and olives to a medium bowl and toss gently for 10 seconds so the vegetables are evenly mixed without crushing the tomatoes. | In a small bowl, whisk the olive oil, lemon juice, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper with a fork for 15–20 seconds until the dressing looks slightly thickened and uniform. | Pour the dressing over the salad and toss gently with a spoon for 15–20 seconds, just until the vegetables are lightly coated and glossy. | Place the feta on top in 2 cm slabs, then let the salad stand for 2 minutes at room temperature so the oregano blooms and juices collect lightly at the bottom; serve immediately.','[\"1 cup\",\"¾ cup\",\"60 g\",\"½ piece\",\"¼ piece\",\"10 pieces\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',430,'greek-salad-80730499-f2f9-4b86-8a38-21de253886e1.png','A classic Greek salad with chopped vegetables, olives, and feta, dressed with olive oil and oregano.',9,0,4,8,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',12,'EASY','Greece',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(495,'Spaghetti Carbonara','spaghetti, beef bacon, cut into 1 cm strips, large egg, egg yolk, finely grated Parmesan cheese, olive oil, freshly ground black pepper, salt','Bring a medium pot of water to a rolling boil over high heat, salt the water generously, add the spaghetti, and cook until al dente, 8–10 minutes, stirring in the first minute so strands don’t stick. | While the pasta cooks, whisk the large egg and egg yolk in a medium bowl for 30 seconds until smooth, then whisk in the grated Parmesan cheese and black pepper until a thick paste forms; set the bowl near the stove so it’s ready when the pasta is drained. | Heat a 25 cm skillet over medium heat for 2 minutes, add the olive oil, then add the beef bacon strips and cook 5–7 minutes, stirring often, until deeply browned and crisp at the edges with rendered fat in the pan; turn the heat to low. | Reserve ⅓ cup pasta cooking water, then drain the spaghetti well and immediately add it to the skillet; toss with tongs for 30–45 seconds over low heat until the pasta is glossy with the rendered fat. | Remove the skillet from the heat for 30 seconds so it’s not screaming hot, then pour in the egg-an','[\"100 g\",\"60 g\",\"1\",\"1\",\"30 g\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',730,'spaghetti-carbonara-fb799b5b-fee9-439c-b465-a8cb9113623f.png','A classic Roman pasta made with spaghetti, crisp beef bacon, eggs, black pepper, and grated Parmesan, finished with a silky sauce made from the egg mixture and starchy pasta water.',10,0,13,4,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(496,'Scrambled Eggs and Toast','large eggs, bread slices, unsalted butter, whole milk, salt, black pepper','Crack the eggs into a small bowl, add the milk, salt, and black pepper, then whisk with a fork for 20–30 seconds until fully blended and slightly foamy. | Toast the bread slice in a toaster to a deep golden color, about 2–3 minutes, then set it on a plate. | Heat a 20 cm nonstick skillet over medium-low heat for 1 minute; add the butter and swirl the pan until it melts and foams but does not brown, about 30–45 seconds. | Pour in the egg mixture and use a silicone spatula to stir slowly, scraping the bottom and pushing the eggs from the edges toward the center continuously; cook 3–5 minutes until small, soft curds form and the eggs look glossy and slightly loose (they will finish setting off the heat). | Remove the skillet from the heat and stir for 10 seconds to stop cooking, then spoon the eggs onto the toast and serve immediately.','[\"2 large\",\"1 slice\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',350,'scrambled-eggs-and-toast-39e2355f-b58b-492a-97bf-3c51f4522e41.png','Soft scrambled eggs served with toasted bread.',10,0,10,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',10,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(497,'Spaghetti Carbonara','dried spaghetti, guanciale, cut into 1 cm strips, Pecorino Romano cheese, finely grated, large egg, egg yolk, freshly ground black pepper, salt','Fill a medium pot with water for boiling, bring to a rolling boil over high heat, then salt the water generously; add the spaghetti and cook, stirring in the first minute, until just al dente, 8–10 minutes (a firm bite in the center). | While the pasta cooks, place the guanciale in a cold 25 cm skillet in a single layer, then set over medium heat and cook 6–8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the fat is rendered and the pieces are deeply golden and crisp; turn the heat to low to keep warm without burning. | In a medium bowl, whisk the egg and egg yolk until smooth, then whisk in the grated Pecorino Romano and black pepper to form a thick paste; set the bowl near the stove. | When the pasta is al dente, use a mug to scoop and reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain the spaghetti well (do not rinse). | Add the drained spaghetti to the skillet with the guanciale and toss over low heat for 30–45 seconds until the pasta is coated in the rendered fat and steaming but not sizzling a','[\"100 g\",\"60 g\",\"35 g\",\"1\",\"1\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\"]',780,'spaghetti-carbonara-356fe149-21a2-49b9-88f5-14d63286fdde.png','A classic Roman pasta made with eggs, Pecorino Romano, black pepper, and crisp guanciale, finished with a silky sauce created by emulsifying cheese and egg with hot pasta water.',10,0,10,4,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(498,'Chicken Shawarma Plate','boneless skinless chicken thighs, tahini, cucumber, tomato, olive oil, lemon juice, water, garlic clove, ground cumin, ground coriander, sweet paprika, ground turmeric, ground black pepper, salt','Trim any large pieces of excess fat from the chicken thighs, then slice into thin strips about 1 cm wide on a cutting board; peel and finely grate the garlic clove. | In a medium bowl, mix the chicken with olive oil, grated garlic, cumin, coriander, paprika, turmeric, black pepper, and ¼ tsp of the salt; stir 30 seconds until every piece is evenly coated, then let sit 10 minutes at room temperature. | Meanwhile, dice the cucumber and tomato into 1–1.5 cm pieces; place in a small bowl and toss with 1 tbsp of the lemon juice and ⅛ tsp salt, then set aside. | Make the tahini sauce by whisking tahini with the remaining 1 tbsp lemon juice and the water in a small bowl for 45–60 seconds; it should turn pale and thick, then loosen to a pourable consistency—add 1 more tsp water only if it is too thick to drizzle. | Heat a 25 cm skillet (cast-iron or heavy nonstick) over medium-high heat until hot (about 190°C); add the seasoned chicken in a single layer and cook 4 minutes without moving, until','[\"250 g\",\"3 tbsp\",\"1 small\",\"1 medium\",\"1 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"½ tsp\"]',690,'chicken-shawarma-plate-f2b97f2c-94ca-4fa7-8f33-c49f79b6cd19.png','Sliced, spiced chicken thighs seared until browned, served with a cucumber-tomato salad and tahini sauce. No dairy is used to keep it meat-friendly under kosher rules.',8,0,16,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',30,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(499,'Chicken Caesar Salad Wrap','cooked chicken breast, sliced, large flour tortilla, romaine lettuce leaves, washed and checked for insects, chopped, olive oil, pareve mayonnaise, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, garlic clove, finely grated, Worcestershire sauce, salt, black pepper','Wash the romaine thoroughly and check for insects; spin or pat very dry so the wrap won’t get soggy. | Make the Caesar-style dressing in a small bowl: whisk the pareve mayonnaise, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, grated garlic, Worcestershire sauce, salt, and black pepper until smooth and glossy, about 30 seconds. | Heat a 20 cm skillet over medium-high heat (about 190°C). Add the olive oil and warm the sliced cooked chicken, stirring, for 2–3 minutes until hot and lightly browned at the edges; remove from the heat. | In a medium bowl, toss the chopped romaine with all the dressing until evenly coated; the leaves should look lightly glossy, not swimming. | Warm the tortilla directly in a dry skillet over medium heat for 20–30 seconds per side until flexible with a few light brown spots. | Assemble: lay the tortilla flat, place the dressed romaine in a strip across the center, top with the warm chicken, fold in the sides, then roll tightly into a wrap. Rest seam-side down for 1 minute, then ','[\"120 g\",\"1 piece (about 25 cm)\",\"2 cups\",\"1 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 piece\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',585,'chicken-caesar-salad-wrap-1358b95b-191d-4a88-b719-bea196b01637.png','A deli-style lunch wrap with warm chicken, crisp romaine, and a from-scratch Caesar dressing, kept kosher by using a pareve Caesar-style sauce (no dairy).',8,0,13,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',15,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(500,'Chicken Stir-Fry with Rice','uncooked jasmine rice, boneless skinless chicken breast, broccoli florets, red bell pepper, carrot, yellow onion, water, soy sauce, canola oil, garlic clove, fresh ginger, cornstarch, rice vinegar, sesame oil, salt, black pepper','Rinse the rice in a fine-mesh strainer under cold running water for 30 seconds, then add it to a small saucepan with the water and salt. Bring to a boil over high heat, cover tightly, reduce to low heat, and cook for 12 minutes until the water is absorbed. Turn off the heat and rest, covered, for 5 minutes; fluff with a fork. | Cut the chicken into 2 cm pieces. Cut the broccoli into bite-size florets, slice the bell pepper into thin strips, peel and slice the carrot into thin half-moons, and thinly slice the onion. Finely grate the garlic and ginger. | In a small bowl, whisk soy sauce, rice vinegar, cornstarch, 2 tablespoons water taken from the measured water (before cooking the rice, if possible), black pepper, and sesame oil until no lumps remain. | Heat a 25–28 cm skillet or wok over medium-high heat (about 200°C) for 2 minutes until a drop of water sizzles on contact. Add canola oil and swirl to coat. | Add chicken in a single layer and cook 3 minutes without moving until browned ','[\"½ cup\",\"170 g\",\"1 cup\",\"½ piece\",\"½ piece\",\"½ piece\",\"1 cup\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 piece\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',650,'chicken-stir-fry-with-rice-56f9b91c-187d-458c-93d7-3206e2f1097c.png','A classic chicken and vegetable stir-fry served over rice, made with a soy-ginger sauce.',9,0,13,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',35,'MID_LEVEL','China',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(501,'Chicken Fried Rice','cooked jasmine rice, chilled, boneless skinless chicken thigh, cut into 1 cm pieces, large egg, frozen peas and carrots mix, yellow onion, finely chopped, canola oil, soy sauce, toasted sesame oil, garlic clove, minced, salt, ground black pepper','If using rice cooked today, spread it in a thin layer on a plate and chill in the freezer for 10 minutes until cool and slightly dry to the touch; break up any clumps with clean hands. | Heat a 25 cm wok or nonstick skillet over medium-high heat (about 200°C) for 2 minutes until a drop of water sizzles on contact. Add ½ tablespoon canola oil and swirl to coat. | Add the chicken and ⅛ teaspoon salt. Stir-fry 4–6 minutes, tossing constantly, until browned in spots and cooked through (no pink and juices run clear). Transfer to a bowl. | Add ½ tablespoon canola oil to the hot pan. Crack in the egg and scramble with a spatula over medium heat for 45–60 seconds until just set in soft curds; transfer to the bowl with the chicken. | Add the remaining ½ tablespoon canola oil. Add the onion and stir-fry 2 minutes over medium-high heat until lightly translucent at the edges. Add the garlic and cook 20–30 seconds until fragrant, not browned. | Add the peas and carrots and stir-fry 2 minutes until ','[\"1½ cups\",\"120 גרם\",\"1\",\"½ cup\",\"¼ cup\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',720,'chicken-fried-rice-38c95bb0-8e49-4724-a1b7-72df8bf03e77.png','A classic Chinese-style fried rice made with chicken, egg, and vegetables, seasoned with soy sauce and sesame oil. Keep the chicken and egg separate from any dairy products to maintain kosher meat status.',9,0,10,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'MID_LEVEL','China',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(502,'Greek Salad','ripe tomatoes, cut into 2 cm chunks, cucumber, cut into 2 cm chunks, feta cheese, coarsely crumbled, red onion, thinly sliced, pitted Kalamata olives, extra-virgin olive oil, fresh lemon juice, dried oregano, salt, black pepper','Wash and dry the tomatoes and cucumber; cut both into 2 cm chunks on a cutting board, slice the red onion very thinly, and place everything in a medium bowl with the olives. | In a small bowl, whisk the olive oil, lemon juice, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper for 15–20 seconds until the dressing looks slightly thickened and uniform. | Pour the dressing over the vegetables and toss gently with a spoon for 10–15 seconds until the surfaces look glossy and evenly coated. | Scatter the crumbled feta over the top and fold once or twice very gently so the feta stays in visible pieces; serve immediately when the vegetables look juicy and the feta is still distinct.','[\"1 cup\",\"1 cup\",\"50 g\",\"¼ small\",\"10 pieces\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',430,'greek-salad-b01ee155-51d9-4f90-85a0-a2e30a087c52.png','A classic Greek salad with tomatoes, cucumber, olives, feta, and an oregano-olive oil dressing.',9,0,4,8,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',10,'EASY','Greece',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(503,'Chicken Teriyaki','uncooked short-grain white rice, boneless skinless chicken thigh, water, soy sauce, mirin, sake, canola oil, cornstarch, water, sesame seeds, sliced scallion','Rinse the rice in a fine-mesh strainer until the water runs mostly clear, then add the rice and ¾ cup water to a small saucepan with a lid. Bring to a boil over high heat, stir once, cover, reduce to low, and cook for 12 minutes until the water is absorbed and small steam holes appear on the surface; remove from the heat and rest covered for 10 minutes, then fluff with a fork. | In a small bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, mirin, and sake until combined; set next to the stove. In a second small bowl, stir the cornstarch with 1 tbsp water until smooth and lump-free. | Pat the chicken thigh dry with paper towels. Heat a 25–28 cm nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot (a drop of water sizzles on contact), then add the canola oil and swirl to coat. | Place the chicken in the skillet smooth-side down and cook for 5–6 minutes over medium-high heat until deeply browned; flip and cook 4–5 minutes more until the second side is browned and the thickest part reaches 74°C, or the juice','[\"½ cup\",\"200 g\",\"¾ cup\",\"3 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"2 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tbsp\"]',820,'chicken-teriyaki-7a981b48-b5fd-4b64-8f59-45b33338ed12.png','Japanese pan-seared chicken glazed with a soy-based teriyaki sauce and served over steamed rice.',9,0,7,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',35,'MID_LEVEL','Japan',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(504,'Chicken Pad Thai','dried rice noodles, boneless skinless chicken thigh, egg, bean sprouts, garlic cloves, green onions, roasted unsalted peanuts, canola oil, tamarind paste, fish sauce, water, soy sauce, lime, red pepper flakes, salt, sugar','Slice the chicken thigh into thin strips about ½ cm thick; thinly slice the green onions (separate the white and green parts), mince the garlic, and roughly chop the peanuts. Cut the lime half into wedges. | Soak the rice noodles in a medium bowl of hot (not boiling) water for 8–10 minutes, stirring once or twice, until pliable but still a bit firm in the center; drain well and set aside. | Stir tamarind paste, fish sauce, water, soy sauce, and sugar in a small bowl until the sugar dissolves and the sauce looks smooth; set next to the stove. | Heat a 25–28 cm wok or large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until a drop of water sizzles on contact (about 190°C). Add canola oil and swirl to coat, then add the garlic and the white parts of the green onions; stir-fry for 20–30 seconds until fragrant and just starting to turn pale golden. | Add the chicken and salt; stir-fry for 3–4 minutes, tossing constantly, until the pieces turn opaque and lightly browned at the edges and the thicke','[\"85 g\",\"120 g\",\"1 large\",\"1 cup\",\"2\",\"2\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"½\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"1 tbsp\"]',760,'chicken-pad-thai-92251f68-c903-4d36-a0de-768a68acefb6.png','Stir-fried rice noodles with chicken, egg, and a tamarind-based sauce, finished with peanuts and lime. Uses no pork or shellfish and avoids mixing meat with dairy.',9,1,12,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',30,'MID_LEVEL','Thailand',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(505,'Scrambled Eggs and Toast','large eggs, bread slices, olive oil, salt, black pepper','Crack the eggs into a medium bowl and whisk with the salt and black pepper for 20–30 seconds, until the mixture looks uniform with no clear streaks. | Heat a 20–24 cm nonstick skillet over medium-low heat (about 150–160°C). Add 1 teaspoon olive oil and swirl to coat the pan; the oil should shimmer but not smoke. | Pour in the eggs and stir continuously with a silicone spatula, scraping the bottom and sweeping the eggs into soft folds, 2–4 minutes. Stop when the curds are glossy and just set (they should look slightly wet because they will finish cooking from residual heat). Transfer immediately to a plate. | Toast the bread slices in a toaster or in a dry skillet over medium heat for 1–2 minutes per side, until the surface is crisp and lightly browned. | Drizzle the remaining 1 teaspoon olive oil over the toast (or lightly brush it on) and serve alongside the scrambled eggs while hot.','[\"2 pieces\",\"2 pieces\",\"2 teaspoons\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',350,'scrambled-eggs-and-toast-01dcab7e-8702-401c-9e9e-e75d307d462b.png','Soft scrambled eggs served with toasted bread; a common breakfast that stays kosher by using oil instead of butter.',10,0,10,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',10,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(506,'Chana Masala','cooked chickpeas, drained and rinsed, canned crushed tomatoes, yellow onion, finely diced, water, olive oil, garlic cloves, finely minced, fresh ginger, finely grated, tomato paste, lemon juice, ground cumin, ground coriander, garam masala, ground turmeric, cayenne pepper, salt','Place a small saucepan over medium heat for 1 minute, add the olive oil, then add the onion and salt; cook 6–8 minutes, stirring every minute, until softened and lightly golden at the edges. | Add the garlic and ginger and stir constantly for 30–45 seconds, just until fragrant (do not let the garlic brown). | Stir in the cumin, coriander, turmeric, cayenne pepper, and garam masala for 20 seconds until the spices smell toasty, then immediately add the tomato paste and stir for 30 seconds to darken slightly. | Add the crushed tomatoes and water, scrape the bottom of the pan with a wooden spoon, and bring to a steady simmer over medium-high heat; reduce to medium-low and simmer 8–10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the sauce thickens and leaves a brief trail when you drag a spoon through it. | Add the chickpeas and simmer 5–7 minutes, stirring gently, until the chickpeas are hot throughout and the sauce clings to them; if it gets too thick, add 1–2 tablespoons water and simmer 1 minu','[\"1 cup\",\"½ cup\",\"½ medium\",\"⅓ cup\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"2\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',420,'chana-masala-76312aac-cb37-4bdd-b3fe-e2161f6a317e.png','Indian chickpea curry simmered in a spiced tomato-onion sauce, finished with lemon.',9,0,5,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','India',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(508,'פיצה מרגריטה ללא גלוטן','קמח ללא גלוטן לאפייה, מים, עגבניות מרוסקות משימורים, גבינה צמחית נמסה מגוררת (ללא חלב), שמן זית, שמרים יבשים, אבקת אפייה, מלח, אורגנו יבש, שום כתוש','לחמם תנור ל-250°C (או החום המקסימלי בתנור הביתי) ולהכניס לתנור תבנית הפוכה או אבן אפייה כדי שיתחממו לפחות 10 דקות; בינתיים להכין את הבצק והרוטב. | בקערה בינונית לערבב קמח ללא גלוטן, שמרים יבשים, אבקת אפייה ומלח עד פיזור אחיד; להוסיף מים ושמן זית ולערבב בכף 45–60 שניות עד שנוצר בצק אחיד ורך שמחזיק יחד. אם יבש ומתפורר להוסיף עוד 1 כף מים ולערבב עד שהבצק גמיש. | להניח את הבצק על נייר אפייה ולשטח בעזרת ידיים לחות לעיגול בקוטר 18–20 ס״מ ובעובי כ-4–5 מ״מ; ליצור שוליים מעט מוגבהים מסביב ולתת לבצק לנוח 5 דקות עד שהוא נראה מעט תפוח ורך יותר למגע. | בקערית לערבב עגבניות מרוסקות, אורגנו יבש, שום כתוש ו-¼ כפית מלח עד אחידות; לטעום ולוודא שהרוטב מתובל (ללא הוספת סוכר). | למרוח את הרוטב בשכבה דקה ואחידה על הבצק, להשאיר שוליים של כ-1 ס״מ; לפזר מעל גבינה צמחית נמסה מגוררת באופן אחיד. | להעביר את הפיצה עם נייר האפייה אל התבנית/האבן החמה בתנור ולאפות 8–10 דקות, עד שהשוליים תפוחים ומזהיבים והגבינה נמסה ומבעבעת מעט. | להוציא לקרש חיתוך, להמתין 2 דקות להתייצבות, לפרוס ולהגיש כשהתחתית מרגישה יציבה ופריכה בק','[\"¾ כוס\",\"¼ כוס\",\"⅓ כוס\",\"½ כוס\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כפית\",\"½ כפית\",\"½ כפית\",\"½ כפית\",\"½ כפית\"]',520,'פיצה-מרגריטה-ללא-גלוטן-b8402064-d1e6-4658-8a5b-80e67db5639b.png','פיצה אישית מבצק מהיר ללא גלוטן, רוטב עגבניות ביתי ושכבת גבינה צמחית נמסה.',10,0,7,5,1,43,'2','1','1','2','0','[]',25,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(509,'אסאדו בתנור','נתח אסאדו עם עצם, מים, בצל, שמן זית, רסק עגבניות, שום, פפריקה מתוקה, פלפל שחור, מלח','לחמם תנור ל-160°C. לקלף את הבצל ולפרוס לפרוסות דקות; לקלף את השום ולמעוך. | לחמם סיר ברזל יצוק עם מכסה או תבנית קטנה חסינת חום עם מכסה על אש בינונית-גבוהה 2 דקות. להוסיף שמן זית ולחמם 30 שניות עד שהוא מבריק. | להניח את נתח האסאדו בסיר ולצרוב 3–4 דקות מכל צד, עד השחמה עמוקה. להעביר את הבשר לצלחת. | להוסיף לסיר את הבצל ולבשל 5–6 דקות על אש בינונית, תוך ערבוב, עד שהוא מתרכך ומקבל זהבה קלה. להוסיף שום ולבשל 30 שניות עד שעולה ריח. | להוסיף רסק עגבניות, פפריקה מתוקה, מלח ופלפל שחור ולערבב 30–45 שניות עד שהרסק נפתח והופך מעט כהה. | להוסיף מים ולגרד בכף עץ את תחתית הסיר 30 שניות כדי לשחרר את כל המשקעים. להחזיר את הבשר לסיר כך שיהיה שקוע חלקית בנוזל. | לכסות היטב ולהעביר לתנור. לבשל 2 שעות ו-45 דקות, עד שהבשר רך מאוד ומזלג נכנס בקלות והבשר מתחיל להיפרד לאורך הסיבים. | להוציא מהתנור. להעביר את הבשר לקרש ולכסות ברפיון 10 דקות. בינתיים להעביר את הסיר לאש בינונית ולצמצם את נוזלי הבישול ללא מכסה 6–10 דקות, עד שמתקבל רוטב מבריק שמצפה כף. | לפרוס או לפרק את האסאדו. להחזיר לסיר עם הרוטב ולחמם דקה על אש','[\"500 גרם\",\"1 כוס\",\"1 קטן\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"2 שיניים\",\"1 כפית\",\"½ כפית\",\"¾ כפית\"]',1150,'אסאדו-בתנור-99b86b1e-baa3-41b3-a88d-0cc151cb035d.png','נתח אסאדו בבישול ארוך בתנור עד רכות ונשירה, עם רוטב טבעי מצומצם ממיצי הבשר ונוזלי הבישול.',7,0,13,4,1,43,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',200,'MID_LEVEL','Argentina',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(510,'Yemeni Kubaneh Bread','flour, water, unsalted butter, softened, large egg, instant yeast, salt, sugar','Place the flour, instant yeast, sugar, and salt in a medium bowl and whisk 15 seconds to distribute evenly. | Add the water and egg, then mix with a spoon until a shaggy dough forms; knead by hand on a clean counter for 8–10 minutes until smooth and elastic, adding up to 1 tablespoon more flour only if the dough is sticking heavily to your hands (it should feel soft and slightly tacky). | Form the dough into a tight ball, put it back in the bowl, cover tightly, and let rise in a warm spot until roughly doubled and puffy, 60–75 minutes. | Grease a small oven-safe dish (about 12–14 cm wide) with ½ tablespoon of the butter. Divide the remaining butter into small pieces so it’s easy to spread while shaping. | Punch down the dough, divide into 4 equal pieces, and roll each into a smooth ball; cover with a towel and rest 10 minutes so the dough relaxes. | Flatten one ball into a thin round (about 10–12 cm), spread a thin layer of butter over it, then roll it into a tight log and coil it into','[\"1½ cups\",\"⅓ cup\",\"3 tbsp\",\"1\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"1 tsp\"]',820,'yemeni-kubaneh-bread-03d619a9-186f-40c4-906c-ac5c9d015689.png','A slow-baked Yemeni pull-apart bread made from enriched yeast dough and layered with butter for a tender, shreddable crumb.',4,0,8,3,1,43,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',220,'MID_LEVEL','Yemen',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(511,'לחמניית שמרים','קמח, מים, שמן זית, שמרים יבשים, סוכר לבן, מלח','לחמם תנור ל-200°C ולרפד תבנית אפייה בנייר אפייה. | בקערה בינונית לערבב מים בטמפרטורת גוף (כ-35–40°C) עם סוכר לבן ושמרים יבשים, ולהמתין 5 דקות עד שמופיע קצף עדין על פני הנוזל. | להוסיף קמח ושמן זית ולערבב בכף עד שנוצר בצק גס. להוסיף מלח וללוש ביד 6–8 דקות עד שהבצק חלק, אלסטי ומעט דביק אך נפרד מהדפנות; אם יבש מאוד להרטיב את היד בכפית מים וללוש עוד דקה. | לכדרר לכדור, להחזיר לקערה, לכסות ולהתפיח במקום חמים 45–60 דקות עד שהבצק כמעט מכפיל נפח ונראה אוורירי. | להוציא אוויר בעדינות, ליצור כדור מתוח וחלק ולסגור את התפר היטב בתחתית. להניח על התבנית, לכסות ולהתפיח 20–25 דקות עד שהלחמנייה תפוחה וכשלוחצים בעדינות האצבע משאירה שקע שחוזר לאט. | לאפות 14–18 דקות עד שהלחמנייה זהובה-עמוקה והחלק התחתון נשמע חלול כשדופקים עליו. לקרר על רשת 10 דקות לפני חיתוך.','[\"¾ כוס\",\"¼ כוס\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כפית\",\"1 כפית\",\"¼ כפית\"]',330,'לחמניית-שמרים-66c7639a-9199-40ed-8147-02c18367e4c4.png','לחמנייה רכה משמרים עם קרום עדין, מתאימה לכריך או לצד מרק.',8,0,8,6,1,43,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',120,'MID_LEVEL','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(512,'Vanilla Ice Cream','heavy cream, whole milk, egg yolk, granulated sugar, vanilla extract, salt','Set a fine-mesh sieve over a medium bowl and place the bowl in the refrigerator to chill; keep a silicone spatula and a small whisk nearby. | In a small saucepan, heat the heavy cream and whole milk over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until steaming and tiny bubbles form around the edges (about 70–75°C), 4–6 minutes; do not let it boil. | In a separate medium bowl, whisk the egg yolk with the granulated sugar and salt for 30–45 seconds, until the mixture looks slightly lighter and the sugar looks mostly dissolved. | Temper the yolk by slowly whisking in about ¼ cup of the hot milk mixture in a thin stream, then pour the warmed yolk mixture back into the saucepan while whisking constantly. | Cook the custard over medium-low heat, stirring constantly with the spatula and scraping the bottom and corners, until it thickens enough to coat the spatula and a finger swiped through leaves a clear line (about 80–82°C), 3–6 minutes; if you see any simmering, lower the heat immediately. | Imm','[\"¾ cup (180 ml)\",\"½ cup (120 ml)\",\"1 large\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',720,'vanilla-ice-cream-9d1728c6-f342-47b4-b5e5-928be35c4bf3.png','Classic custard-style vanilla ice cream, churned and frozen until scoopable.',10,2,3,2,1,43,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',450,'MID_LEVEL','France',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(513,'מפרום תפוחי אדמה','תפוחי אדמה גדולים קלופים, בשר בקר טחון, עגבניות מרוסקות ללא תוספת סוכר, מים, ביצה גדולה, קמח אורז, שמן קנולה, בצל קטן מגורד דק, שיני שום כתושות, רסק עגבניות, פפריקה מתוקה, כמון טחון, פלפל שחור, מלח','לפרוס את תפוחי האדמה לפרוסות בעובי כ-1.5 ס״מ בעזרת סכין חדה. בכל פרוסה לבצע חתך לרוחב כמעט עד הסוף כך שתיווצר ״כיס״, ולהניח בקערה עם מים קרים ל-10 דקות כדי לצמצם השחרה; לסנן ולייבש היטב במגבות נייר. | בקערה בינונית לערבב בשר בקר טחון עם בצל מגורד, 1 כפית מלח, פלפל שחור, כמון ופפריקה עד איחוד בלבד (לא ללוש יותר מדי כדי לא לקבל מרקם דחוס). | למלא כל ״כיס״ תפוח אדמה בשכבה אחידה של תערובת הבשר, לדחוס בעדינות כך שהמילוי יהיה שטוח עם שוליים נקיים יחסית, ולהניח על צלחת. | להכין בלילה: בקערה רחבה לטרוף ביצה עם קמח אורז ו-¼ כפית מלח עד לקבלת בלילה סמיכה ואחידה ללא גושים; אם סמיך מדי להוסיף 1–2 כפות מים מהכמות של המים הרשומה עד שהבלילה מצפה כף בשכבה דקה. | לחמם מחבת רחבה עם 3 כפות שמן קנולה על חום בינוני-גבוה (כ-190°C). לטבול כל תפוח אדמה ממולא בבלילה, לתת לעודפים לטפטף 5 שניות, ולהניח בזהירות במחבת. לטגן 2–3 דקות מכל צד עד הזהבה ברורה וקרום יציב; לעבוד ב-2 נגלות ולהוסיף עוד 2 כפות שמן בין הנגלות לפי הצורך. | בזמן הטיגון להכין רוטב בסיר רחב ונמוך: לחמם על חום בינוני את רסק העגבניות עם העגבניות ה','[\"4 יח׳\",\"350 גרם\",\"1½ כוסות\",\"1 כוס\",\"1 יח׳\",\"⅓ כוס\",\"5 כפות\",\"1 יח׳\",\"2 יח׳\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כפית\",\"½ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\",\"2 כפיות\"]',1700,'מפרום-תפוחי-אדמה-e617418a-e1e8-4a34-bec3-238f208c3f72.png','פרוסות תפוחי אדמה ממולאות בבשר טחון, מצופות בבלילה ללא גלוטן ומבושלות ברוטב עגבניות עד שהכול רך ומצופה ברוטב סמיך.',6,0,9,4,3,43,'2','0','1','2','0','[]',105,'MID_LEVEL','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(514,'Chicken Noodle Soup','chicken thighs, bone-in and skin-on, water, egg noodles, carrot, celery stalk, yellow onion, olive oil, fresh parsley, fresh dill, bay leaf, ground black pepper, salt','Pat the chicken thighs dry with paper towels; season all over with ¼ teaspoon salt and ⅛ teaspoon black pepper. | Heat a medium pot (about 2–3 liters) over medium-high heat (about 190°C). Add the olive oil, then add the chicken skin-side down and sear 3–4 minutes until the skin is deep golden; flip and sear 2 minutes more. | Add the water, scraping the bottom with a wooden spoon to loosen any browned bits. Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce to a gentle simmer over low heat; skim off any foam with a spoon for the first 5 minutes. | Meanwhile, cut the carrot into ½ cm slices, slice the celery ½ cm thick, and dice the onion into 1 cm pieces. Add carrot, celery, onion, and the bay leaf to the pot; keep at a gentle simmer (small bubbles) for 35–40 minutes, until the chicken is very tender and easily pulls from the bone. | Transfer the chicken to a plate with tongs. When cool enough to handle, remove and discard skin and bones, then shred the meat into bite-size pieces; return the s','[\"2 pieces\",\"2½ cups\",\"¾ cup\",\"1 medium\",\"1 piece\",\"½ medium\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 leaf\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"¾ teaspoon\"]',520,'chicken-noodle-soup-c867104b-9236-46aa-b03d-a3133806f738.png','Classic chicken soup simmered with vegetables, herbs, and egg noodles.',10,0,6,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',65,'MID_LEVEL','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(515,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','flour, semi-sweet chocolate chips, unsalted butter, softened, packed light brown sugar, white sugar, egg yolk, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Preheat the oven to 175°C. Line a small baking sheet with baking paper and set a rack in the middle of the oven. | Sift the flour into a medium bowl to check for insects, then whisk in the baking soda and salt until evenly combined. | In a second medium bowl, mix the softened butter, packed light brown sugar, and white sugar with a spoon or silicone spatula for about 1 minute, until smooth and glossy with no visible butter streaks. | Add the egg yolk and vanilla extract and stir vigorously for 30–45 seconds, until the mixture looks thicker and slightly lighter in color. | Add the flour mixture and fold just until no dry flour remains; the dough should look soft and cohesive. Fold in the semi-sweet chocolate chips until evenly distributed without over-mixing. | Scoop the dough into 3 mounds (about 4–5 cm across each) and place them on the prepared baking sheet with at least 5 cm spacing. Gently press each mound to about 2 cm thick so they spread evenly. | Bake for 10–12 minutes, until t','[\"½ cup\",\"⅓ cup\",\"3 tbsp\",\"3 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 large\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',650,'chocolate-chip-cookies-f6d38918-6b33-4da7-ab8f-761f51296252.png','A classic kosher dairy cookie with browned edges and a soft center, baked as a small batch.',10,5,6,2,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',32,'MID_LEVEL','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(516,'Chicken Shawarma Pita','boneless skinless chicken thighs, pita bread, tahini paste, water, tomato, cucumber, red onion, lemon juice, olive oil, garlic clove, ground cumin, ground coriander, paprika, ground turmeric, ground black pepper, salt','Pat the chicken thighs dry with paper towels, then slice into thin strips (about 1 cm). In a medium bowl, mix the chicken with olive oil, lemon juice, finely grated garlic clove, ground cumin, ground coriander, paprika, ground turmeric, ground black pepper, and ½ tsp salt; stir for 30 seconds until evenly coated. | Heat a 25 cm cast-iron skillet or heavy nonstick skillet over medium-high heat (the pan should feel very hot when you hover your hand above it, about 200°C). Add the seasoned chicken in one layer and cook 3 minutes without moving, until deep brown patches form; flip and cook 3–4 minutes more, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through (no pink spots and the pieces feel firm). | While the chicken cooks, dice the tomato, cucumber, and red onion. Combine them in a small bowl with a pinch of salt (about ⅛ tsp) and toss; the salad should look glossy and lightly juicy after 1 minute. | Make tahini sauce in a small bowl by whisking tahini paste with water and a pinch o','[\"200 g\",\"1 piece\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 medium\",\"½ medium\",\"¼ small\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 piece\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¾ tsp\"]',720,'chicken-shawarma-pita-42afc71c-2433-4847-ba56-8eeb73839d0f.png','A kosher chicken shawarma-style filling seared in a skillet and served in pita with tahini and chopped salad.',9,0,15,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(517,'Spaghetti Carbonara','dried spaghetti, guanciale, cut into 1 cm strips, Pecorino Romano cheese, finely grated, egg yolk, whole egg, freshly ground black pepper, salt','Bring a medium pot of water to a rolling boil over high heat, salt the water with ½ tsp salt, add the spaghetti, and cook until just al dente, stirring for the first 30 seconds so it doesn’t stick (about 9–11 minutes, or 1 minute less than the package suggests). | While the pasta cooks, place the guanciale in a cold 25 cm skillet and set over medium heat; cook, stirring often, until the fat renders and the pieces are deeply golden and crisp, 6–8 minutes. Turn the heat to low to keep warm; the rendered fat should remain in the skillet. | In a small bowl, whisk the egg yolk, whole egg, Pecorino Romano, and black pepper until thick and cohesive; it should look like a paste. | Reserve ⅓ cup pasta cooking water, then drain the spaghetti well. Add the spaghetti to the skillet with the guanciale and toss over low heat for 30 seconds until the pasta is coated in the rendered fat. | Remove the skillet from the heat for 30 seconds, then add the egg-and-cheese mixture and toss vigorously with ton','[\"100 g\",\"60 g\",\"30 g\",\"1 large\",\"1 large\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\"]',780,'spaghetti-carbonara-23a72f83-29e0-428e-ae04-d932bde743bc.png','A classic Roman pasta of spaghetti tossed with crisp cured pork, eggs, black pepper, and cheese for a glossy, creamy sauce made without cream.',10,0,12,4,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(518,'Chicken Stir-Fry','boneless skinless chicken breast, uncooked jasmine rice, water, broccoli florets, red bell pepper, carrot, yellow onion, canola oil, low-sodium soy sauce, water, cornstarch, fresh ginger, finely grated, garlic clove, finely grated, toasted sesame oil, salt, black pepper','Rinse the jasmine rice in a fine-mesh strainer until the water runs mostly clear. Combine the rinsed rice and ⅔ cup water in a small saucepan, bring to a boil over high heat, cover, reduce to low, and cook 12 minutes until the water is absorbed; rest covered off-heat 5 minutes, then fluff with a fork. | While the rice cooks, check the broccoli florets for any insects, then wash well and drain. Thinly slice the red bell pepper, cut the carrot into thin matchsticks, and slice the onion into thin wedges. Cut the chicken breast into 2 cm bite-size pieces and pat dry with paper towels. | In a small bowl, whisk low-sodium soy sauce, 3 tbsp water, cornstarch, grated ginger, grated garlic, toasted sesame oil, salt, and black pepper until the cornstarch is fully dissolved and the sauce looks smooth. | Heat a 25 cm skillet or wok over medium-high heat until a drop of water sizzles immediately (about 200°C pan surface). Add canola oil and swirl to coat. Add the chicken in a single layer and cook ','[\"200 g\",\"⅓ cup\",\"⅔ cup\",\"1 cup\",\"½ piece\",\"1 small\",\"¼ piece\",\"1 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"3 tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 piece\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',720,'chicken-stir-fry-3999f586-a816-48f1-a780-0fe56aeec140.png','A kosher chicken and vegetable stir-fry served over steamed rice with a soy-ginger sauce.',9,0,12,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',30,'EASY','China',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(519,'שיפודי פרגית על האש','פרגית ללא עצמות ועור, חתוכה לקוביות בגודל 3 ס״מ, בצל, חתוך לריבועים גדולים, שמן זית, מיץ לימון, שום, כתוש, פפריקה מתוקה, כמון, פלפל שחור, מלח','בקערה בינונית לערבב שמן זית, מיץ לימון, שום, פפריקה, כמון, פלפל שחור ומלח עד שהתערובת אחידה ומבריקה. | להוסיף את קוביות הפרגית והבצל, לערבב בידיים או בכף עד שכל החתיכות מצופות היטב, לכסות ולהשרות במקרר 30 דקות (עד שעה אם יש זמן). | אם משתמשים בשיפודי עץ, להשרות אותם במים 20 דקות כדי שלא יישרפו על הגריל, ואז לנער מעודפי מים. | להדליק מנגל/גריל ולחמם לחום בינוני-גבוה עד שגחלים מכוסות שכבה דקה אפורה או שהגריל חם מאוד (כ-220–250°C); לנקות את הרשת במברשת. | לשפד לסירוגין פרגית ובצל על שיפוד, בלי לדחוס מדי, ולהשאיר מעט רווחים כדי שייחרך יפה. | לצלות על הרשת 4 דקות, להפוך בעזרת מלקחיים ולצלות עוד 4–6 דקות, עד שהפרגית שחומה עם סימני גריל ברורים והמרכז כבר לא ורוד; אם יש מדחום, לכוון ל-74°C בחלק העבה. | להוריד לצלחת, לנוח 3 דקות כדי שהמיצים יתייצבו, ואז להגיש מיד.','[\"250 גרם\",\"½ יח׳\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"1 שן\",\"1 כפית\",\"½ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\",\"½ כפית\"]',520,'שיפודי-פרגית-על-האש-f2182cec-2aa7-4850-b43e-762b246a5d27.png','שיפודי פרגית מושחמים על גריל/מנגל, מושרים במרינדה של שמן זית, לימון ותבלינים עד לקבלת חריכה יפה ועסיסיות.',8,0,15,6,1,43,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',60,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(520,'Mixed Green Salad','mixed salad greens, cucumber, cherry tomatoes, red onion, extra-virgin olive oil, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, salt, black pepper','Rinse and thoroughly dry the mixed salad greens using a salad spinner or clean towel; the leaves should look dry and crisp so the dressing clings instead of pooling. | Cut the cucumber into ½ cm half-moons and halve the cherry tomatoes; slice the red onion very thin so it softens in the dressing. | In a large bowl, whisk the extra-virgin olive oil, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, salt, and black pepper for 20–30 seconds until the dressing looks slightly thickened and uniform. | Add the mixed salad greens, cucumber, cherry tomatoes, and red onion to the bowl; toss with tongs for 20–30 seconds until everything is evenly coated and the leaves look glossy, not soggy. | Taste and adjust with a pinch more salt or a few grinds of black pepper if needed, then serve immediately while the greens are still crisp.','[\"2 packed cups\",\"½ medium\",\"8 pieces\",\"2 thin slices\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"2 teaspoons\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',160,'mixed-green-salad-ada5778d-a052-401d-865b-c60ca10f3975.png','A mixed green salad with cucumber, cherry tomatoes, and a lemon-olive oil vinaigrette.',10,0,1,9,1,43,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',10,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(521,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','flour, semi-sweet chocolate chips, unsalted butter, softened, brown sugar, packed, white sugar, egg yolk, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Preheat the oven to 175°C and line a small baking sheet with baking paper; set a medium bowl and a silicone spatula nearby. | If keeping kosher, sift the flour into the bowl to check for insects, then add the baking soda and salt and stir for 10 seconds to distribute evenly. | In a separate medium bowl, mix the softened butter, brown sugar, and white sugar with a fork for about 1 minute until smooth and paste-like with no visible butter lumps. | Add the egg yolk and vanilla extract and mix vigorously for 30–45 seconds until the mixture looks slightly lighter and glossy. | Add the flour mixture and fold with a spatula just until no dry flour remains; the dough should look thick and cohesive. Fold in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed. | Scoop the dough into 3 equal mounds (about 1½ tablespoons each) and place them 6–7 cm apart on the lined baking sheet; lightly press each mound to about 2 cm thick with your fingertips. | Bake on the middle rack for 9–11 minutes, until the edge','[\"½ cup\",\"⅓ cup\",\"3 tbsp\",\"3 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 piece\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',520,'chocolate-chip-cookies-8c3f1cee-80af-4b1f-b911-f6f45441675a.png','Classic drop cookies with brown sugar flavor and chocolate chips, baked until the edges set and the centers stay slightly soft. Dairy-based and meat-free to keep the recipe kosher-compliant without mixing meat and dairy.',10,4,6,2,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',26,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(522,'Spaghetti Carbonara','spaghetti, guanciale, cut into 1 cm batons, Pecorino Romano cheese, finely grated, egg yolk, freshly ground black pepper, salt','Bring a medium pot of water to a rolling boil over high heat, salt the water generously, add the spaghetti, and cook until just al dente, stirring in the first minute to prevent sticking. | While the pasta cooks, heat a large skillet over medium heat (about 170–180°C). Add the guanciale and cook 7–9 minutes, stirring often, until the fat renders and the pieces are deep golden and crisp; turn off the heat and keep the rendered fat in the skillet. | In a small bowl, whisk the egg yolk with the Pecorino Romano and black pepper until a thick paste forms. | Using tongs, transfer the spaghetti directly into the skillet with the guanciale. Add 3 tbsp of the hot pasta cooking water and toss over low heat for 20–30 seconds until the noodles are glossy and the water emulsifies with the rendered fat. | Remove the skillet from the heat. Add the egg-and-cheese mixture and toss vigorously for 30–45 seconds, adding 1–2 tbsp more pasta water as needed, until the sauce turns creamy and coats the pasta ','[\"100 g\",\"60 g\",\"30 g\",\"1 large\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',740,'spaghetti-carbonara-9c91dab4-6c4c-472a-ba52-369bfaa6c38c.png','A classic Roman pasta of spaghetti tossed with crisp guanciale, egg yolk, and black pepper, finished with Pecorino Romano for a glossy, creamy sauce without cream.',10,0,11,4,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(523,'Spaghetti Carbonara','dried spaghetti, guanciale, cut into 1 cm strips, Pecorino Romano cheese, finely grated, large egg, egg yolk, freshly ground black pepper, salt','Bring a medium pot of water to a rolling boil over high heat, salt the water with the ½ tsp salt, add the spaghetti, and cook until al dente, about 9–11 minutes; the pasta should be flexible but still have a firm center when bitten. | While the pasta cooks, place the guanciale in a cold 25 cm skillet and set over medium heat; cook, stirring often, until the fat renders and the guanciale is deep golden and crisp at the edges, 7–10 minutes. Turn the heat off and keep the rendered fat in the skillet. | In a medium bowl, whisk the whole egg and egg yolk until smooth, then stir in the grated Pecorino Romano and the black pepper to form a thick paste. | When the pasta is al dente, use tongs to transfer it directly into the skillet with the guanciale (do not drain fully); add 3 tbsp of the starchy pasta cooking water to the skillet and toss over low heat for 20–30 seconds until the spaghetti looks lightly glossy. | Remove the skillet from the heat for 30 seconds to cool slightly, then pour in','[\"100 g\",\"60 g\",\"30 g\",\"1\",\"1\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\"]',740,'spaghetti-carbonara-32888b93-80a6-423d-a3fc-e6a558a473b3.png','Classic Roman pasta with guanciale, eggs, Pecorino Romano, and black pepper, finished with a glossy sauce made from the heat of the pasta.',10,0,12,4,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(524,'Tuna Salad Sandwich','canned tuna in water, drained, sandwich bread slices, mayonnaise, celery stalk, finely chopped, red onion, finely chopped, lettuce leaves, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, olive oil, black pepper, salt','Drain the tuna thoroughly in a fine-mesh strainer for 1 minute, pressing lightly with a spoon until it looks mostly dry and flaky. | In a medium bowl, mix the mayonnaise, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, salt, and black pepper until smooth, then fold in the tuna, breaking it into small flakes with a fork. | Stir in the chopped celery and red onion until evenly distributed; the salad should look creamy but not runny, holding its shape when scooped. | Heat a skillet over medium heat (about 170°C) for 2 minutes. Brush one side of each bread slice with the olive oil, then toast in the skillet for 1–2 minutes per side until golden with crisp edges. | Place the lettuce on one toasted bread slice, mound the tuna salad on top, then close with the second slice. Press gently, wait 1 minute for the filling to set, then slice in half and serve.','[\"1 can (about 140 g drained)\",\"2 slices\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"1 stalk\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"2 leaves\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',520,'tuna-salad-sandwich-0a5275ca-0a22-4b6c-b4be-c6267e7e1d2c.png','A classic deli-style tuna salad mixed with celery and onion, dressed with mayonnaise and lemon, then piled onto toasted bread with lettuce.',8,0,15,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',15,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(525,'Chicken Fried Rice','cooked white rice, chilled, boneless skinless chicken thigh, cut into 1 cm pieces, egg, frozen peas and carrots mix, green onions, thinly sliced, canola oil, soy sauce, toasted sesame oil, garlic clove, minced, salt, black pepper','Pat the chicken dry with paper towels, then season it evenly with the salt and black pepper. | Heat a 25 cm nonstick skillet or wok over medium-high heat until very hot (about 200°C surface temperature), then add 1 tablespoon canola oil and swirl to coat. | Add the chicken in a single layer and cook 2–3 minutes without moving, until browned on the bottom; stir-fry 1–2 minutes more until the pieces are opaque throughout and the edges are deeply browned. Transfer the chicken to a bowl. | Lower heat to medium, add the remaining ½ tablespoon canola oil, then add the garlic and stir constantly for 15–20 seconds until fragrant (do not let it brown). | Add the peas and carrots and stir-fry 2 minutes until hot and any surface frost is gone. | Add the rice and stir-fry 3–4 minutes, pressing and breaking up clumps with a spatula, until the grains look separate and the rice is steaming and lightly toasted in spots. | Push the rice to one side of the pan. Add the egg to the empty side and scramble','[\"1½ cups\",\"120 g\",\"1 large\",\"½ cup\",\"2 pieces\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 piece\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',820,'chicken-fried-rice-07e39e18-61b2-4dee-88db-a9e74f0f6a56.png','A classic Chinese-style fried rice made with day-old rice, chicken, egg, and vegetables, seasoned with soy sauce and sesame oil.',9,0,9,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'EASY','China',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(526,'Falafel Pita','dried chickpeas, pita bread, tahini, water, tomato, cucumber, red onion, fresh parsley, checked and washed, olive oil, lemon juice, garlic clove, ground cumin, ground coriander, baking powder, salt, black pepper','Soak the dried chickpeas in a small bowl with plenty of cool water (at least 5 cm above the chickpeas) for 12–18 hours at room temperature; they should swell and crush with a firm bite, not turn mushy. Drain very well in a fine strainer for 5 minutes until no water drips. | Prep for kosher checking: wash and check the parsley carefully for insects, then pat completely dry. Peel the garlic clove. | Make the falafel mix: in a small food processor, pulse the drained chickpeas, garlic, parsley, cumin, coriander, salt, and black pepper in short bursts, scraping down as needed, until you get a coarse, damp “wet sand” texture that holds together when pinched; avoid making a smooth hummus-like paste. | Transfer to a small bowl, sprinkle in the baking powder, and mix with a spoon for 20 seconds until evenly distributed. Let the mixture rest 10 minutes so it firms up slightly. | Shape: with wet hands, form 6 small balls (about 3 cm wide each) and compress firmly so they don’t crack; if the surfa','[\"½ cup\",\"1 piece\",\"3 tablespoons\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"½ piece\",\"½ piece\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 piece\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¾ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',720,'falafel-pita-17e2be3f-c236-41a5-9c38-ead511dfd9a4.png','Classic Mediterranean falafel served in pita with tahini sauce and fresh salad. Keep ingredients separate from dairy to maintain kosher meat/dairy separation.',9,0,7,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',800,'MID_LEVEL','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(527,'חומוס טחינה','גרגירי חומוס מבושלים ומסוננים, טחינה גולמית, מים, מיץ לימון סחוט טרי, שמן זית, שום, כמון טחון, מלח, פפריקה מתוקה','לבדוק ולשטוף היטב את שן השום כדי לוודא שאין חרקים; אם משתמשים בתבלינים שנשמרו זמן רב, לנפות/לבדוק חזותית שאין מזיקים. | להכניס למעבד מזון את גרגירי החומוס, הטחינה, המים, מיץ הלימון, השום, הכמון והמלח. לעבד 60–90 שניות עד שמתקבל ממרח חלק; אם סמיך מדי, להוסיף עוד 1 כף מים ולעבד עוד 20 שניות, עד שהמרקם קרמי ונמרח. | להעביר את החומוס לקערה חסינת חום קטנה וליישר עם גב כף ליצירת שקע רדוד במרכז. לחמם במיקרוגל בעוצמה גבוהה 30–45 שניות, עד שהחומוס חמים ומעלה אדים קלים. | למזוג את שמן הזית לשקע, ולפזר מעל פפריקה מתוקה. להגיש מיד כשהחומוס חמים והטחינה מבריקה על פני השטח.','[\"1 כוס\",\"3 כפות\",\"3 כפות\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"1 שן\",\"¼ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\"]',520,'חומוס-טחינה-82584ff1-f45d-492d-87ea-b9aced5c513a.png','חומוס חם עם טחינה, שמן זית ופפריקה, מוגש כמו במסעדות חומוס ישראליות. מתאים לכשרות (פרווה), עם הקפדה על בדיקת חרקים בשום ועל ניפוי תבלינים במידת הצורך.',9,0,7,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',10,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(528,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','flour, semi-sweet chocolate chips, unsalted butter, softened, packed brown sugar, white sugar, egg yolk, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Preheat the oven to 175°C and line a small baking sheet with baking paper; set a rack in the middle of the oven. | Sift the flour into a medium bowl to help check for insects and to remove lumps, then whisk in the baking soda and salt until evenly combined. | In a second medium bowl, mix the softened butter, brown sugar, and white sugar with a spoon for 60–90 seconds until the mixture looks glossy and slightly lighter in color; scrape the bowl sides with the spoon. | Add the egg yolk and vanilla extract and stir vigorously for 30–45 seconds until smooth and cohesive with no streaks of yolk visible. | Add the dry mixture to the butter mixture and stir just until no dry flour remains; the dough should look thick and slightly sticky. Fold in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed. | Shape the dough into 1 thick ball (about 5–6 cm wide and about 2.5 cm tall) and place it in the center of the lined baking sheet; do not flatten it. | Bake for 10–12 minutes, until the edges are set and ','[\"⅓ cup\",\"3 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 piece\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',410,'chocolate-chip-cookies-262970ce-2485-4290-9779-446121ca7191.png','A single-batch baked cookie with crisp edges and a soft center, made with dairy and without any meat to keep it kosher-style compliant.',10,3,5,2,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',32,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(529,'Chicken Salad Sandwich','cooked chicken breast, shredded, bread slices, celery stalk, finely diced, red onion, finely diced, dill pickle, finely chopped, lettuce leaves, washed and checked for insects, tomato slices, pareve mayonnaise, Dijon mustard, olive oil, lemon juice, black pepper, salt','Wash the lettuce leaves thoroughly and check for insects; spin or pat completely dry with paper towels so the sandwich stays crisp. | In a medium bowl, mix the pareve mayonnaise, Dijon mustard, lemon juice, salt, and black pepper until smooth and glossy, about 20 seconds with a spoon. | Add the shredded cooked chicken, diced celery, diced red onion, and chopped dill pickle; fold with a spoon for 30–45 seconds just until evenly coated and the mixture looks creamy with no dry chicken. | Heat a nonstick skillet over medium heat (about 170–180°C). Brush one side of each bread slice with olive oil, then toast oil-side down for 1–2 minutes until golden with lightly crisp edges; flip and toast 30–60 seconds more, then remove to a plate. | Assemble: place 1 toasted slice on the plate, add the lettuce, then the chicken salad in an even layer, then the tomato slices; close with the second toast slice. | Let the sandwich sit 1 minute to set, then slice diagonally with a serrated knife; the fillin','[\"1 cup\",\"2 slices\",\"1\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"2 leaves\",\"2 slices\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',620,'chicken-salad-sandwich-eb51f2db-6209-4102-97df-440c6b06d144.png','A classic deli-style chicken salad on toasted bread with crisp vegetables; pareve dressing keeps it kosher with meat.',8,0,16,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',15,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(530,'Chicken Shawarma Pita','boneless skinless chicken thigh, pita bread, cucumber, tomato, red onion, tahini paste, water, lemon juice, olive oil, garlic clove, salt, ground cumin, ground paprika, ground coriander, ground turmeric, ground black pepper','Pat the chicken dry with paper towels. In a medium bowl, finely grate the garlic clove, then mix in olive oil, salt, cumin, paprika, coriander, turmeric, and black pepper. Add the chicken thigh and rub thoroughly; let stand 10 minutes at room temperature while you prep the vegetables. | Dice the cucumber and tomato into 1 cm pieces. Thinly slice the red onion. Set the vegetables aside. | Make the tahini sauce in a small bowl by whisking tahini paste, water, and lemon juice for 30–45 seconds until smooth and pale; it should be pourable. If it looks too thick, whisk in 1 more teaspoon water until it ribbons off the spoon. | Heat a 25 cm cast-iron skillet or heavy nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until a drop of water sizzles immediately (about 200°C surface temperature). Place the chicken in the dry skillet and cook 5–6 minutes on the first side until deeply browned with crisp edges, then flip and cook 4–5 minutes more until the center is no longer pink and an instant-read thermome','[\"200 g\",\"1 piece\",\"½ piece\",\"1 small piece\",\"¼ piece\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 piece\",\"¾ tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',690,'chicken-shawarma-pita-5d1457f0-c056-4828-a847-54a4cf7fc67d.png','A classic lunch pita filled with spiced chicken, salad, and tahini sauce; keep meat and dairy separate for a kosher meal.',8,0,13,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(531,'Lasagna Bolognese','dry lasagna noodles, ground beef (90–95% lean), passata, whole milk, mozzarella cheese, shredded, Parmesan cheese, finely grated, yellow onion, finely chopped, carrot, finely diced, celery stalk, finely diced, olive oil, butter, flour, tomato paste, garlic cloves, minced, dried oregano, black pepper, salt','Heat the oven to 190°C and set a rack in the middle. Lightly butter a 20×20 cm baking dish and set aside. | Make the ragù: heat a large skillet over medium-high heat (about 200°C). Add olive oil, then onion, carrot, and celery with ½ tsp salt; cook 6–8 minutes, stirring, until softened and the onion looks translucent. Add garlic and cook 30 seconds until fragrant. Add ground beef and cook 6–8 minutes, breaking it up with a wooden spoon, until no pink remains and browned bits appear. Stir in tomato paste for 1 minute until it darkens slightly, then add passata, oregano, black pepper, and ½ tsp salt. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 12–15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until thick enough that a spoon dragged through leaves a brief trail. | Make the béchamel: in a small saucepan over medium heat, melt butter until foaming subsides (about 1 minute). Whisk in flour and cook 1 minute until it smells slightly nutty but is not browned. Slowly whisk in milk in a thin stream. Add 1 tsp salt','[\"200 g\",\"350 g\",\"2 cups (480 ml)\",\"2 cups (480 ml)\",\"150 g\",\"40 g\",\"1 medium\",\"1 medium\",\"1 stalk\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"2 cloves\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"2 tsp\"]',1970,'lasagna-bolognese-0a29e633-2619-410b-ad88-6a72c7f2baed.png','Classic layered lasagna with beef ragù, béchamel, and cheeses baked until bubbling and browned.',10,0,11,4,3,43,'1','0','0','0','0','[]',80,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(532,'Shakshuka','large eggs, canned crushed tomatoes, red bell pepper, diced (about 1 cm), yellow onion, finely diced, olive oil, water, garlic cloves, minced, tomato paste, ground cumin, sweet paprika, salt, ground black pepper, cayenne pepper','Prep the vegetables: dice the onion and bell pepper, mince the garlic, and set everything by the stove; open the tomatoes and measure the tomato paste, spices, salt, and water. | Heat a 20 cm skillet over medium heat (about 175°C). Add the olive oil, then add the onion and bell pepper and cook, stirring, for 6–8 minutes until softened and the onion turns translucent with lightly golden edges. | Add the minced garlic and cook for 30 seconds, stirring constantly, until fragrant but not browned. | Stir in the tomato paste, cumin, paprika, black pepper, and cayenne and cook for 1 minute until the paste darkens slightly and coats the vegetables. | Add the crushed tomatoes, salt, and water. Bring to a gentle simmer over medium-high heat, then reduce to medium-low and simmer 8–10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the sauce thickens enough that a spoon dragged through leaves a trail that slowly fills in. | Make 2 shallow wells in the sauce with the back of a spoon. Crack the eggs into the ','[\"2\",\"1 cup\",\"½\",\"½\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"2\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',430,'shakshuka-02cab61e-9c9d-46ee-a556-55fafc09410e.png','Eggs poached in a spiced tomato and pepper sauce, served straight from the skillet.',8,0,10,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(533,'Chicken Salad Sandwich','cooked chicken breast, chopped, bread slices, mayonnaise, celery stalk, finely diced, red onion, finely diced, lettuce leaves, washed and checked for insects, tomato slices, olive oil, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, black pepper, salt','Wash the lettuce leaves thoroughly and check for insects; pat dry with paper towels, then slice the tomato and set both aside. | In a medium bowl, mix the chopped cooked chicken breast, mayonnaise, diced celery, diced red onion, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, salt, and black pepper for 30–45 seconds with a spoon until evenly coated; the mixture should look creamy but not runny. | Heat a nonstick skillet over medium heat (about 170°C) for 2 minutes; brush one side of each bread slice with olive oil. | Toast the bread in the skillet, oiled-side down, for 1–2 minutes until golden with crisp edges; flip and toast 30–60 seconds more, then transfer to a plate. | Build the sandwich by layering one toasted slice with the lettuce, then the chicken salad, then tomato slices; close with the second slice, press gently, and cut in half. The bread should be crisp and the filling cold/room temperature.','[\"1 cup\",\"2 slices\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"1 piece\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"2 pieces\",\"2 slices\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',560,'chicken-salad-sandwich-649c77b1-24d7-4263-b1c6-f6ba2371dd6f.png','A deli-style chicken salad served on toasted bread with crisp lettuce and tomato; keep it kosher by using mayonnaise (no dairy) and checking greens for insects.',8,0,14,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',15,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(534,'Greek Salad','ripe tomato, cut into 2 cm chunks, cucumber, cut into 2 cm chunks, feta cheese, cut into 2 cm pieces, pitted Kalamata olives, red onion, thinly sliced, extra-virgin olive oil, red wine vinegar, dried oregano, salt, black pepper','Wash the tomato and cucumber well; for kosher practice, inspect the tomato and cucumber and check the red onion slices for any insects, then pat everything dry so the dressing clings. | Cut the tomato and cucumber into 2 cm chunks; thinly slice the red onion. Put them in a medium bowl and add the olives. | Add the olive oil, red wine vinegar, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper. Toss with a spoon for 20–30 seconds until the vegetables look glossy and a little liquid collects at the bottom of the bowl. | Add the feta pieces on top and gently fold 2–3 times so the feta stays in distinct chunks; the salad is ready when the feta is lightly coated and the vegetables are evenly seasoned.','[\"1 medium (about 170 g)\",\"1 small (about 150 g)\",\"50 g\",\"10 pieces\",\"¼ small (about 25 g)\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',380,'greek-salad-1632126b-7c33-478d-ab24-455b6275d973.png','A classic chopped salad of tomato, cucumber, red onion, olives, and feta dressed with olive oil and oregano. For kosher, keep it dairy (no meat added) and check vegetables and herbs for insects.',9,0,5,8,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',12,'EASY','Greece',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(535,'Spaghetti Bolognese','dried spaghetti, ground beef, canned crushed tomatoes, onion, finely chopped, carrot, finely diced, celery stalk, finely diced, tomato paste, olive oil, garlic clove, minced, dry red wine, water, salt, black pepper, dried oregano, bay leaf','Prepare the vegetables: finely chop the onion and mince the garlic; dice the carrot and celery into 3–4 mm pieces so they soften quickly and disappear into the sauce. | Heat olive oil in a 20–24 cm heavy skillet or small pot over medium heat (about 170°C). Add onion, carrot, and celery with ¼ tsp salt and cook 6–8 minutes, stirring, until softened and lightly golden at the edges. | Add the garlic and cook 30 seconds, stirring constantly, until fragrant (do not let it brown). | Add the ground beef and raise heat to medium-high. Break it up with a wooden spoon and cook 5–7 minutes until no longer pink and there are browned bits on the bottom; the meat should look crumbly and lightly caramelized. | Stir in the tomato paste and cook 1 minute until it darkens slightly and coats the meat and vegetables. | Pour in the red wine and scrape the bottom well to dissolve browned bits. Simmer 2–3 minutes until the wine smell softens and the liquid reduces by about half. | Add crushed tomatoes, water','[\"100 g\",\"150 g\",\"1 cup (240 ml)\",\"½ small onion\",\"½ small carrot\",\"½ stalk\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 clove\",\"¼ cup (60 ml)\",\"¼ cup (60 ml)\",\"¾ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"1 leaf\"]',820,'spaghetti-bolognese-82ed1c45-f1c7-441c-a6ed-c0919f2e8aeb.png','Classic Italian pasta with a slow-simmered tomato and beef sauce. Made without dairy to keep meat and dairy separate under kosher-style cooking.',10,0,10,5,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',45,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(536,'Chicken Shawarma Wrap','boneless skinless chicken thigh, pita bread, cucumber, tomato, tahini, lemon juice, olive oil, water, garlic clove, salt, ground cumin, paprika, ground coriander, ground turmeric, black pepper','Pat the chicken thigh dry with paper towels, then place it on a cutting board; cut into 2 cm strips so it cooks quickly and evenly. | In a medium bowl, mix the olive oil, salt, ground cumin, paprika, ground coriander, ground turmeric, and black pepper until a paste forms; add the chicken strips and toss for 30 seconds until fully coated, then let stand 10 minutes at room temperature while you prep the vegetables. | Wash the cucumber and tomato well; dice both into 1 cm pieces and set aside in a small bowl. | Make the tahini sauce in a small bowl: finely grate the garlic clove, then whisk in the tahini and lemon juice; whisk in the water 1 tablespoon at a time until smooth and pourable, with a thick-drizzle consistency. | Heat a 25 cm cast-iron skillet or heavy nonstick skillet over medium-high heat (about 200°C) for 2 minutes until very hot; add the chicken in a single layer and cook 3 minutes without moving, until browned with crisp edges. | Flip the chicken and cook 2–3 minutes more,','[\"200 g\",\"1 piece\",\"½ piece\",\"1 small piece\",\"3 tablespoons\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"1 piece\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',780,'chicken-shawarma-wrap-eb972b09-2b44-4e24-b2d1-9a0095a42087.png','A kosher chicken shawarma wrap with spiced chicken, chopped salad, and tahini sauce.',9,0,12,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(537,'Apple Pie','flour, apple, peeled and thinly sliced, unsalted butter, cold and cubed, water, sugar, lemon juice, cornstarch, salt, ground cinnamon','Heat the oven to 190°C. Place a small oven-safe dish (about 12–14 cm wide) on a rimmed baking sheet to catch any drips. | Make the crust: In a medium bowl, mix flour and salt. Add cold butter cubes and rub in with fingertips (or cut in with a fork) for 1–2 minutes until you have pea-size pieces and some sandy bits. Drizzle in water 1 tablespoon at a time, tossing with a fork just until the dough holds together when squeezed; it should look shaggy, not wet. | Form the dough into a flat disk, wrap, and chill in the freezer for 10 minutes so the butter firms up. Roll the dough on a lightly floured counter into a 15 cm circle, then lay it into the small dish, letting the excess hang over the edges. | Make the filling: In the same bowl, toss sliced apple with sugar, lemon juice, cornstarch, and cinnamon until no dry starch remains and the slices look evenly coated. | Fill and seal: Pile the apples into the lined dish, pressing lightly so there are fewer gaps. Fold the overhanging dough over','[\"½ cup\",\"1 medium\",\"3 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',520,'apple-pie-ae733cdb-0f2a-439a-8fbb-b19fe920b29f.png','Single-crust apple pie baked in a small oven-safe dish, with a buttery flaky crust and tender spiced apples.',9,2,4,3,1,43,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',70,'MID_LEVEL','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(540,'Chicken Fried Rice','cooked white rice, cold, boneless skinless chicken thigh, cut into 1 cm pieces, large egg, frozen peas and carrots mix, yellow onion, finely chopped, canola oil, garlic clove, minced, soy sauce, toasted sesame oil, ground black pepper, salt','Place the cold rice in a medium bowl and break up clumps with your fingers or a fork until the grains are mostly separated; set aside so it warms slightly while you prep. | Heat a 25–28 cm wok or large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until a drop of water sizzles on contact (about 200°C). Add 1 tsp canola oil, then add the chicken and spread it into a single layer. Cook 2 minutes without moving to brown, then stir-fry 2–3 minutes until the chicken is cooked through and no longer pink in the center; transfer to a plate. | Return the pan to medium-high heat. Add 1 tsp canola oil, add the egg, and scramble with a spatula for 45–60 seconds until just set in soft curds; transfer to the plate with the chicken. | Add the remaining 1 tbsp canola oil to the pan. Add the onion and peas-and-carrots. Stir-fry 2–3 minutes until the onion turns translucent and the vegetables are hot and glossy. | Add the garlic and stir constantly for 20–30 seconds until fragrant (do not let it brown). Add th','[\"1 cup\",\"100 g\",\"1\",\"⅓ cup\",\"¼ cup\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',650,'chicken-fried-rice-2dca1b04-c753-4cdd-abc5-4333f02a50b6.png','A classic Chinese-style fried rice made with chicken, egg, and vegetables, seasoned with soy sauce and toasted sesame oil.',9,4,9,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'MID_LEVEL','China',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(541,'Hummus with Tahini','cooked chickpeas, drained and rinsed, tahini paste, water, fresh lemon juice, olive oil, garlic clove, ground cumin, salt, paprika','Rinse the chickpeas very well under running water in a fine strainer, then drain for 1 minute; briefly check the garlic clove for any spoilage and peel it. | Add the tahini paste, water, fresh lemon juice, garlic clove, ground cumin, and salt to a small food processor bowl. Process on high for 30–45 seconds, scraping down the sides once, until the mixture turns pale and thick. | Add the cooked chickpeas and process on high for 1–2 minutes, scraping down once, until very smooth; if it looks too stiff or grainy, add 1 tablespoon water and blend 15–20 seconds more until creamy and glossy. | Taste and adjust with an extra pinch of salt if needed (the hummus should taste slightly brighter than you want; it mellows after 2 minutes of rest). | Spoon into a shallow bowl and use the back of a spoon to make a swirl. Drizzle the olive oil over the top and dust evenly with paprika; serve immediately or let stand 10 minutes for the texture to settle.','[\"1 cup\",\"3 tablespoons\",\"3 tablespoons\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 piece\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',420,'hummus-with-tahini-6c6a8072-175a-40f1-9cb9-95f831ca19eb.png','A classic Mediterranean chickpea spread blended with tahini, lemon, and garlic, finished with olive oil and paprika. This version is pareve and fits kosher guidelines (with brief produce-check notes).',9,4,7,8,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',10,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(542,'Shakshuka','canned crushed tomatoes, large eggs, red bell pepper, diced (about 1 cm), yellow onion, finely diced, bread slices, olive oil, tomato paste, water, garlic cloves, minced, salt, ground cumin, sweet paprika, black pepper, cayenne pepper','Set a 20 cm nonstick or stainless-steel skillet over medium heat (about 180°C). Add the olive oil; when it shimmers, add the onion and red bell pepper and cook 6–8 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon, until softened and the onion turns translucent with lightly golden edges. | Add the minced garlic, cumin, sweet paprika, black pepper, and cayenne pepper. Stir constantly for 30 seconds until fragrant, keeping the heat at medium so the garlic does not brown. | Stir in the tomato paste for 30 seconds, then add the crushed tomatoes, water, and salt. Bring to a steady simmer over medium-high heat (about 200°C), then reduce to medium-low (about 160°C) and simmer 6–8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the sauce thickens enough that a spoon dragged through it leaves a trail that slowly fills in. | Use the spoon to make 2 shallow wells in the sauce. Crack the eggs into the wells. Cover the skillet with a lid and cook 4–6 minutes on low heat, until the whites are set and opaque and the yolks','[\"1 cup\",\"2\",\"½\",\"½\",\"2\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"¼ cup\",\"2\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',520,'shakshuka-c12c73fa-8973-42ab-b3ae-f830939f11c6.png','Eggs poached in a spiced tomato and pepper sauce, served straight from the skillet with bread.',8,12,7,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(543,'Chicken Shawarma Pita','boneless skinless chicken thigh, pita bread, cucumber, tomato, red onion, tahini paste, water, olive oil, lemon juice, garlic clove, ground cumin, ground coriander, sweet paprika, ground turmeric, ground black pepper, salt','Pat the chicken thigh dry with paper towels, then slice into 1 cm strips on a cutting board; in a medium bowl mix olive oil, 1 tbsp lemon juice, cumin, coriander, paprika, turmeric, black pepper, and ¼ tsp salt, add the chicken and toss until evenly coated, then let stand 10 minutes at room temperature. | Make the tahini sauce in a small bowl by whisking tahini paste with water, the remaining ½ tbsp lemon juice, the garlic clove finely grated, and the remaining ¼ tsp salt until smooth and pourable; if it seizes, whisk 1 more tbsp water until it loosens and looks glossy. | Dice the cucumber and tomato into 1 cm pieces and thinly slice the red onion; combine on a plate and lightly toss to distribute. | Heat a 25 cm cast-iron skillet or heavy nonstick skillet over medium-high heat (about 200°C) for 3 minutes until a drop of water sizzles on contact; add the chicken in a single layer and cook 3 minutes without moving until deep golden patches form, then stir and cook 3–4 minutes more until','[\"200 g\",\"1 piece\",\"½ piece\",\"1 small piece\",\"¼ piece\",\"2 tbsp\",\"3 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1 piece\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"½ tsp\"]',710,'chicken-shawarma-pita-d0601bb7-8425-42a6-86e8-471fe5b5e9e9.png','Sliced spiced chicken with tahini sauce and salad stuffed into warm pita; keep meat and dairy separate for kosher cooking.',9,8,15,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(544,'Roast Chicken Thighs and Potatoes','bone-in, skin-on chicken thighs, Yukon Gold potatoes, cut into 3 cm chunks, water, olive oil, lemon juice, garlic cloves, finely grated, Dijon mustard, salt, black pepper, paprika, dried oregano','Heat the oven to 220°C. Pat the chicken thighs dry with paper towels so the skin browns well. Use a small rimmed baking dish (about 20×20 cm) or a small sheet pan. | In the baking dish, whisk together the olive oil, lemon juice, finely grated garlic, Dijon mustard, salt, black pepper, paprika, and dried oregano until smooth. Add the potato chunks and toss until coated. | Nestle the chicken thighs skin-side up among the potatoes and rub any remaining marinade over the chicken. Pour the water into the dish along the side (not over the chicken skin) to create juices without preventing browning. | Roast for 40–50 minutes, turning the potatoes once at the 25-minute mark. The dish is done when the chicken skin is deep golden-brown, the thickest part of the thigh reaches 74°C on an instant-read thermometer, and the potatoes are tender when pierced with a knife. | Remove the dish from the oven and rest 5 minutes. Spoon the pan juices over the chicken and potatoes; scrape up any browned bits fr','[\"2 pieces (about 300 g total)\",\"1½ cups (about 250 g)\",\"¼ cup\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"2 cloves\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"¾ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\"]',820,'roast-chicken-thighs-and-potatoes-785efd75-c831-4a2c-aae2-701a224cc3f4.png','Bone-in chicken thighs and potatoes roasted together with lemon, garlic, and herbs until browned, with pan juices spooned over at the end.',9,4,12,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',60,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(545,'Shakshuka','canned crushed tomatoes, large eggs, red bell pepper, diced (about 1 cm), yellow onion, finely diced, olive oil, garlic cloves, finely minced, water, tomato paste, ground cumin, sweet paprika, salt, black pepper, cayenne pepper','Set a 20 cm non-stick skillet over medium heat for 2 minutes, then add the olive oil and warm it until it shimmers. | Add the diced onion and red bell pepper and cook over medium heat for 6–8 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon, until the onion turns translucent and the pepper softens. | Add the minced garlic and cook for 30 seconds, stirring constantly, until fragrant but not browned. | Stir in the tomato paste, cumin, sweet paprika, salt, black pepper, and cayenne; cook for 30–45 seconds until the paste darkens slightly and the spices smell toasted. | Add the crushed tomatoes and water, bring to a gentle simmer over medium-high heat, then reduce to medium-low and simmer for 6–8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the sauce thickens enough that a spoon leaves a trail that slowly fills in. | Use the back of a spoon to make 2 shallow wells in the sauce; crack an egg into each well. Cover the skillet and cook over low heat for 5–7 minutes, until the whites are set and opaque and the ','[\"1 cup\",\"2\",\"½ pepper\",\"½ small onion\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"2\",\"¼ cup\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',430,'shakshuka-9fe38b1e-e02d-486c-a515-ec85c6816dad.png','Eggs gently poached in a spiced tomato and pepper sauce, served straight from the skillet.',8,11,8,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(546,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','flour, semi-sweet chocolate chips, unsalted butter, softened, packed brown sugar, white sugar, egg yolk, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Preheat the oven to 175°C and line a small baking sheet with parchment paper; if using flour, sift it well to check for insects, then set it aside. | In a medium bowl, cream the softened butter with the brown sugar and white sugar using a spoon or silicone spatula for about 1 minute, until smooth and paste-like (no dry sugar pockets). | Add the egg yolk and vanilla extract and mix vigorously for 30–45 seconds, until glossy and fully combined. | Add the flour, baking soda, and salt; mix just until no dry flour remains and the dough looks thick and cohesive, scraping the bowl as needed (do not overmix). | Fold in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed. | Scoop the dough into 3 mounds (about 1½ tbsp each) and place them 5–6 cm apart on the lined sheet; gently press each mound to about 1.5 cm thick so they bake evenly. | Bake on the middle rack for 9–11 minutes, until the edges are set and lightly browned while the centers still look slightly soft and puffy. | Cool on the baking shee','[\"½ cup\",\"⅓ cup\",\"3 tbsp\",\"3 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 yolk\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',520,'chocolate-chip-cookies-b7731413-5fff-4464-a4cc-6ddb14ddf67a.png','Classic drop cookies with brown sugar, butter, and chocolate chips, baked until the edges set and the centers stay slightly soft. This dairy-based dessert contains no meat, keeping it kosher in a dairy meal context.',10,34,6,2,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',30,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(547,'Beef Hamburger','ground beef (80–85% lean), hamburger bun, yellow onion, grated, ketchup, tomato, sliced, iceberg lettuce leaves, washed and checked for insects, dill pickle slices, canola oil, salt, black pepper, garlic powder','Pat the ground beef dry with paper towels. In a medium bowl, combine the ground beef, grated onion, salt, black pepper, and garlic powder; mix with your fingertips for 15–20 seconds just until evenly combined (do not knead or compress). | Shape the mixture into a patty about 11 cm wide and about 2 cm thick. Press a shallow dimple (about 6 cm wide) into the center, about 5 mm deep, to reduce bulging during cooking. Keep the edges slightly thicker than the center. | Heat a 25 cm cast-iron skillet or heavy stainless-steel skillet over medium-high heat until very hot (about 200°C; a drop of water should sizzle and evaporate immediately), about 3 minutes. Add the canola oil and swirl to coat. | Lay the patty in the skillet and cook undisturbed for 3½–4 minutes, until the bottom has a deep brown crust and juices start to bead on top. Flip with a thin spatula and cook 3–4 minutes more, until browned and the center feels springy-firm; for safety, cook to 71°C in the center if using an instant-','[\"170 g\",\"1 bun\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"2 slices\",\"1–2 leaves\",\"3 slices\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',650,'beef-hamburger-0441286e-9caf-4f28-8042-e3b933b460ad.png','A classic beef burger with toasted bun and standard toppings, kept kosher by avoiding all dairy ingredients.',10,6,12,4,1,43,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(548,'פלאפל בפיתה','חומוס יבש מושרה ומסונן היטב, פיתה, טחינה גולמית, שמן קנולה לטיגון, בצל, עלי כוסברה שטופים ובדוקים מחרקים, שום, עגבנייה, מלפפון, לימון, מים, קמח חומוס, אבקת אפייה, כמון טחון, כוסברה טחונה, פלפל שחור, מלח','להשרות את החומוס בקערה עם הרבה מים (לפחות פי 3 נפח) למשך 12–18 שעות בטמפרטורת חדר; לסנן ולשטוף היטב עד שהמים צלולים, ואז לסנן 5 דקות במסננת כדי שהגרגרים יהיו יבשים יחסית למגע. | להכין את סלט הירקות: לקצוץ קטן עגבנייה ומלפפון, לשים בקערית ולתבל ב-⅛ כפית מלח וב-1 כפית מיץ לימון (מהחצי לימון). לערבב ולהניח בצד 5 דקות שיגיר מעט נוזלים. | להכין טחינה: בקערית לערבב טחינה גולמית עם 4 כפות מים ו-2 כפיות מיץ לימון (מהחצי לימון) ו-⅛ כפית מלח עד שמתקבלת טחינה בהירה וסמיכה שנוזלת לאט מהכף; אם סמיך מדי להוסיף עוד 1 כף מים ולהמשיך לערבב 20 שניות. | להכין את תערובת הפלאפל: במעבד מזון לשים חומוס מושרה ומסונן, בצל, עלי כוסברה, שום, כמון, כוסברה טחונה, פלפל שחור ו-½ כפית מלח. לטחון בפולסים 45–60 שניות, לעצור ולגרד דפנות, ולהמשיך עוד 20–30 שניות עד שמתקבלים פירורים אחידים שנדבקים כשצובטים ביד (לא מחית חלקה). להעביר לקערה ולערבב פנימה קמח חומוס ואבקת אפייה. | לחמם שמן קנולה בסיר קטן ועמוק (כ-14–16 ס\"מ קוטר) על חום בינוני-גבוה עד 175–180°C; אם אין מדחום, להשליך פירור קטן מהתערובת—הוא צריך לבעבע מיד ולעלות ','[\"¾ כוס\",\"1 יח׳\",\"3 כפות\",\"1½ כוס\",\"¼ יח׳\",\"¼ כוס\",\"1 שן\",\"½ יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"5 כפות\",\"1 כף\",\"½ כפית\",\"½ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\",\"⅛ כפית\",\"¾ כפית\"]',820,'פלאפל-בפיתה-b773fc33-95ff-4e2d-a976-8760df00fa15.png','פלאפל ישראלי קלאסי: כדורי חומוס מתובלים ומטוגנים, מוגשים בפיתה עם טחינה וסלט קצוץ. המתכון פרווה ומתאים לכשרות; יש לשטוף היטב ולבדוק שאין חרקים בכוסברה.',8,8,10,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',815,'MID_LEVEL','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(549,'Chicken Soup','bone-in chicken thighs, water, carrot, celery stalk, yellow onion, fresh parsley, fresh dill, olive oil, salt, ground black pepper, turmeric','Trim any excess skin from the chicken thighs with a knife; rinse the carrot, celery, parsley, and dill well and check the herbs for insects, then slice the carrot into ½ cm rounds, slice the celery ½ cm thick, and finely chop the onion. | Heat a medium pot over medium heat for 1 minute, add the olive oil, then add the onion and cook for 3 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon, until softened and lightly translucent (not browned). | Add the chicken thighs, salt, black pepper, and turmeric and stir for 30 seconds to coat; add the water and scrape the bottom of the pot to release any stuck bits. | Bring to a strong simmer over medium-high heat (about 8–10 minutes), then reduce to low so the surface gently bubbles; skim off any foam with a spoon for the clearest broth. | Add the carrot and celery, cover partially with a lid, and simmer on low for 45 minutes, until the chicken is very tender and the broth is golden. | Turn off the heat and stir in the chopped parsley and dill; rest 5 minute','[\"2 pieces (about 300 g)\",\"3 cups (720 ml)\",\"1 piece (about 90 g)\",\"1 piece (about 60 g)\",\"½ piece (about 80 g)\",\"2 tablespoons, chopped\",\"1 tablespoon, chopped\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',520,'chicken-soup-85b27770-373f-4d2c-95fe-993d7fc865b3.png','Clear chicken and vegetable soup simmered with herbs until the broth is golden and the chicken is tender.',9,6,7,8,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',70,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(550,'Greek Salad','ripe tomato, cut into 2 cm chunks, cucumber, cut into 2 cm chunks, feta cheese, cut into 2 cm pieces, red onion, thinly sliced, pitted Kalamata olives, extra-virgin olive oil, fresh lemon juice, dried oregano, salt, black pepper','Wash the tomato and cucumber; for kosher-style produce handling, rinse well and visually check the vegetables for any insects or debris, then cut the tomato and cucumber into 2 cm chunks and place in a medium bowl. | Add the sliced red onion and the olives to the bowl, then toss gently for 10 seconds to distribute without crushing the tomato. | In a small bowl, whisk the olive oil, lemon juice, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper with a fork for 15–20 seconds until the dressing looks slightly thickened and unified. | Pour the dressing over the salad and toss with two spoons for about 15 seconds, just until everything is lightly glossy. | Add the feta pieces on top and give one very gentle final toss (or leave the feta on top); rest 2 minutes at room temperature so the flavors settle, then serve.','[\"1 medium\",\"½ medium\",\"50 g\",\"¼ small\",\"10 pieces\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1½ tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',360,'greek-salad-b3c07cce-13c6-4166-a8e2-270e8127002b.png','A classic Greek salad with tomatoes, cucumber, olives, and feta, dressed with olive oil and oregano.',9,6,4,8,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',12,'EASY','Greece',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(551,'Greek Salad','ripe tomato, cut into 2 cm chunks, cucumber, cut into 2 cm chunks, feta cheese, cut into 1.5 cm pieces, red bell pepper, cut into 2 cm chunks, red onion, thinly sliced, pitted Kalamata olives, extra-virgin olive oil, fresh lemon juice, dried oregano, salt, black pepper','Wash the tomato, cucumber, bell pepper, and onion thoroughly and check them for insects where relevant; pat dry with a clean towel, then cut the tomato, cucumber, and bell pepper into 2 cm chunks and thinly slice the onion. | Add the tomato, cucumber, bell pepper, onion, and olives to a medium bowl and toss for 10 seconds with a spoon until evenly mixed. | In a small bowl, whisk the olive oil, lemon juice, oregano, salt, and black pepper for 15 seconds until slightly thickened and uniform. | Pour the dressing over the vegetables and toss gently for 20–30 seconds, just until the surfaces look glossy. | Add the feta on top, toss once or twice very gently to avoid breaking it up too much, and let the salad stand 2 minutes so the oregano blooms; serve when the vegetables look juicy at the bottom of the bowl.','[\"1 medium\",\"½ medium\",\"40 g\",\"¼ pepper\",\"3 tablespoons\",\"8 pieces\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"2 teaspoons\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',360,'greek-salad-9202ffb3-ecdb-4cb6-bbf8-de8cfd5a8f88.png','A classic chopped salad of tomatoes, cucumber, onion, olives, and feta, dressed with olive oil and oregano. For kosher preparation, wash and check the vegetables for insects before chopping.',9,6,4,8,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',12,'EASY','Greece',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(552,'Spaghetti Carbonara','dried spaghetti, guanciale, cut into 1 cm strips, Pecorino Romano cheese, finely grated, large egg, egg yolk, freshly ground black pepper, salt','Bring a medium pot of water to a rolling boil over high heat; salt the water generously, then cook the spaghetti until just al dente, stirring in the first minute to prevent sticking, about 8–10 minutes (it should still have a firm center when bitten). | While the pasta cooks, place the guanciale in a cold medium skillet and set over medium heat; cook, stirring occasionally, until the fat renders and the pieces are deep golden with crisp edges, 6–9 minutes, then turn off the heat and keep the pan warm. | In a medium bowl, whisk the egg, egg yolk, grated Pecorino Romano, and black pepper until a thick, cohesive paste forms; it should look glossy and lightly loosen when whisked. | Using tongs, transfer the spaghetti directly into the skillet with the guanciale, tossing for 30–60 seconds to coat in the rendered fat; add 3 tbsp pasta cooking water and toss until the pasta looks slick and lightly steamy (not aggressively boiling). | Wait 30 seconds for the pan to cool slightly (no sizzling ','[\"100 g\",\"60 g\",\"30 g\",\"1 piece\",\"1 piece\",\"1 tsp\",\"½ tsp\"]',690,'spaghetti-carbonara-25ef3c0f-22d3-4e86-8d97-0106088ac34b.png','Classic Roman pasta with eggs, pecorino, black pepper, and cured pork, tossed off the heat for a silky sauce.',10,3,13,4,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(553,'Chicken Piccata','boneless skinless chicken breast, chicken stock, flour, olive oil, lemon, capers, drained, garlic clove, parsley leaves, salt, black pepper','Place the chicken breast between two sheets of baking paper and pound with a rolling pin or the bottom of a small saucepan to an even 1 cm thickness; pat dry with paper towels. | Put the flour in a shallow bowl. Season the chicken on both sides with the salt and black pepper, then dredge in the flour and shake off excess until you have a thin, even coating. | Heat a 25 cm skillet over medium-high heat until the oil shimmers (about 190°C). Add the chicken and cook 3–4 minutes on the first side and 2–3 minutes on the second side, until deep golden brown and the thickest part reaches 74°C; transfer to a plate. | Lower heat to medium. Add the garlic clove (finely grated) to the same skillet and stir 20–30 seconds until fragrant, keeping it from browning. | Add the chicken stock, scraping the browned bits with a wooden spoon. Simmer 2–3 minutes until the liquid reduces slightly and looks glossy. | Squeeze in 2 tablespoons lemon juice, add the capers, and simmer 1 minute. Taste and adjust wi','[\"1 piece (about 180 g)\",\"½ cup\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"1 piece\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 piece\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',520,'chicken-piccata-0c1d5a1c-4e03-4413-a95f-f2cd9d740f97.png','Pan-seared chicken cutlet finished in a lemon-caper sauce thickened with flour. This version is kosher by using olive oil instead of butter.',8,2,19,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(554,'Chicken Noodle Soup','bone-in chicken thigh, water, carrot, celery stalk, yellow onion, egg noodles, olive oil, fresh parsley, salt, ground black pepper','Wash and check the parsley leaves carefully for insects, then rinse and pat dry; peel the carrot, trim the celery, and cut the carrot and celery into 1 cm pieces, and cut the onion into 2–3 cm chunks. | Heat the olive oil in a small pot (about 2 liters) over medium heat; add the onion, carrot, and celery and cook, stirring with a wooden spoon, for 4–5 minutes until the onion looks glossy and slightly softened (not browned). | Add the chicken thigh, water, salt, and black pepper; raise heat to high until you see a steady boil, then reduce to low so it simmers gently with small bubbles for 35–45 minutes, skimming any foam with a spoon, until the chicken is cooked through and easily pulls from the bone. | Transfer the chicken to a plate with tongs; let it cool 3–4 minutes, then remove skin and bone and shred the meat into bite-size pieces, returning the shredded chicken to the pot. | Bring the soup back to a gentle simmer over medium-low heat; add the egg noodles and cook 6–8 minutes, sti','[\"1 piece (about 200 g)\",\"2½ cups\",\"1 small (about 80 g)\",\"1 piece (about 60 g)\",\"½ piece (about 70 g)\",\"½ cup (about 35 g)\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',520,'chicken-noodle-soup-b677fb11-1b77-4f8f-bf11-464aee502976.png','Classic chicken soup simmered with vegetables and noodles; keep it meat-only (no dairy) to fit kosher-style home cooking.',10,6,6,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',60,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(555,'Chicken Stir-Fry Rice Bowl','uncooked jasmine rice, water, boneless skinless chicken breast, broccoli florets, red bell pepper, carrot, yellow onion, canola oil, low-sodium soy sauce, chicken stock, cornstarch, garlic clove, fresh ginger, toasted sesame oil, rice vinegar, black pepper, salt','Rinse the jasmine rice in a fine-mesh strainer until the water runs mostly clear, then add the rice and 1 cup water to a small saucepan; bring to a boil over high heat, cover, reduce to low, and cook for 12 minutes until the water is absorbed and the rice looks dry on top. | Turn off the heat and keep the pot covered for 5 minutes, then fluff with a fork; keep covered to stay warm while you cook the stir-fry. | Cut the chicken breast into 2 cm cubes; cut the red bell pepper into thin strips, slice the carrot into thin half-moons, and slice the onion thinly; mince the garlic clove and finely grate the ginger. | In a small bowl, whisk the soy sauce, chicken stock, cornstarch, rice vinegar, toasted sesame oil, black pepper, and salt until the cornstarch is fully dissolved and no lumps remain. | Heat a 25–28 cm skillet or wok over medium-high heat until a drop of water sizzles on contact (about 200°C), add 1 tbsp canola oil, then add the chicken in a single layer; cook for 3 minutes withou','[\"½ cup\",\"1 cup\",\"170 g\",\"1 cup\",\"½ piece\",\"½ piece\",\"¼ piece\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"¼ cup\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 piece\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',820,'chicken-stir-fry-rice-bowl-2d9ef36b-68c0-408a-869c-943531018c8c.png','A kosher chicken and vegetable stir-fry served over rice with a soy-ginger sauce.',8,8,11,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',30,'MID_LEVEL','China',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(556,'Chicken Tikka Masala','boneless skinless chicken thigh, canned crushed tomatoes, canned full-fat coconut milk, yellow onion, canola oil, garlic cloves, fresh ginger, water, tomato paste, lemon juice, ground cumin, ground coriander, sweet paprika, garam masala, ground turmeric, salt, black pepper, cayenne pepper','Pat the chicken dry with paper towels, then cut into 3 cm pieces on a cutting board. In a medium bowl, toss chicken with lemon juice, 1 tsp canola oil, ½ tsp garam masala, ½ tsp paprika, ¼ tsp cumin, ¼ tsp salt, and black pepper; mix until coated and let stand 10 minutes at room temperature. | Finely chop the onion; mince the garlic; grate the ginger. Heat a 25 cm skillet over medium-high heat for 2 minutes, then add ½ tbsp canola oil and swirl. Add the chicken in a single layer and sear 3–4 minutes, stirring once or twice, until browned in spots but not necessarily cooked through; transfer to a plate. | Lower heat to medium. Add the remaining 1 tbsp canola oil to the same skillet, then add the onion and cook 5–6 minutes, stirring, until soft and lightly golden. Add garlic and ginger and cook 30 seconds until very fragrant. | Add cumin, coriander, turmeric, the remaining ½ tsp paprika, and cayenne; stir 20 seconds to toast the spices without letting them scorch. Stir in tomato paste an','[\"200 g\",\"¾ cup\",\"½ cup\",\"½ small onion\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"2 cloves\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ cup\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',780,'chicken-tikka-masala-67c537a7-fb49-489b-a51d-071b92dd9a3d.png','Grilled-spiced chicken pieces simmered in a tomato-cream-style sauce made with coconut milk so it stays meat-only and kosher-friendly.',9,15,15,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',45,'MID_LEVEL','India',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(557,'Shakshuka','large eggs, canned crushed tomatoes, red bell pepper, diced, onion, finely chopped, olive oil, garlic cloves, minced, tomato paste, water, salt, sweet paprika, ground cumin, ground black pepper, cayenne pepper','Set a 20 cm skillet over medium heat for 2 minutes, add the olive oil, then add the onion and red bell pepper and cook for 6–8 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon, until the onion turns translucent and the pepper softens with lightly browned edges. | Add the minced garlic, sweet paprika, ground cumin, black pepper, and cayenne pepper; stir constantly for 30 seconds until fragrant (do not let the garlic brown). | Stir in the tomato paste for 1 minute to darken slightly, then add the crushed tomatoes, water, and salt. Bring to a gentle simmer over medium heat, then reduce to medium-low and simmer uncovered for 8–10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the sauce thickens enough that a spoon leaves a brief trail. | Use the spoon to make 2 shallow wells in the sauce. Crack the eggs into a small bowl one at a time, then slide each egg into a well to keep yolks intact. | Cover the skillet with a lid, cook on low for 5–7 minutes, until the whites are set and opaque but the yolks are still s','[\"2 pieces\",\"1 cup\",\"½ piece\",\"¼ piece\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"2 pieces\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"¼ cup\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',430,'shakshuka-a22bd789-58f4-4e86-8b56-cad4d1957173.png','A classic Israeli pan of eggs poached in a spiced tomato and pepper sauce, served hot.',8,13,8,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(558,'פאד תאי עוף','אטריות אורז שטוחות, חזה עוף ללא עור, ביצה גדולה, נבטים, מים, רוטב סויה, רוטב דגים, מחית תמרינדי, מיץ ליים סחוט, שמן צמחי ניטרלי (קנולה/חמניות), בוטנים קלויים קצוצים, בצל ירוק פרוס, שום כתוש, פתיתי צ׳ילי','לכסות את אטריות האורז בקערה במים רותחים מהקומקום ל-6–8 דקות, עד שהן גמישות אך עדיין מעט קשות במרכז; לסנן היטב ולנער כדי להוציא נוזלים. | לפרוס את חזה העוף לרצועות דקות בעובי כ-½ ס״מ כדי שייצלה מהר ובאופן אחיד. | לערבב בכוס את המים, רוטב הסויה, רוטב הדגים, מחית התמרינדי ומיץ הליים עד שהמחית נמסה והרוטב אחיד. | לחמם ווק או מחבת רחבה על להבה גבוהה 2 דקות עד שחמה מאוד (טיפה של מים צריכה להתאדות מיד), להוסיף את השמן ולסובב לציפוי הדפנות. | להוסיף את העוף בשכבה אחת ולטגן/להקפיץ 2–3 דקות, לערבב ולהמשיך עוד 1–2 דקות עד שהוא משנה צבע לגמרי ומשחים מעט בקצוות. | להוסיף את השום ופתיתי הצ׳ילי ולהקפיץ 20–30 שניות רק עד שעולה ריח שום, בלי להשחים מאוד. | לדחוף את העוף לצד המחבת, לשבור את הביצה לצד הפנוי ולערבב בכף עץ 30–60 שניות עד שמתקבלים גושים רכים ולא נוזליים. | להוסיף את האטריות המסוננות ואת הרוטב, ולהקפיץ 1–2 דקות בעזרת מלקחיים/כף עץ עד שהאטריות מצופות והרוטב מסמיך מעט ומבריק; אם יבש מדי, להוסיף 1–2 כפות מים נוספים מהברז ולהמשיך להקפיץ עד שהאטריות רכות-לעיס. | להוסיף נבטים ורוב הבצל הירוק ולהקפי','[\"90 גרם\",\"120 גרם\",\"1 יח׳\",\"1 כוס\",\"½ כוס\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"2 כפות\",\"1 יח׳\",\"1 שן\",\"¼ כפית\"]',690,'פאד-תאי-עוף-f5f12d1e-8662-4d1d-a608-9c995eb32b3e.png','אטריות אורז מוקפצות עם עוף, ביצה, נבטים ורוטב תמרינדי עם ליים ובוטנים.',9,11,11,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'MID_LEVEL','Thailand',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(559,'Spaghetti Aglio e Olio','dried spaghetti, olive oil, garlic cloves, thinly sliced, fresh parsley, finely chopped, red pepper flakes, salt, black pepper','Bring a medium pot of water to a rolling boil over high heat, salt the water generously, add the spaghetti, and cook until al dente, 8–10 minutes; reserve ⅓ cup pasta cooking water, then drain. | While the pasta cooks, heat a 25 cm skillet over medium-low heat (the oil should shimmer but not smoke). Add the olive oil and sliced garlic and cook 2–3 minutes, stirring constantly, until the garlic turns pale golden; if it starts browning quickly, pull the skillet off the heat for 20 seconds to prevent burning. | Add the red pepper flakes to the skillet and stir for 15 seconds until fragrant. | Add the drained spaghetti to the skillet along with 3 tablespoons of the reserved pasta cooking water. Toss vigorously with tongs over medium heat for 1–2 minutes until the pasta looks glossy and the oil clings to the noodles; add 1–2 more tablespoons reserved water if it looks dry. | Turn off the heat, add the chopped parsley, black pepper, and a pinch more salt if needed, then toss for 10 seconds a','[\"100 g\",\"2½ tablespoons\",\"3 pieces\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',540,'spaghetti-aglio-e-olio-a98a5739-c025-4d72-8676-0483f203731d.png','Classic Italian spaghetti dressed with garlic-infused olive oil, chili, and parsley.',9,3,6,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'EASY','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(560,'שקשוקה','עגבניות מרוסקות משימורים, ביצה גדולה, פיתה, בצל, פלפל אדום, שמן זית, שום, רסק עגבניות, מים, פטרוזיליה, מלח, פפריקה מתוקה, כמון טחון, פלפל שחור','לשטוף היטב ולבדוק שאין חרקים בפטרוזיליה; לקצוץ דק. לקלף את הבצל ולחתוך לקוביות קטנות. להוציא גרעינים מהפלפל ולחתוך לקוביות קטנות. לקלף את השום ולקצוץ דק. | לחמם מחבת כבדה בקוטר 24–26 ס״מ על אש בינונית (כ־180°C) עם שמן זית במשך 30 שניות, עד שהשמן זורם בקלות. להוסיף בצל ופלפל ולטגן 6–8 דקות תוך ערבוב כל דקה, עד שהבצל רך ושקוף והפלפל מתרכך בלי להישרף. | להוסיף שום, פפריקה וכמון ולערבב 20–30 שניות רק עד שעולה ריח (לא לתת לשום להשחים). | להוסיף עגבניות מרוסקות, רסק עגבניות, מים, מלח ופלפל שחור. להביא לרתיחה קלה על אש בינונית-גבוהה (בועות עדינות), ואז להנמיך לאש בינונית-נמוכה ולבשל 8–10 דקות, עד שהרוטב מסמיך ומצטמצם מעט ומתחיל להשאיר שביל כשמעבירים כף בתחתית המחבת. | ליצור 2 גומות ברוטב עם גב כף. לשבור ביצה לכל גומה. לכסות במכסה ולבשל על אש בינונית-נמוכה 5–7 דקות, עד שחלבון הביצה לבן ואטום והחלמון עדיין מעט רוטט (לביצה קשה יותר לבשל עוד 1–2 דקות). | בזמן הבישול, לחמם את הפיתה על מחבת יבשה על אש בינונית 30–45 שניות לכל צד עד שהיא חמה וגמישה עם סימני צריבה קלים. לפזר פטרוזיליה מעל השקשוקה ולהג','[\"1 כוס\",\"2 יח׳\",\"1 יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"1 כף\",\"2 שיניים\",\"1 כף\",\"¼ כוס\",\"1 כף\",\"½ כפית\",\"1 כפית\",\"¼ כפית\",\"⅛ כפית\"]',590,'שקשוקה-0cebd5f0-8f63-4a8a-b837-b4a543d793c3.png','תבשיל עגבניות ופלפלים עם ביצים שמתבשלות ברוטב, מוגש חם עם פיתה.',9,15,6,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(561,'Greek Salad','ripe tomato, cut into 2 cm chunks, English cucumber, cut into 2 cm chunks, green bell pepper, sliced into thin rings, red onion, thinly sliced, feta cheese, cut into 2 cm pieces, pitted Kalamata olives, extra-virgin olive oil, red wine vinegar, dried oregano, salt, black pepper','Wash the tomato, cucumber, and bell pepper; for kosher practice, inspect the vegetables carefully, then cut the tomato and cucumber into 2 cm chunks and slice the bell pepper into thin rings on a cutting board with a chef’s knife. | Thinly slice the red onion; if the bite is strong, soak the slices in a small bowl of cold water for 5 minutes, then drain well and pat dry. | Add the tomato, cucumber, bell pepper, and red onion to a medium bowl; add the olives and toss gently for 10 seconds to distribute without crushing the vegetables. | In a small bowl, whisk the olive oil, red wine vinegar, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper with a fork for 15–20 seconds until slightly thickened and uniform. | Pour the dressing over the salad and toss gently with a spoon for about 15 seconds, just until the vegetables look glossy. | Add the feta pieces on top and give one very gentle fold so some feta stays in distinct pieces; serve immediately while the vegetables are crisp and the feta remains int','[\"1 medium\",\"½ medium\",\"½ medium\",\"¼ small\",\"60 g\",\"10 pieces\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',420,'greek-salad-9e338291-2bdb-44be-9a9b-318ccf27cb61.png','A classic chopped vegetable salad with feta and olives dressed with olive oil and red wine vinegar.',9,6,4,8,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',15,'EASY','Greece',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(562,'שקשוקה עגבניות','ביצים גדולות, עגבניות מרוסקות משימורים, פלפל אדום, בצל, שמן זית, רסק עגבניות, שום, מים, פטרוזיליה, מלח, כמון טחון, פפריקה מתוקה, פלפל שחור טחון','לשטוף היטב את הפטרוזיליה ולבדוק שאין חרקים. לקצוץ דק את הבצל, לחתוך את חצי הפלפל האדום לקוביות קטנות, ולקצוץ את השום. | לחמם מחבת ברזל יצוק או מחבת נון-סטיק בקוטר 20–24 ס״מ על אש בינונית (כ־170–180°C) למשך דקה, להוסיף שמן זית ולערבב 10 שניות לציפוי התחתית. | להוסיף בצל ופלפל אדום, לטגן על אש בינונית 6–8 דקות תוך ערבוב כל דקה, עד שהבצל שקוף עם קצוות זהובים והפלפל מתרכך. | להוסיף שום ולערבב 30–45 שניות רק עד שמריחים ניחוח חזק בלי שהשום משחים. | להוסיף רסק עגבניות, לערבב ולטגן 1 דקה עד שהוא מתכהה מעט ומצפה את הירקות. להוסיף עגבניות מרוסקות ומים, לתבל במלח, כמון, פפריקה ופלפל שחור, להביא לרתיחה עדינה ואז להנמיך לאש בינונית-נמוכה (בעבוע קטן). לבשל 8–10 דקות, עד שהרוטב מסמיך ונראה כמו רוטב פסטה סמיך; אם הוא מתייבש מדי, להוסיף 1–2 כפות מים בזמן הבישול. | בעזרת כף ליצור 2 גומות ברוטב, לשבור לכל גומה ביצה. לכסות במכסה ולבשל על אש נמוכה 5–7 דקות, עד שחלבוני הביצים לבנים ומוצקים והחלמונים עדיין רכים; אם רוצים חלמון מוצק יותר, להוסיף 1–2 דקות. | לכבות אש, לפזר פטרוזיליה קצוצה ולהגיש מיד ישר מהמחבת','[\"2 יח׳\",\"1 כוס (240 מ״ל)\",\"½ יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"2 שיניים\",\"¼ כוס (60 מ״ל)\",\"1 כף קצוצה\",\"¼ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\",\"½ כפית\",\"⅛ כפית\"]',410,'שקשוקה-עגבניות-5ef27477-b7d7-4c0b-aec7-ea28acc829c7.png','שקשוקה קלאסית בסגנון ים־תיכוני: רוטב עגבניות ופלפלים מתובל שבו ביצים מתבשלות בעדינות עד שהחלבון מתייצב והחלמון נשאר רך.',9,12,7,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',30,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(563,'Chicken Fried Rice','cooked jasmine rice, chilled, boneless skinless chicken thigh, cut into 1 cm pieces, egg, frozen mixed peas and carrots, yellow onion, finely chopped, soy sauce, canola oil, toasted sesame oil, garlic, minced, salt, ground black pepper','Set a wok or 28 cm skillet over medium-high heat until a drop of water sizzles on contact (about 200°C pan surface), then add 1 tsp canola oil and swirl to coat. | Add the chicken in a single layer, season with the salt and black pepper, and stir-fry 3–4 minutes until lightly browned and cooked through (no pink spots; juices run clear). Transfer to a bowl. | Add the remaining 2 tsp canola oil to the hot pan, add the onion and stir-fry 1 minute until glossy and just starting to soften, then add the garlic and stir-fry 20 seconds until fragrant (do not let it brown). | Push the aromatics to one side, add the egg to the empty side of the pan, and scramble 45–60 seconds over medium-high heat until just set in small curds. | Add the peas and carrots and stir-fry 1–2 minutes until hot and no longer icy, then add the chilled rice. Use a spatula to break up clumps and toss constantly 2–3 minutes until the rice is steaming and some grains look slightly toasted. | Return the chicken to the pan, ','[\"1½ cups\",\"120 g\",\"1 large\",\"½ cup\",\"¼ cup\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"2 cloves\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',720,'chicken-fried-rice-55e84b99-ee7a-4d25-a14f-52b01232c27f.png','A classic Chinese-style fried rice made with day-old rice, chicken, egg, and vegetables, finished with soy sauce and sesame oil.',9,6,11,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'EASY','China',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(564,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','flour, semi-sweet chocolate chips, unsalted butter, softened, brown sugar, packed, white sugar, egg yolk, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Heat the oven to 175°C and line a small baking sheet with parchment paper; set a medium bowl and a rubber spatula on the counter. | Sift the flour into the bowl to help check for insects and break up lumps, then mix in the baking soda and salt until evenly distributed. | In a second medium bowl, mix the softened butter, brown sugar, and white sugar with a fork or spatula for about 1 minute until smooth and paste-like; it should look slightly lighter and spreadable. | Add the egg yolk and vanilla extract and mix vigorously for 30–45 seconds until glossy and fully combined, with no streaks of yolk visible. | Add the flour mixture and fold with the spatula just until no dry flour remains; the dough should be thick and hold together without being crumbly. | Fold in the chocolate chips until evenly scattered, then scoop the dough into 4 equal mounds and place them on the baking sheet at least 5 cm apart; gently press each mound to about 1.5 cm thick without flattening completely. | Bake on ','[\"½ cup\",\"⅓ cup\",\"3 tbsp\",\"3 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 piece\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',520,'chocolate-chip-cookies-c9064bfb-6167-49f7-b1c3-1b7fe8089e33.png','A classic American cookie with a buttery vanilla dough and melted chocolate chips; contains dairy but no meat, fitting kosher dairy practice.',10,41,6,2,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',32,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(565,'קרם ברולה וניל','שמנת מתוקה, חלמון ביצה גדולה, סוכר לבן, תמצית וניל, מלח','לחמם תנור ל-160°C. להניח תבנית אפייה עמוקה במרכז התנור, ולהרתיח קומקום מים. | בסיר קטן לחמם שמנת מתוקה על אש בינונית כ-4–6 דקות, עד שהיא חמה מאוד ומתחילות להופיע בועיות קטנות בשוליים (לא לתת לה לרתוח). להוריד מהאש. | בקערה בינונית לטרוף חלמונים עם 2 כפות סוכר לבן, תמצית וניל ומלח כ-45–60 שניות, עד שהתערובת בהירה ומעט מסמיכה. | למזוג את השמנת החמה בהדרגה אל קערת החלמונים תוך טריפה רציפה, כדי למנוע בישול של הביצים. לסנן דרך מסננת דקה אל קנקן קטן או קערה עם פיה. | לשפוך את הקרם לכלי קטן חסין חום. להניח את הכלי בתוך התבנית העמוקה בתנור, ולמזוג לתבנית מים רותחים עד שמגיעים בערך לחצי גובה הכלי (אמבט מים). | לאפות 28–35 דקות, עד שהשוליים יציבים והמרכז עדיין רוטט קלות כשמנערים בעדינות את הכלי. להוציא בזהירות את הכלי מאמבט המים ולהניח על רשת צינון 30 דקות. | לכסות ולהעביר למקרר לפחות 2 שעות, עד שהקרם קר ומוצק. | לפזר מעל הקרם את 1 כף הסוכר הלבן הנותרת בשכבה אחידה ודקה. לקרמל עם מבער ידני בתנועות קצרות 1–2 דקות, עד שהסוכר נמס ומשחים לענבר עמוק. להמתין 2–3 דקות עד שנוצרת שכבה קשה ושבירה, ולהגיש.','[\"⅔ כוס\",\"2 יח׳\",\"3 כפות\",\"½ כפית\",\"קורט\"]',620,'קרם-ברולה-וניל-b1d4dcef-eccb-4965-8802-70d9ea9201ea.png','קינוח קלאסי: קרם וניל עשיר עם שכבת סוכר מקורמלת ושבירה מעל.',9,38,5,3,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',235,'MID_LEVEL','France',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(566,'שקשוקה','עגבניות מרוסקות משימורים, ביצים גדולות, פלפל אדום, בצל, שמן זית, רסק עגבניות, שום, מים, פטרוזיליה קצוצה, מלח, כמון טחון, פפריקה מתוקה, פלפל שחור','לשטוף היטב את הפטרוזיליה ולבדוק שאין חרקים; לקצוץ. לקלף ולחתוך את הבצל לקוביות קטנות (כ-½ ס״מ). לחתוך את הפלפל לקוביות קטנות. לקלף ולקצוץ דק את השום. | לחמם מחבת כבדה בקוטר 20–24 ס״מ על להבה בינונית (כ-170–180°C) ולהוסיף שמן זית. להוסיף בצל ולבשל 4–5 דקות תוך ערבוב בכף עץ עד שהוא שקוף ומתרכך בלי השחמה חזקה. | להוסיף פלפל אדום ולבשל 3–4 דקות על להבה בינונית עד שהוא מתרכך ומבריק. להוסיף שום ולערבב 30 שניות עד שעולה ריח חזק אך לא שרוף. | להוסיף רסק עגבניות, פפריקה מתוקה וכמון ולערבב 45–60 שניות כדי לפתוח טעמים; הרסק צריך להכהות מעט ולהידבק קלות לתחתית. | להוסיף עגבניות מרוסקות, מים, מלח ופלפל שחור. להביא לרתיחה עדינה על להבה בינונית-גבוהה ואז להנמיך ללהבה בינונית-נמוכה ולבשל 8–10 דקות ללא מכסה, עד שהרוטב מסמיך ונשארת \"שביל\" קצר כשמעבירים כף בתחתית. | ליצור 2 גומות ברוטב עם גב הכף. לשבור בכל גומה ביצה. לכסות את המחבת במכסה ולהמשיך לבשל על להבה נמוכה 5–7 דקות, עד שחלבון הביצה אטום ולבן והחלמון עדיין רך (או 8–9 דקות לחלמון מוצק יותר). | לכבות את האש, לפזר פטרוזיליה קצוצה ולהמתין דקה עם מכסה ','[\"1 כוס\",\"2 יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"2 שיניים\",\"¼ כוס\",\"1 כף\",\"½ כפית\",\"½ כפית\",\"½ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\"]',420,'שקשוקה-c8a2453d-4a34-4a76-8acc-b66636ce58d1.png','שקשוקה ביתית עם רוטב עגבניות-פלפלים וביצים מבושלות בעדינות, מוגשת ישר מהמחבת. מתאים לכשרות ללא ערבוב בשר וחלב.',7,11,8,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(568,'Buttermilk Pancakes','flour, buttermilk, egg, canola oil, sugar, baking powder, salt','Whisk flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl until evenly combined and no clumps remain. | In a small bowl, whisk buttermilk, egg, and 2 teaspoons of the canola oil until smooth. Pour into the dry ingredients and whisk just until no dry flour remains; the batter should look slightly lumpy and thick. Rest 5 minutes at room temperature to hydrate the flour. | Heat a 20–25 cm non-stick skillet over medium heat until a drop of water sizzles on contact (about 175–190°C). Add the remaining 1 teaspoon canola oil and wipe to a thin film with a paper towel. | Scoop about ¼ cup batter per pancake into the skillet, leaving space between pancakes. Cook 2–3 minutes, until bubbles form on top, the edges look set and slightly matte, and the bottoms are deep golden brown. | Flip with a thin spatula and cook 1–2 minutes more, until the second side is golden brown and the center springs back when lightly pressed. Transfer to a plate and cook remaining batter, adjusting heat to prevent sc','[\"½ cup\",\"½ cup\",\"1 large\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',520,'buttermilk-pancakes-6045e056-e29d-4558-8b0d-6f517d63b85e.png','Classic skillet pancakes with a tender crumb and lightly browned edges.',10,15,6,4,1,43,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',20,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(570,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','flour, semi-sweet chocolate chips, unsalted butter, softened, packed light brown sugar, white sugar, egg yolk, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Heat the oven to 175°C and line a small baking sheet with parchment paper; set a rack in the middle of the oven. | In a medium bowl, mix the softened butter, packed light brown sugar, and white sugar with a fork for about 1 minute, until smooth and glossy with no visible butter streaks. | Add the egg yolk and vanilla extract and mix for 30–45 seconds until the mixture looks thicker and evenly combined. | Sprinkle in the flour, baking soda, and salt; stir with a spoon just until no dry flour remains and the dough looks uniform (about 20–30 strokes). | Fold in the semi-sweet chocolate chips until evenly distributed. | Scoop the dough into 3 mounds (about 2 tbsp each), place them spaced apart on the baking sheet, and gently press each mound to about 1.5 cm thick so they bake evenly. | Bake for 10–12 minutes, until the edges are light golden and the centers look slightly underbaked and puffed. | Cool on the baking sheet for 10 minutes to set, then transfer to a plate; the centers should fi','[\"½ cup (60 g)\",\"¼ cup (45 g)\",\"2 tbsp (28 g)\",\"2 tbsp (25 g)\",\"1 tbsp (12 g)\",\"1 large\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',560,'chocolate-chip-cookies-419d3708-921b-4adb-893a-50991b929e3a.png','Classic drop cookies with crisp edges and a soft center.',10,41,8,2,1,69,'0','0','0','0','0','[]',32,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(571,'Avocado Toast With Egg','bread slice, ripe avocado, large egg, olive oil, lemon juice, salt, black pepper, red pepper flakes','Toast the bread in a toaster or in a 25 cm skillet over medium heat until deep golden and crisp, about 2–3 minutes total, flipping once if using a skillet; set on a plate. | Scoop the avocado into a small bowl and mash with a fork for 20–30 seconds until mostly smooth with a few small chunks; mix in the lemon juice, salt, and black pepper until evenly combined. | Heat a 20–25 cm non-stick skillet over medium heat (about 175°C) for 1 minute, add 1 teaspoon olive oil, and swirl to coat; crack in the egg and fry 2–3 minutes until the whites are fully set and the edges look lacy and lightly browned, covering the pan for the last 30–60 seconds if needed to set the top. | Spread the avocado mixture evenly over the toast, slide the egg on top, drizzle with the remaining 1 teaspoon olive oil, and finish with red pepper flakes; serve immediately while the toast is still crisp.','[\"1 slice\",\"½ avocado\",\"1 egg\",\"2 teaspoons\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',360,'avocado-toast-with-egg-a9b03c31-e218-497d-bbf4-a7a73bbea7f9.png','A classic breakfast of toasted bread topped with mashed avocado and a fried egg, finished with lemon and black pepper. Kept kosher by using olive oil (no butter).',9,2,9,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',10,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(572,'Shakshuka','canned crushed tomatoes, large eggs, red bell pepper, finely diced, yellow onion, finely diced, olive oil, garlic cloves, minced, tomato paste, water, ground cumin, sweet paprika, salt, black pepper, cayenne pepper','Place a 20 cm nonstick or cast-iron skillet over medium heat (about 175°C). Add the olive oil, then add the onion and red bell pepper and cook, stirring with a wooden spoon, for 6–8 minutes until softened and lightly golden at the edges. | Add the minced garlic and cook for 30 seconds, stirring constantly, until fragrant (do not let it brown). | Stir in the tomato paste, cumin, sweet paprika, salt, black pepper, and cayenne pepper. Cook for 1 minute, stirring, until the paste darkens slightly and the spices smell toasted. | Add the crushed tomatoes and water. Bring to a steady simmer over medium-high heat, then reduce to medium-low and simmer uncovered for 8–10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until thick enough that a spoon leaves a trail and the sauce no longer looks watery. | Use the back of a spoon to make 2 shallow wells in the sauce. Crack the eggs into the wells. Cover the skillet with a lid and cook on low heat for 4–6 minutes, until the whites are set and opaque and the yolks a','[\"1 cup\",\"2\",\"½ pepper\",\"¼ onion\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"2 cloves\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"¼ cup\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',430,'shakshuka-5438edaa-fa77-4832-8ff5-e99ce134374a.png','Eggs gently poached in a spiced tomato and pepper sauce, served straight from the skillet.',9,13,7,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Tunisia',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(573,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','flour, semi-sweet chocolate chips, unsalted butter, softened, brown sugar, packed, white sugar, egg yolk, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Preheat the oven to 175°C and line a small baking sheet with parchment paper; sift the flour into a medium bowl to check for insects, then whisk in the baking soda and salt until evenly mixed. | In a second medium bowl, use a fork to cream the softened butter with the brown sugar and white sugar for about 1 minute, until glossy and paste-like with no dry sugar patches. | Add the egg yolk and vanilla extract and mix with the fork for about 30 seconds, until smooth and fully emulsified. | Add the flour mixture and fold with a spatula just until no dry flour remains; fold in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed, avoiding over-mixing so the dough stays tender. | Scoop the dough into 3 mounds (about 1½ tbsp each) and place them 6–7 cm apart; gently press each mound to about 5 cm wide and 1.5 cm thick for even baking. | Bake on the center rack for 10–12 minutes, until the edges are lightly browned and set while the centers still look slightly soft and underdone. | Cool on the baking ','[\"½ cup\",\"¼ cup\",\"3 tbsp\",\"3 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 piece\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',470,'chocolate-chip-cookies-bb79aa15-db17-4df7-aa4b-98198be5def2.png','A classic kosher dairy cookie with crisp edges and a chewy center.',10,31,6,2,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',30,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(574,'Chickpea Salad Sandwich','canned chickpeas, drained and rinsed, bread slices, mayonnaise, celery stalk, finely diced, red onion, finely diced, dill pickles, finely chopped, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, olive oil, salt, black pepper','Place the chickpeas in a medium bowl and mash with a fork for 45–60 seconds until about 70% are crushed and a few chickpeas remain whole for texture. | Add the mayonnaise, celery, red onion, dill pickles, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, salt, and black pepper. Stir with a spoon for 20–30 seconds until the mixture looks creamy and evenly combined; taste and adjust with a pinch more salt if needed. | Heat a skillet over medium heat (about 170°C) for 2 minutes. Brush one side of each bread slice with the olive oil, then toast oil-side down in the skillet for 1½–2 minutes, until golden with crisp edges; flip and toast the second side for 30–45 seconds. | Pile the chickpea salad onto one slice of toast, spreading it to the edges. Top with the second slice, press gently for 5 seconds, then slice and serve.','[\"½ cup\",\"2 slices\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 piece\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',520,'chickpea-salad-sandwich-586865d5-dbe0-4859-85c5-71f9f5728554.png','A classic chickpea salad mixed with mayonnaise, lemon, and crunchy vegetables, piled onto toasted bread.',7,6,7,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',15,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(575,'פאד תאי עוף','אטריות אורז רחבות, חזה עוף ללא עצם וללא עור, פרוס לרצועות דקות, נבטים, ביצה גדולה, בצל ירוק, פרוס דק, בוטנים קלויים, קצוצים גס, מים, מיץ ליים טרי, רוטב דגים, מחית תמרינדי, רוטב סויה, שמן קנולה, שום, כתוש, פתיתי צ\'ילי, סוכר חום','להשרות את אטריות האורז בקערה עם מים רותחים מהקומקום עד כיסוי ל-6–8 דקות, עד שהן גמישות אך עדיין מעט נגיסות; לסנן היטב ולהחזיר לקערה יבשה. | לערבב בכוס את המים, מחית התמרינדי, רוטב הדגים, רוטב הסויה, מיץ הליים וסוכר חום עד שהסוכר נמס והרוטב אחיד. | לחמם ווק או מחבת גדולה בקוטר כ-28 ס\"מ על אש בינונית-גבוהה כ-1½ דקות עד שחם מאוד; להוסיף שמן קנולה ולסובב לציפוי. להוסיף את רצועות העוף ולטגן 3–4 דקות, תוך ערבוב תכוף, עד שהעוף לבן כמעט לגמרי ושוליים מתחילים להשחים. | להוסיף שום ופתיתי צ\'ילי ולטגן 20–30 שניות רק עד שמריחים שום (לא לתת לו להשחים כהה). | לדחוף את העוף לצד אחד של המחבת, לשבור את הביצה לצד הריק ולטרוף עם כף עץ 30–45 שניות עד שמתקבלת ביצה מקושקשת רכה; לערבב עם העוף. | להוסיף את האטריות המסוננות ולשפוך את הרוטב; להקפיץ 2–3 דקות על אש בינונית-גבוהה בעזרת מלקחיים/כף, עד שהאטריות מצופות, הרוטב נספג חלקית והאטריות מבריקות ורכות אך לא מתפוררות. אם נראה יבש מדי, להוסיף 1–2 כפות מים מהברז ולהקפיץ עוד 20 שניות. | להוסיף נבטים ובצל ירוק ולהקפיץ 30–45 שניות רק עד שהנבטים מתחממים אך נשארים פרי','[\"90 גרם\",\"150 גרם\",\"1 כוס\",\"1\",\"2 גבעולים\",\"2 כפות\",\"⅓ כוס\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"2 כפיות\",\"1 כף\",\"2 שיניים\",\"¼ כפית\",\"1 כפית\"]',720,'פאד-תאי-עוף-4916c6b3-b533-4fd0-97cf-c87077cc504e.png','פאד תאי קלאסי בסגנון תאילנדי עם אטריות אורז, עוף, ביצה, בוטנים ורוטב תמרינדי מאוזן. מתאים לכשרות ללא ערבוב בשר וחלב.',9,7,13,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'MID_LEVEL','Thailand',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(576,'שקשוקה','ביצים גדולות, עגבניות בשלות קצוצות, פלפל אדום קצוץ, בצל קצוץ, שמן זית, שום כתוש, רסק עגבניות, מים, פפריקה מתוקה, כמון טחון, מלח, פלפל שחור','להניח מחבת בקוטר 24 ס״מ על אש בינונית ולחמם 1 כף שמן זית 30 שניות, עד שהוא זורם בקלות ומבריק. | להוסיף ½ בצל קצוץ ו-½ פלפל אדום קצוץ ולטגן 6–7 דקות על אש בינונית, תוך ערבוב עם כף עץ, עד שהבצל שקוף ומתחיל להשחים בקצוות והפלפל מתרכך. | להוסיף 2 שיני שום כתושות, 1 כפית פפריקה מתוקה ו-¼ כפית כמון ולטגן 30 שניות תוך ערבוב, עד שעולה ריח חזק (להיזהר לא לשרוף את השום). | להוסיף 1 כף רסק עגבניות ולערבב 30 שניות לציפוי הירקות, ואז להוסיף 2 עגבניות קצוצות, ¼ כוס מים, ½ כפית מלח ו-¼ כפית פלפל שחור. להביא לבעבוע עדין על אש בינונית (כ-2 דקות). | להנמיך לאש בינונית-נמוכה ולבשל 8–10 דקות ללא מכסה, עד שהרוטב מסמיך ומצטמצם כך שכאשר מעבירים כף נוצר שביל שמחזיק שנייה-שתיים. אם הרוטב סמיך מדי, להוסיף עוד 1–2 כפות מים ולהחזיר לבעבוע עדין. | ליצור עם כף 2 גומות ברוטב. לשבור לכל גומה ביצה גדולה אחת כך שהחלמון נשאר שלם. לכסות את המחבת ולבשל 4–6 דקות על אש בינונית-נמוכה, עד שהחלבון לבן ומבושל והחלמון עדיין מעט רוטט כשמנערים בעדינות את המחבת. | לכבות את האש, להשאיר מכוסה 1 דקה לייצוב, ואז להגיש ישר מהמחבת כשהרוט','[\"2 יח׳\",\"2 יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"1 כף\",\"2 שיניים\",\"1 כף\",\"¼ כוס\",\"1 כפית\",\"¼ כפית\",\"½ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\"]',360,'שקשוקה-4d064cf3-8d44-43ac-8024-fb03928530d5.png','ארוחת צהריים ישראלית פופולרית של ביצים ברוטב עגבניות-פלפלים מתובל, שמוגשת ישר מהמחבת עם חלמונים רכים.',9,10,9,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(577,'עוגת שוקולד בספל','קמח מנופה, סוכר לבן, קקאו, חלב, שמן קנולה, ביצה גדולה, שוקולד מריר קצוץ, אבקת אפייה, מלח, תמצית וניל','לנפות את הקמח לקערית קטנה ולוודא שאין חרקים; להכין ספל מיקרוגל בנפח כ-300–350 מ״ל וכפית לערבוב. | לשים בספל את הקמח, הסוכר, הקקאו, אבקת האפייה והמלח ולערבב היטב בכפית 20–30 שניות עד שאין גושים כהים של קקאו. | להוסיף לספל את החלב, שמן הקנולה, הביצה ותמצית הווניל ולטרוף בכפית 45–60 שניות, לגרד את הדפנות והתחתית, עד שנוצלת בלילה אחידה וסמיכה. | לפזר מעל את השוקולד המריר הקצוץ ולערבב ערבוב אחד-שניים בלבד כדי שיישארו חתיכות שיימסו בפנים. | לבשל במיקרוגל בעוצמה גבוהה 60–80 שניות; לעצור כשחלק העליון תפוח ומבריק אך עדיין מעט לח במרכז, ואם נראה נוזלי מאוד להוסיף עוד 10 שניות ולהמשיך בפולסים קצרים. | להניח על השיש 2 דקות להתייצבות; להגיש ישר מהספל כשהמרכז רך והדפנות יציבות.','[\"4 כפות\",\"2 כפות\",\"2 כפות\",\"4 כפות\",\"2 כפות\",\"1 יח׳\",\"1 כף\",\"¼ כפית\",\"קורט\",\"¼ כפית\"]',510,'עוגת-שוקולד-בספל-57713ab0-a306-461d-bc53-0c2410088d99.png','קינוח ביתי נפוץ: עוגת שוקולד אישית שמוכנה במיקרוגל ומתקבלת לחה במרכז.',8,26,8,3,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',10,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(578,'מרק עוף עם ירקות','ירך עוף עם עצם ועור, מים, גזר, תפוח אדמה, בצל, גבעול סלרי, שמן זית, שום, מלח, פלפל שחור','לקלף את הגזר ותפוח האדמה ולחתוך לקוביות של כ-2 ס״מ; לקלף את הבצל ולחתוך גס; לשטוף היטב את גבעול הסלרי ולבדוק שאין חרקים, ואז לפרוס דק; לקלף ולכתוש את שן השום. | לחמם סיר קטן וכבד בנפח 1.5–2 ליטר על אש בינונית (כ-170°C) במשך דקה, להוסיף שמן זית ולהניח את ירך העוף עם צד העור כלפי מטה. לצרוב 4–5 דקות בלי להזיז, עד שהעור מזהיב ומשתחרר בקלות; להפוך ולצרוב עוד 2 דקות עד שיש השחמה קלה. | להוסיף לסיר את הבצל, הגזר, הסלרי ותפוח האדמה ולערבב 1 דקה על אש בינונית עד שהבצל מתחיל להתרכך והירקות מצופים בשומן מהסיר. | להוסיף מים, מלח, פלפל שחור ושום. להביא לרתיחה על אש גבוהה (כ-210°C) במשך 4–6 דקות עד שיש בעבוע חזק. | להנמיך לאש נמוכה כך שיהיה בעבוע עדין בלבד, לכסות חלקית (להשאיר חריץ), ולבשל 60–75 דקות. במהלך הבישול להסיר בעדינות קצף אם מצטבר. המרק מוכן כשהעוף רך מאוד ונפרד בקלות מהעצם והירקות רכים אך לא מתפרקים לגמרי. | לכבות את האש, להוציא את ירך העוף לצלחת עם מלקחיים, להמתין 3 דקות ואז להפריד בשר מהעצם. להחזיר את הבשר לסיר, לטעום ולהוסיף עוד קורט מלח אם צריך. להגיש חם עם ירקות וציר.','[\"1 יח׳ (כ-220 גרם)\",\"2½ כוסות (600 מ״ל)\",\"1 יח׳ (כ-100 גרם)\",\"1 קטן (כ-130 גרם)\",\"½ יח׳ (כ-70 גרם)\",\"1 יח׳ (כ-50 גרם)\",\"1 כפית\",\"1 שן\",\"½ כפית\",\"⅛ כפית\"]',430,'מרק-עוף-עם-ירקות-8d88378e-e280-4038-acb2-5f090658a453.png','מרק עוף קלאסי בסגנון ביתי, מבוסס על ציר שמתבשל לאט עם ירקות ושום, ומתובל בעדינות. מתאים לכשרות ללא ערבוב בשר וחלב.',9,7,5,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',90,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(579,'Chicken Pad Thai','dried flat rice noodles, boneless skinless chicken breast, thinly sliced, egg, bean sprouts, rinsed and drained, garlic clove, finely chopped, roasted unsalted peanuts, coarsely chopped, fresh lime, canola oil, tamarind paste, fish sauce, water, brown sugar, sweet paprika','Soak the rice noodles in a medium bowl with very hot tap water (not boiling) for 8–10 minutes, stirring once or twice, until pliable but still slightly firm in the center; drain well and set aside. | In a small bowl, whisk together the tamarind paste, fish sauce, water, brown sugar, and sweet paprika until the sugar dissolves and the sauce looks smooth; set next to the stove. | Heat a 25 cm nonstick skillet or wok over medium-high heat (about 190°C) for 2 minutes; add the canola oil and heat 20 seconds until it shimmers. | Add the sliced chicken and cook for 3–4 minutes, tossing constantly, until the pieces turn opaque and lightly browned at the edges; add the chopped garlic and stir-fry 20–30 seconds until fragrant. | Push the chicken to one side of the pan; crack in the egg on the empty side and scramble with a spatula for 45–60 seconds until just set in small curds, then mix through the chicken. | Add the drained noodles and pour in the sauce; toss and stir-fry for 2–3 minutes until','[\"85 g\",\"120 g\",\"1 large\",\"1 cup\",\"1\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"½\",\"2 tablespoons\",\"1½ tablespoons\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"3 tablespoons\",\"2 teaspoons\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',760,'chicken-pad-thai-84fcd055-bdc7-4333-9dd3-b723cab2a05d.png','Stir-fried rice noodles with chicken, egg, bean sprouts, and a tamarind-fish sauce.',9,13,12,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'MID_LEVEL','Thailand',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(580,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','flour, semi-sweet chocolate chips, unsalted butter, softened, light brown sugar, packed, white sugar, egg yolk, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Preheat the oven to 175°C and line a small baking sheet with parchment paper. Set a medium bowl and a rubber spatula on the counter. | In the medium bowl, mix the softened butter, light brown sugar, and white sugar with the spatula for about 1 minute, until the mixture looks smooth and slightly fluffy and no dry sugar patches remain. | Add the egg yolk and vanilla extract and mix vigorously for 30–45 seconds, until the mixture looks glossy and fully combined. | Add the flour, baking soda, and salt. Fold with the spatula just until no dry flour remains; the dough should be soft but not runny. Fold in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed. | Scoop the dough into 2 mounds (about 2½–3 tbsp each) and place them on the baking sheet about 7 cm apart. Gently press each mound to about 6–7 cm wide and about 2 cm thick; leave the edges slightly taller than the center for a thicker cookie. | Bake on the middle rack for 9–11 minutes, until the edges are light golden and set, while the center','[\"½ cup\",\"¼ cup\",\"3 tbsp\",\"2½ tbsp\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"1 piece\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',620,'chocolate-chip-cookies-816e0add-86c9-457a-ae37-dccfc04db193.png','Classic chocolate chip cookies baked until the edges are golden and the centers stay soft. Dairy-based and meat-free to keep it kosher-friendly without mixing meat and dairy.',10,35,7,2,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(581,'Chicken Noodle Soup','bone-in chicken thighs, water, carrot, celery stalk, yellow onion, egg noodles, fresh parsley, canola oil, salt, black pepper','Rinse the parsley very well and check it for insects; peel the carrot, trim the celery, and cut the carrot, celery, and onion into 1 cm pieces. | Heat a medium pot (about 2 liters) over medium heat (about 170°C). Add the canola oil, then add the onion, carrot, and celery and cook for 4–5 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon, until the onion looks glossy and slightly softened without browning. | Add the chicken thighs, water, salt, and black pepper. Increase to high heat and bring to a strong boil, about 4–6 minutes, then immediately reduce to low to maintain a gentle simmer with small bubbles. | Simmer partially covered for 35–40 minutes, skimming any foam with a spoon, until the chicken is very tender and pulls easily from the bone and the broth looks clear and golden. | Transfer the chicken to a plate with tongs. When cool enough to handle, remove skin and bones, shred the meat into bite-size pieces, and return the meat to the pot. | Bring the soup back to a steady simmer over mediu','[\"2 pieces (about 350 g)\",\"2½ cups (600 ml)\",\"1 piece (about 80 g)\",\"1 piece (about 60 g)\",\"½ piece (about 80 g)\",\"½ cup (about 40 g)\",\"2 tablespoons (chopped)\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',520,'chicken-noodle-soup-469cc5f3-2126-42a1-8ff4-6a1d268d0770.png','Classic chicken noodle soup made with a clear chicken broth, vegetables, and egg noodles; contains no dairy so it stays kosher-friendly with meat.',10,7,8,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',60,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(582,'Scrambled Eggs and Toast','large eggs, bread, tomato, cucumber, butter, olive oil, salt, black pepper, lemon juice','Set out a cutting board, chef’s knife, medium bowl, fork, nonstick skillet (20–24 cm), silicone spatula, toaster or a dry skillet, and a plate. | Dice the tomato into 1 cm pieces and dice the cucumber into 1 cm pieces; place in a bowl, add the olive oil, lemon juice, and ¼ teaspoon salt, and toss until glossy and lightly juicy. | Crack the eggs into a medium bowl, add ¼ teaspoon salt and the black pepper, and whisk with a fork for 20–30 seconds until the whites and yolks are fully blended and slightly foamy. | Toast the bread in a toaster to deep golden, or toast in a dry skillet over medium heat (about 175°C) for 1–2 minutes per side until crisp and browned at the edges. | Heat the nonstick skillet over medium-low heat (about 150–160°C). Add the butter and swirl until fully melted and just starting to foam, without browning. | Pour in the eggs and cook 2–4 minutes, stirring slowly and constantly with a silicone spatula, sweeping the pan and folding the curds. Stop when the eggs are so','[\"2 pieces\",\"2 slices\",\"1 medium\",\"½ medium\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"½ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\"]',520,'scrambled-eggs-and-toast-6cafdacf-270b-4b97-a632-17fbbb41fa02.png','Classic breakfast of soft scrambled eggs with toasted bread and a simple tomato-cucumber salad; dairy is kept separate from any meat for kosher compliance.',9,4,10,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',12,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(583,'שקשוקה','עגבניות מרוסקות משימורים, ביצים גדולות, פלפל אדום, בצל, שמן זית, מים, שום, רסק עגבניות, כמון טחון, פפריקה מתוקה, מלח, פלפל שחור','לקלף ולחתוך את הבצל לקוביות קטנות (כ-5 מ״מ). להסיר גרעינים מהפלפל ולחתוך לקוביות קטנות. לקלף ולכתוש את השום. | לחמם מחבת כבדה בקוטר 20–24 ס״מ על אש בינונית (כ-170°C) במשך דקה, להוסיף שמן זית ולהטות את המחבת לציפוי. | להוסיף בצל ולטגן 4–5 דקות על אש בינונית, תוך ערבוב בכף עץ, עד שהוא שקוף ומתחיל להזהיב בקצוות. להוסיף פלפל ולטגן עוד 3–4 דקות עד שהוא מתרכך. | להוסיף שום, כמון ופפריקה ולערבב 30 שניות עד שעולה ריח. להוסיף רסק עגבניות ולערבב דקה עד שהצבע מתכהה מעט. | להוסיף עגבניות מרוסקות ומים, לערבב ולהביא לבעבוע עדין על אש בינונית-נמוכה (כ-140–150°C). לבשל 6–8 דקות ללא מכסה, עד שהרוטב מסמיך ומותיר שביל כשמעבירים כף, ולהוסיף מלח ופלפל שחור. | בעזרת כף ליצור 2 גומות ברוטב, לשבור לתוכן את הביצים. לכסות את המחבת ולבשל 4–6 דקות על אש נמוכה, עד שהחלבון אטום והחלמון עדיין רך (או עוד 1–2 דקות לחלמון מוצק יותר). | לכבות את האש, להשאיר מכוסה דקה להתייצבות, ולהגיש ישר מהמחבת כשהרוטב סמיך ומבעבע קלות סביב הביצים.','[\"1 כוס\",\"2 יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"1 כף\",\"¼ כוס\",\"2 שיניים\",\"1 כף\",\"½ כפית\",\"½ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\",\"⅛ כפית\"]',380,'שקשוקה-af665c0e-1dce-4d23-89ea-0527c2cace9e.png','מנה ישראלית פופולרית לארוחת בוקר: ביצים שמבושלות ברוטב עגבניות ופלפלים מתובל, ומוגשות חמות מהמחבת.',9,10,7,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',22,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(584,'סלט ישראלי קצוץ','עגבנייה בשלה, מלפפון, בצל סגול קטן, פטרוזיליה טרייה, שמן זית, מיץ לימון סחוט טרי, מלח, פלפל שחור','לשטוף היטב את הפטרוזיליה תחת זרם מים, להפריד עלים, לבדוק שאין חרקים ולייבש היטב במגבת נייר או במייבש חסה; לקצוץ דק. | לחתוך את העגבנייה והמלפפון לקוביות קטנות של כ-½ ס״מ על קרש חיתוך בעזרת סכין חדה; לקצוץ את הבצל הסגול דק מאוד. | להעביר לקערה בינונית את העגבנייה, המלפפון, הבצל והפטרוזיליה ולערבב בכף עד שהירקות מתחלקים באופן אחיד. | להוסיף שמן זית, מיץ לימון, מלח ופלפל שחור; לערבב 20–30 שניות עד שהסלט מבריק והנוזלים מצפים את הירקות, ולטעום ולהתאים מלח במידת הצורך. | להניח לסלט לעמוד 5 דקות בטמפרטורת החדר כדי שהירקות יגירו מעט נוזלים והטעמים יתאחדו, ואז לערבב קצרה ולהגיש.','[\"1 יח׳\",\"1 יח׳\",\"¼ יח׳\",\"2 כפות\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"¼ כפית\",\"⅛ כפית\"]',165,'סלט-ישראלי-קצוץ-7c5a8265-a94f-4289-8c2b-7510b081f543.png','סלט ירקות קצוץ בסגנון ישראלי עם תיבול לימון ושמן זית. לשטוף היטב את הפטרוזיליה ולבדוק שאין חרקים.',9,5,1,9,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',12,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(585,'ספגטי קרבונרה','ספגטי, גואנצ׳אלה חתוך לקוביות קטנות, חלמון ביצה גדול, ביצה גדולה, גבינת פקורינו טבעונית מגוררת, פלפל שחור גרוס, מלח','להביא לרתיחה סיר גדול עם מים ולמלוח היטב; לבשל את הספגטי לפי הוראות היצרן עד אל דנטה, ולשמור ½ כוס ממי הבישול לפני הסינון. | בינתיים לחמם מחבת רחבה על אש בינונית ולהוסיף את קוביות הגואנצ׳אלה; לטגן 6–8 דקות תוך ערבוב מדי פעם, עד שהשומן נמס והקוביות זהובות וקריספיות בקצוות. לכבות את האש ולהשאיר את הגואנצ׳אלה והשומן במחבת. | בקערה לערבב חלמון וביצה עם גבינת פקורינו טבעונית מגוררת, פלפל שחור ומלח עד לקבלת קרם סמיך ואחיד. | להוסיף את הספגטי המסונן למחבת עם הגואנצ׳אלה ולערבב 30 שניות כשהמחבת כבויה, כדי שהפסטה תצופה בשומן. | להוסיף לקערת הביצים 3 כפות ממי הבישול החמים בהדרגה תוך טריפה (כדי להשוות טמפרטורה), ואז לשפוך מיד את התערובת למחבת ולערבב במהירות עם מלקחיים/כף עץ 45–60 שניות עד שנוצר רוטב מבריק שמצפה את הפסטה בלי להיקרש. אם סמיך מדי, להוסיף עוד מי בישול כף-כף עד מרקם קרמי שנשפך באיטיות.','[\"100 גרם\",\"60 גרם\",\"1 יח׳\",\"1 יח׳\",\"⅓ כוס\",\"1 כפית\",\"¼ כפית\"]',700,'ספגטי-קרבונרה-ed543a7f-d246-4c0a-a2ed-ef5037bd9b1b.png','ספגטי קרבונרה עם גואנצ׳אלה, ביצה וגבינת פקורינו; גרסה ביתית קלאסית ללא שמנת. כשר: מנה בשרית ללא מוצרי חלב.',9,3,7,4,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(586,'ספגטי ברוטב עגבניות ובזיליקום','ספגטי יבש, עגבניות מרוסקות משימורים, גבינת פרמזן מגוררת דק, שמן זית, שום, בזיליקום טרי, רסק עגבניות, מלח, פלפל שחור','להכין סיר בינוני עם הרבה מים להרתחה (המים לא נכנסים לרשימת המצרכים). להביא לרתיחה חזקה על אש גבוהה, להמליח את מי הבישול בנדיבות, להוסיף את הספגטי ולבשל לפי הוראות היצרן עד אל דנטה, תוך ערבוב ב-30 השניות הראשונות כדי שלא יידבק; לשמור ¼ כוס ממי הבישול ואז לסנן. | בזמן שהפסטה מתבשלת, לקצוץ דק את השום. לקרוע את עלי הבזיליקום ביד ולשטוף היטב ולבדוק שאין חרקים. | לחמם מחבת רחבה על אש בינונית (כ-170–180°C) עם שמן הזית במשך 30 שניות. להוסיף את השום ולטגן 30–45 שניות עד שעולה ריח ושום מתחיל להזהיב קלות (לא להשחים). | להוסיף למחבת את רסק העגבניות ולערבב 30 שניות עד שהוא מעט מתכהה. להוסיף עגבניות מרוסקות, מלח ופלפל שחור, להביא לבעבוע עדין על אש בינונית-נמוכה ולבשל 6–8 דקות עד שהרוטב מסמיך ומצפה כף. | להוסיף למחבת את הספגטי המסונן ולערבב/להקפיץ 1–2 דקות על אש בינונית עד שהרוטב מצפה היטב את הפסטה. אם הרוטב סמיך מדי, להוסיף בהדרגה 1–3 כפות ממי הבישול ששמרתם עד שמתקבל רוטב מבריק שנצמד לפסטה. | לכבות את האש, להוסיף את הבזיליקום ולערבב 10 שניות. להגיש מיד ולפזר מעל את הפרמזן.','[\"100 גרם\",\"1 כוס\",\"25 גרם\",\"1 כף\",\"2 שיניים\",\"6 עלים\",\"1 כף\",\"½ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\"]',560,'ספגטי-ברוטב-עגבניות-ובזיליקום-4341ae91-4d57-4507-9832-5aea9d076599.png','מנה איטלקית ביתית פופולרית של פסטה ברוטב עגבניות עם שום ובזיליקום, מוגשת עם פרמזן.',9,9,5,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'EASY','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(587,'Chicken Stir-Fry with Rice','uncooked jasmine rice, water, boneless skinless chicken breast, broccoli florets, red bell pepper, carrot, canola oil, low-sodium soy sauce, water, cornstarch, garlic clove, fresh ginger, sesame oil, rice vinegar, salt, black pepper','Rinse the jasmine rice in a fine-mesh strainer for 20–30 seconds until the water runs less cloudy. Add the rice and ¾ cup water to a small saucepan, cover, and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce to low heat and cook for 12 minutes without lifting the lid, until the water is absorbed and steam holes appear on the surface. | Turn off the heat and let the rice stand covered for 5 minutes, then fluff with a fork until the grains separate. | While the rice cooks, cut the chicken breast into 2 cm pieces. Cut the red bell pepper into thin strips, slice the carrot into thin half-moons, and keep the broccoli as small bite-size florets so everything cooks evenly. | In a small bowl, whisk the low-sodium soy sauce, 3 tablespoons water, cornstarch, sesame oil, and rice vinegar until the cornstarch is fully dissolved and no lumps remain. Finely grate the garlic clove and ginger into the bowl and stir to combine. | Heat a 25 cm skillet or wok over medium-high heat until a drop of water sizzles on','[\"½ cup\",\"¾ cup\",\"150 g\",\"1 cup\",\"½ piece\",\"½ piece\",\"1 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"3 tbsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 piece\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',640,'chicken-stir-fry-with-rice-e4e50615-7da8-43f7-8b8a-5dc65470f64d.png','Chicken and vegetables are stir-fried and coated in a soy-garlic sauce, then served over steamed rice.',9,7,11,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',30,'EASY','China',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(588,'Tuna Salad Sandwich','canned tuna in water, drained, bread slices, mayonnaise, celery stalk, finely diced, red onion, finely diced, dill pickle, finely chopped, lettuce leaves, Dijon mustard, lemon juice, black pepper, salt','Open the can of tuna, drain it well, and press it lightly with the back of a spoon in a fine-mesh strainer for 30–60 seconds to remove excess water; transfer to a medium bowl. | Add the mayonnaise, diced celery, diced red onion, chopped dill pickle, Dijon mustard, lemon juice, salt, and black pepper; mix with a fork for 30–45 seconds until evenly combined and the tuna breaks into small flakes, but is not paste-like. | Toast the bread slices in a toaster or on a dry skillet over medium heat (about 180°C) for 1–2 minutes total, flipping once if using a skillet, until the surface is lightly golden and feels dry and crisp. | Lay the lettuce leaves on one slice of toast, spread the tuna salad evenly on top in a 1–1.5 cm layer, then close with the second slice; press gently for 5 seconds so it holds together. | Slice in half with a serrated knife and serve immediately; the filling should look creamy with visible celery and onion pieces and no watery liquid pooling.','[\"1 can (about 140 g)\",\"2 slices\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 piece\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 piece\",\"2 pieces\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',520,'tuna-salad-sandwich-77b5b874-ba64-4044-a318-01d114cc463e.png','A classic deli-style tuna salad sandwich with a crisp celery crunch and a lemon-mustard dressing.',8,4,14,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',12,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(589,'Spaghetti Carbonara','spaghetti, egg yolk, grated Pecorino Romano cheese, beef bacon, cut into 1 cm pieces, black pepper, salt','Bring a medium pot of well-salted water to a rolling boil over high heat, add the spaghetti, and cook until al dente, about 9–11 minutes; reserve ⅓ cup pasta cooking water, then drain the spaghetti. | While the pasta cooks, place the beef bacon in a cold 25 cm skillet and set over medium heat; cook, stirring occasionally, until the fat renders and the pieces are deeply browned and crisp, 6–8 minutes, then turn off the heat. | In a small bowl, whisk the egg yolk, grated Pecorino Romano, and black pepper until a thick paste forms. | Add the hot drained spaghetti to the skillet with the beef bacon and toss for 30 seconds over the residual heat so the pasta is coated in the rendered fat; if the pan seems dry, add 1 tablespoon of the reserved pasta water. | Remove the skillet from the heat and wait 20 seconds so the pan is no longer sizzling, then add the egg-and-cheese mixture and toss vigorously with tongs for 45–60 seconds, adding reserved pasta water 1 tablespoon at a time until a gloss','[\"100 g\",\"1 large\",\"30 g\",\"60 g\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\"]',735,'spaghetti-carbonara-eeeac6fd-1220-4d00-96a3-b9803fc4ec0f.png','Classic Roman spaghetti tossed with crisp beef bacon, egg yolk, Pecorino, and black pepper. This version avoids pork to fit kosher-style restrictions and keeps the dairy separate from any meat by using beef bacon instead of guanciale.',10,3,12,4,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',20,'MID_LEVEL','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(590,'Chicken Tikka Masala','boneless skinless chicken thighs, canned crushed tomatoes, canned full-fat coconut milk, yellow onion, finely chopped, canola oil, garlic cloves, minced, fresh ginger, finely grated, tomato paste, lemon juice, water, ground cumin, ground coriander, garam masala, paprika, ground turmeric, ground black pepper, salt','Cut the chicken thighs into 3 cm pieces on a cutting board. In a medium bowl, toss the chicken with lemon juice, 1 tsp grated ginger, 1 minced garlic clove, ½ tsp salt, ½ tsp cumin, ½ tsp coriander, ½ tsp garam masala, ½ tsp paprika, turmeric, and black pepper; mix until every piece is coated, then let stand 10 minutes at room temperature. | Heat a 25 cm heavy skillet over medium-high heat until a drop of water sizzles immediately (about 200°C surface). Add 1 tbsp canola oil, swirl, then spread the chicken in a single layer; cook 3 minutes without moving until browned edges appear, flip, and cook 2–3 minutes more until the exterior is charred in spots and the chicken is about 80% cooked through. Transfer to a plate (leave any browned bits in the pan). | Reduce heat to medium. Add the remaining ½ tbsp canola oil, then add the onion and cook 6–8 minutes, stirring, until soft and lightly golden. Add the remaining garlic clove and remaining 1 tsp ginger and cook 30 seconds until fragrant. ','[\"200 g\",\"¾ cup\",\"½ cup\",\"½ medium\",\"1½ tbsp\",\"2 cloves\",\"2 tsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"¼ cup\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¾ tsp\"]',720,'chicken-tikka-masala-30e86123-0978-4a26-860e-e298306ef8c1.png','Charred spiced chicken simmered in a tomato-coconut sauce; a classic restaurant-style dish made dairy-free to keep it kosher with meat.',9,18,12,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',40,'MID_LEVEL','India',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(591,'שקשוקה','עגבניות מרוסקות משימורים, ביצים גדולות, פלפל אדום, בצל, שמן זית, מים, שום, רסק עגבניות, פפריקה מתוקה, כמון טחון, פלפל שחור, מלח','לקלף את הבצל ולקצוץ לקוביות קטנות; לשטוף את הפלפל, להסיר גרעינים ולחתוך לקוביות קטנות; לקלף את השום ולכתוש. להשתמש בירקות נקיים ולבדוק שאין חרקים במידת הצורך. | לחמם מחבת כבדה בקוטר 20–24 ס״מ על אש בינונית (כ-170–180°C) עם שמן זית במשך 1 דקה עד שהשמן נוזלי ומנצנץ קלות. | להוסיף בצל ופלפל ולבשל 6–8 דקות על אש בינונית, תוך ערבוב כל דקה-שתיים, עד שהבצל שקוף עם הזהבה קלה והפלפל מתרכך. | להוסיף שום, פפריקה וכמון ולערבב 30 שניות על אש בינונית-נמוכה עד שעולה ריח תבלינים ולא נשרף. | להוסיף עגבניות מרוסקות, רסק עגבניות, מים, מלח ופלפל שחור; לערבב היטב עד שהרסק נמס. להביא לרתיחה עדינה על אש בינונית, ואז להנמיך לאש בינונית-נמוכה ולבשל 6–8 דקות ללא מכסה עד שהרוטב מסמיך ומבעבע בעדינות (כשהכף משאירה “שביל” קצר בתחתית המחבת). | בעזרת כף ליצור 2 שקעים ברוטב ולשבור לתוכם את הביצים. לכסות במכסה ולבשל 4–6 דקות על אש נמוכה עד שהחלבון לבן ואטום, והחלמון עדיין מעט רוטט במרכז (לבישול מלא יותר להוסיף עוד 1–2 דקות). | להסיר מהאש, להניח 1 דקה להתייצבות, ולהגיש ישירות מהמחבת כשהביצים יושבות ברוטב הסמיך.','[\"1 כוס\",\"2 יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"1 כף\",\"3 כפות\",\"2 שיניים\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כפית\",\"¼ כפית\",\"⅛ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\"]',420,'שקשוקה-11067887-7ea9-4435-ab16-e099bea9f491.png','שקשוקה ישראלית במחבת: ביצים ברוטב עגבניות, פלפל ותיבול בסיסי. מתאים לכשרות ללא שילוב בשר וחלב.',8,14,7,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(592,'סלט ירקות ישראלי','עגבנייה, מלפפון, בצל, פטרוזיליה קצוצה, שמן זית, מיץ לימון סחוט טרי, מלח, פלפל שחור','לשטוף היטב ולבדוק שאין חרקים בפטרוזיליה; לייבש. לשטוף את העגבנייה והמלפפון ולייבש, לקלף את הבצל. | על קרש חיתוך, לקצוץ את העגבנייה והמלפפון לקוביות קטנות מאוד (כ-5 מ״מ). לקצוץ דק את הבצל ואת הפטרוזיליה. | להעביר לקערה בינונית, להוסיף שמן זית, מיץ לימון, מלח ופלפל שחור, ולערבב בכף 20–30 שניות עד שהירקות מצופים והרוטב מצטבר מעט בתחתית הקערה. | להניח 5 דקות בטמפרטורת החדר כדי שהירקות יגירו מעט נוזלים, לערבב שוב ולטעום; אם צריך להוסיף עוד קורט מלח עד שהטעם מאוזן וחמצמץ.','[\"1 גדולה\",\"1 בינוני\",\"¼ קטן\",\"2 כפות\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"¼ כפית\",\"⅛ כפית\"]',170,'סלט-ירקות-ישראלי-6014bc5d-2592-4d66-961c-dabdd1d358d6.png','סלט קצוץ דק עם עגבנייה, מלפפון, בצל ומיץ לימון, מוגש לרוב לצד ארוחות ביתיות.',9,6,1,9,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',12,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(593,'מרק עדשים','עדשים כתומות יבשות שטופות ומסוננות, מים, בצל, גזר, סלרי (גבעולים), שמן זית, רסק עגבניות, כמון טחון, כורכום, פלפל שחור, מלח','לבדוק ולשטוף היטב את גבעול הסלרי ולוודא שאין חרקים; לקצוץ דק ½ בצל, לקלף ולחתוך את הגזר לקוביות קטנות (כ-1 ס״מ) ולפרוס דק את הסלרי. | לחמם סיר קטן (כ-1.5 ליטר) על אש בינונית כ-1 דקה, להוסיף 1 כף שמן זית ואת הבצל ולטגן 4–5 דקות תוך ערבוב בכף עץ עד שהבצל שקוף ורך ולא משחים. | להוסיף את הגזר והסלרי ולטגן עוד 2 דקות על אש בינונית עד שהירקות מתחילים להתרכך וריח הירק נפתח. | להוסיף 1 כף רסק עגבניות, 1 כפית כמון ו-¼ כפית כורכום ולערבב 30 שניות על האש עד שהרסק נצמד מעט לתחתית והריח נעשה עמוק. | להוסיף ½ כוס עדשים כתומות ו-2 כוסות מים, להעלות לאש גבוהה ולהביא לרתיחה מלאה כ-3–5 דקות (בועות גדולות על פני השטח). | להנמיך לאש נמוכה, לכסות חלקית ולבשל 18–22 דקות עד שהעדשים מתפרקות והמרק מסמיך; לערבב פעם-פעמיים כדי שלא יידבק לתחתית. אם סמיך מדי, להוסיף עוד 2–4 כפות מים ולהחזיר לרתיחה עדינה. | לתבל ב-½ כפית מלח, ¼ כפית פלפל שחור, לערבב ולבשל עוד 1 דקה; המרק מוכן כשהוא סמיך, חלק יחסית, והגזר רך למעיכה עם כף.','[\"½ כוס\",\"2 כוסות\",\"½ יח׳\",\"1 יח׳\",\"1 יח׳\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כפית\",\"¼ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\",\"½ כפית\"]',380,'מרק-עדשים-40d1b32d-6aff-48c3-9576-e5070b5e76d3.png','מרק עדשים כתומות בסגנון ביתי, מבושל על בסיס בצל, גזר וסלרי עם כמון וכורכום. מתאים לכשרות (פרווה) ללא ערבוב בשר וחלב.',8,8,4,8,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',35,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(594,'פסטה ברוטב עגבניות ובזיליקום','פסטה קצרה, עגבניות מרוסקות משימורים, שמן זית, בצל קטן קצוץ דק, שום כתוש, רסק עגבניות, מים, פרמזן מגוררת, עלי בזיליקום, מלח, פלפל שחור','לשטוף היטב את עלי הבזיליקום ולבדוק שאין חרקים; לייבש ולקצוץ גס. | להרתיח סיר בינוני עם הרבה מים ולהמליח היטב; לבשל את הפסטה לפי זמן היצרן עד אל דנטה (בדרך כלל 8–11 דקות), עד שהיא רכה אך עדיין נגיסה. לשמור 2 כפות ממי הבישול ולסנן. | בזמן שהפסטה מתבשלת, לחמם מחבת רחבה על אש בינונית, להוסיף שמן זית ובצל ולטגן 4–6 דקות עד שהבצל שקוף ורך בלי השחמה חזקה. | להוסיף שום ולטגן 30–45 שניות רק עד שעולה ריח (לא לתת לשום להשחים). | להוסיף רסק עגבניות ולערבב 1 דקה עד שהרסק מתכהה מעט ומצפה את הבצל. | להוסיף עגבניות מרוסקות, מים, מלח ופלפל שחור; להביא לבעבוע עדין על אש בינונית-נמוכה ולבשל 8–10 דקות ללא מכסה, עד שהרוטב מסמיך ומבריק ומכסה גב כף. | להוסיף למחבת את הפסטה המסוננת ו-2 כפות ממי הבישול ששמרתם; לערבב על אש בינונית 1–2 דקות עד שהרוטב נצמד לפסטה. אם הרוטב סמיך מדי, להוסיף עוד כף מים בהדרגה. | לכבות את האש, להוסיף בזיליקום קצוץ ופרמזן, לערבב 20–30 שניות עד שהגבינה נמסה חלקית והרוטב נהיה קרמי. לטעום ולהוסיף מעט מלח או פלפל לפי הצורך.','[\"90 גרם\",\"¾ כוס\",\"1 כף\",\"½ יח׳\",\"2 שיניים\",\"1 כף\",\"¼ כוס\",\"2 כפות\",\"6 יח׳\",\"½ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\"]',560,'פסטה-ברוטב-עגבניות-ובזיליקום-33c98591-25ad-4c5b-b3ca-c836cbbc993a.png','מנה איטלקית ביתית ופופולרית של פסטה ברוטב עגבניות עם שום ובזיליקום. כשר: ללא בשר וללא מוצרים מן הים, ועם בדיקה קצרה לעלי התיבול.',9,10,5,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Italy',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(595,'Chicken Shawarma Pita','boneless skinless chicken thigh, pita bread, cucumber, tomato, tahini paste, water, canola oil, lemon juice, garlic clove, ground cumin, sweet paprika, ground turmeric, ground black pepper, salt','Pat the chicken dry with paper towels, then slice into thin 1 cm strips on a cutting board; place in a medium bowl and add lemon juice, minced garlic, ground cumin, sweet paprika, ground turmeric, ground black pepper, and ¼ tsp of the salt, then mix with a spoon until every piece is evenly coated; let stand 10 minutes at room temperature. | Dice the cucumber and tomato into 1 cm pieces; rinse well and inspect for insects as needed, then place in a small bowl and season with the remaining ¼ tsp salt; toss and set aside. | Make the tahini sauce in a small bowl by whisking tahini paste with water for 30–45 seconds until smooth and pourable; if it seizes, keep whisking until it loosens and looks like thin mayonnaise. | Heat a 25 cm nonstick or cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat until a drop of water sizzles on contact (about 190°C), add canola oil and swirl to coat, then spread the chicken in a single layer; cook 3–4 minutes without moving until deeply browned on the bottom. | Flip th','[\"200 g\",\"1 piece\",\"⅓ piece\",\"½ piece\",\"2 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 tbsp\",\"1 piece\",\"1 tsp\",\"1 tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"½ tsp\"]',780,'chicken-shawarma-pita-4a4cbbe6-c606-46ea-bd81-f7957f9a4974.png','A kosher chicken shawarma-style filling cooked in a skillet and tucked into a pita with chopped salad and tahini.',9,5,13,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(596,'Chocolate Chip Cookies','flour (sifted), unsalted butter, softened, semi-sweet chocolate chips, light brown sugar, packed, white sugar, egg yolk, vanilla extract, baking soda, salt','Preheat the oven to 175°C and line a small sheet pan with baking paper; sift the flour into a medium bowl to check for insects, then whisk in the baking soda and salt until evenly combined. | In a second medium bowl, use a fork to mash and mix the softened butter with the brown sugar and white sugar for about 60–90 seconds, until the mixture looks like a thick, smooth paste with no dry sugar pockets. | Add the egg yolk and vanilla extract and mix vigorously with the fork for 30–45 seconds, until the mixture turns glossy and slightly lighter in color. | Add the flour mixture and stir with a spoon just until no dry flour remains; the dough should look thick and slightly tacky. Fold in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed. | Scoop the dough into 2 mounds (about 5–6 cm wide each) and place them on the sheet pan with at least 6 cm space between them; lightly press each mound to about 2 cm thick so they spread evenly. | Bake on the middle rack for 10–12 minutes, until the edges are l','[\"½ cup\",\"3 tbsp\",\"¼ cup\",\"3 tbsp\",\"2 tbsp\",\"1 large\",\"½ tsp\",\"¼ tsp\",\"⅛ tsp\"]',520,'chocolate-chip-cookies-2cb9e6c6-b401-462b-bdf3-f770052ee0e3.png','A classic kosher dairy chocolate chip cookie with crisp edges and a soft center.',10,35,7,2,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',32,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(597,'Vegetable Chickpea Curry','cooked chickpeas, drained and rinsed, cooked white rice, canned crushed tomatoes, water, fresh baby spinach, yellow onion, finely chopped, olive oil, garlic clove, minced, fresh ginger, finely grated, lemon juice, ground cumin, curry powder, salt, black pepper','Warm a small saucepan over medium heat for 1 minute, add the olive oil, then add the chopped onion and cook 4–5 minutes, stirring, until softened and lightly golden at the edges. | Add the minced garlic and grated ginger and cook 30–45 seconds, stirring constantly, until very fragrant (do not let the garlic brown). | Add the ground cumin and curry powder and stir for 15 seconds to toast the spices, then pour in the crushed tomatoes and water; scrape the bottom of the pan with a spoon and bring to a gentle simmer over medium heat. | Stir in the chickpeas and salt, reduce heat to medium-low, and simmer uncovered for 8–10 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes, until the sauce thickens enough to coat a spoon and the chickpeas are hot throughout. | Add the spinach and cook 1–2 minutes, stirring, until fully wilted and bright green; turn off the heat, stir in the lemon juice and black pepper, and taste and adjust salt if needed. | Spoon the hot rice into a bowl and ladle the curry over it; let i','[\"¾ cup\",\"¾ cup\",\"½ cup\",\"¼ cup\",\"1 packed cup\",\"½ small onion\",\"1 tablespoon\",\"1 clove\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\",\"⅛ teaspoon\"]',560,'vegetable-chickpea-curry-f1eddcb8-e702-4c1b-9610-9f9b479c4a09.png','A stovetop chickpea curry with tomatoes and spinach, finished with lemon and served over rice.',8,8,5,8,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',22,'EASY','India',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(598,'Chicken Noodle Soup','bone-in chicken thighs, water, carrot, celery stalk, yellow onion, dry egg noodles, olive oil, fresh parsley, salt, ground black pepper','Peel and slice the carrot into ½ cm rounds, slice the celery into ½ cm pieces, and finely chop the onion; set a medium pot on medium heat and warm the olive oil for 30 seconds until it shimmers. | Add the onion, carrot, and celery and sauté on medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon, until the onion turns translucent and the vegetables smell sweet but are not browned. | Add the chicken thighs, water, salt, and black pepper; raise heat to high until it reaches a steady boil, then immediately reduce to low to maintain a gentle simmer with small bubbles. | Simmer partially covered for 35–45 minutes, skimming off any foam with a spoon in the first 10 minutes, until the chicken is very tender and pulls easily from the bone. | Transfer the chicken to a plate with tongs; let it cool for 5 minutes, then pull the meat into bite-size shreds and discard skin and bones. | Bring the broth back to a gentle boil over medium heat; stir in the egg noodles and cook 6–8 minutes, stirring ','[\"2 pieces (about 300 g)\",\"3 cups (720 ml)\",\"1 medium (about 100 g)\",\"1 stalk (about 50 g)\",\"½ medium (about 80 g)\",\"½ cup (about 40 g)\",\"1 teaspoon\",\"1 tablespoon, chopped\",\"¾ teaspoon\",\"¼ teaspoon\"]',520,'chicken-noodle-soup-dad475f5-7db7-44fc-973b-84bbf348800e.png','Classic chicken soup with noodles, vegetables, and a clear broth.',9,6,7,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',65,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(599,'בראוניז שוקולד','שוקולד מריר, סוכר לבן, ביצה גדולה, קמח מנופה, שמן צמחי ניטרלי (קנולה/חמניות), אבקת קקאו, תמצית וניל, מלח','לחמם תנור ל-175°C. לרפד תבנית קטנה חסינת חום בגודל כ-10×10 ס״מ בנייר אפייה (או לשמן היטב בשמן קנולה/חמניות). לנפות את הקמח היטב כדי לוודא שאין חרקים. | להמיס את השוקולד המריר בקערה חסינת חום במיקרוגל בפולסים של 20 שניות, לערבב בין פולס לפולס, עד שהתערובת חלקה וחמימה (לא רותחת). | להוסיף לקערה את השמן ולערבב 20 שניות עד אחידות ומראה מבריק. להוסיף סוכר ולערבב 30 שניות עד שהתערובת סמיכה מעט. | להוסיף את הביצה ותמצית הווניל ולטרוף במטרפה ידנית 45–60 שניות, עד שהתערובת מסמיכה ונראית אחידה וללא פסי ביצה. | להוסיף קמח מנופה, אבקת קקאו ומלח, ולקפל במרית 20–30 שניות רק עד שלא רואים קמח יבש (לא לערבב יתר על המידה). | למרוח את הבלילה בתבנית בשכבה אחידה. לאפות על רשת אמצעית 14–18 דקות, עד שהשוליים תפוחים ויציבים והמרכז עדיין מעט רך; קיסם צריך לצאת עם פירורים לחים ולא עם בלילה נוזלית. | להניח להתקרר בתבנית 10 דקות להתייצבות, ואז להרים בעזרת נייר האפייה ולחתוך לקוביות כשהבראוניז פושר או בטמפרטורת החדר.','[\"70 גרם\",\"3 כפות\",\"1 יח׳\",\"2 כפות\",\"2 כפות\",\"1 כף\",\"½ כפית\",\"⅛ כפית\"]',560,'בראוניז-שוקולד-0afbba07-b415-4bb5-83df-0a9ef8ce2e33.png','בראוניז שוקולד קלאסי בסגנון ביתי, פרווה ומתאים לכשרות (ללא ערבוב בשר וחלב).',9,40,8,3,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',35,'EASY','United States',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(600,'פאד תאי עוף','אטריות אורז שטוחות, חזה עוף ללא עור, פרוס לרצועות דקות, ביצה גדולה, נבטי שעועית, בצל ירוק פרוס, בוטנים קלויים קצוצים, שמן צמחי ניטרלי (קנולה/חמניות), מים, רוטב דגים, מחית תמרינדי, רוטב סויה, מיץ ליים, סוכר חום, שום כתוש, פתיתי צ׳ילי','לשים את אטריות האורז בקערה בינונית, לכסות במים רותחים מהקומקום (לא נמדד), ולהשרות 6–8 דקות עד שהאטריות גמישות אבל עדיין מעט נוקשות במרכז; לסנן היטב ולנער במסננת 30 שניות כדי להיפטר מעודפי מים. | בקערית לערבב מים, מחית תמרינדי, רוטב דגים, רוטב סויה וסוכר חום עד שהסוכר נמס והרוטב אחיד (כ-30–45 שניות). | לחמם ווק או מחבת רחבה 28–30 ס״מ על אש בינונית-גבוהה כ-2 דקות עד שהכלי חם מאוד; להוסיף שמן ולסובב לציפוי. להוסיף את רצועות העוף ולצרוב 2–3 דקות תוך ערבוב, עד שהעוף משנה צבע ללבן-זהוב ואין חלקים ורודים. | להוסיף שום ופתיתי צ׳ילי ולערבב 15–20 שניות רק עד שעולה ריח (לא לתת לשום להשחים). לדחוף את העוף לצד אחד של המחבת, לשבור את הביצה לצד הפנוי, ולערבב עם מרית 45–60 שניות עד שהביצה כמעט מוצקה לחתיכות קטנות. | להוסיף למחבת את האטריות המסוננות ואת הרוטב. להקפיץ על אש בינונית-גבוהה 2–3 דקות בעזרת מלקחיים/שתי כפות, עד שהאטריות מקבלות צבע ענברי קל והרוטב מצפה אותן בלי שלולית נוזל בתחתית. | להוסיף נבטי שעועית ובצל ירוק ולהקפיץ עוד 45–60 שניות רק עד שהנבטים מתרככים מעט אבל נשארים פריכים. לכבות אש, להו','[\"90 גרם\",\"150 גרם\",\"1 יח׳\",\"1 כוס\",\"2 גבעולים\",\"2 כפות\",\"1½ כפות\",\"¼ כוס\",\"1 כף\",\"1½ כפות\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"2 כפיות\",\"1 שן\",\"¼ כפית\"]',720,'פאד-תאי-עוף-a2104baa-eb74-4e1c-a6aa-3fc7d0175de5.png','מוקפץ תאילנדי קלאסי של אטריות אורז עם עוף, רוטב תמרינדי, ביצה, נבטים ובוטנים. המנה בשרית וללא מוצרי חלב כדי לשמור על כשרות.',9,11,12,6,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'MID_LEVEL','Thailand',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(601,'מלבי מי ורדים','חלב, מים, קורנפלור, סוכר לבן, מי ורדים, מי ורדים (לסירופ), מים (לסירופ), סוכר לבן (לסירופ), מיץ לימון, קוקוס טחון, פיסטוקים קצוצים','לערבב בקערה קטנה את הקורנפלור עם 2 כפות מים בעזרת כפית עד שמתקבלת תערובת חלקה ללא גושים. | לשפוך לסיר קטן את החלב ו-3 כפות סוכר, לחמם על אש בינונית ולערבב עם מטרפה 2–3 דקות עד שהסוכר נמס והחלב חם מאוד (אדים עולים, אך לא רותח). | להנמיך לאש בינונית-נמוכה, להוסיף לסיר בהדרגה את תערובת הקורנפלור תוך ערבוב רציף עם מטרפה, ולהמשיך לבשל 3–5 דקות עד שהתערובת מסמיכה לפודינג חלק שמצפה את גב הכף. | להסיר מהאש, להוסיף 1 כפית מי ורדים ולערבב 10 שניות. למזוג מיד לכלי הגשה קטן חסין חום, להחליק את פני השטח, ולכסות בניילון נצמד כך שייגע ישירות במשטח כדי למנוע קרום. | לקרר במקרר לפחות 2 שעות, עד שהמלבי יציב למגע ונענע קל של הכלי מראה תזוזה קטנה בלבד במרכז. | להכין סירופ: בסירון קטן לערבב 2 כפות מי ורדים, 2 כפות מים, 1 כף סוכר ו-¼ כפית מיץ לימון. להביא לרתיחה עדינה על אש בינונית, ואז לבשל 2 דקות תוך ערבוב עד שהסוכר נמס לגמרי והנוזל נראה מעט סמיך ומבריק. לקרר 10 דקות לטמפרטורת חדר. | להגשה: לשפוך את הסירופ מעל המלבי הקר, לפזר קוקוס טחון ופיסטוקים קצוצים, ולהגיש קר.','[\"1 כוס\",\"2 כפות\",\"1 כף\",\"3 כפות\",\"1 כפית\",\"2 כפות\",\"2 כפות\",\"1 כף\",\"¼ כפית\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\"]',470,'מלבי-מי-ורדים-388c8de8-a450-4f78-be96-f8b9911e651a.png','קינוח ישראלי פופולרי על בסיס חלב עם מי ורדים, מוגש קר עם סירופ ורדים וקוקוס.',7,53,4,3,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',155,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]'),(602,'שקשוקה','עגבניות מרוסקות משימורים, ביצה גדולה, בצל, פלפל אדום, שמן זית, רסק עגבניות, מים, שום, פפריקה מתוקה, כמון טחון, פלפל שחור, מלח','לקלף ולקצוץ דק את הבצל; לנקות את הפלפל האדום מהגרעינים ולקצוץ לקוביות קטנות; לקלף ולקצוץ את שן השום. | לחמם מחבת כבדה בקוטר 20–24 ס״מ על אש בינונית (כ-170°C) במשך 1 דקה, להוסיף שמן זית ולחמם 20 שניות עד שהוא מבריק. | להוסיף בצל ופלפל למחבת ולטגן על אש בינונית 6–8 דקות, לערבב כל דקה עם כף עץ, עד שהבצל שקוף והפלפל מתרכך ומקבל קצוות מוזהבים. | להוסיף שום, פפריקה וכמון ולערבב 30–45 שניות על אש בינונית עד שעולה ריח תבלינים, בלי לשרוף את השום. | להוסיף עגבניות מרוסקות, רסק עגבניות, מים, מלח ופלפל שחור; לערבב היטב, להביא לרתיחה עדינה על אש בינונית-גבוהה ואז להנמיך לאש בינונית-נמוכה. לבשל 8–10 דקות ללא מכסה, עד שהרוטב מסמיך ונשארים שבילים כשמעבירים כף בתחתית המחבת. | בעזרת כף ליצור 2 גומות ברוטב, לשבור לתוך כל גומה ביצה. לכסות ולבשל על אש נמוכה 5–7 דקות, עד שחלבון הביצה לבן ואטום והחלמון עדיין רוטט מעט כשמנערים בעדינות את המחבת (לביצה עשויה יותר: עוד 1–2 דקות). | לכבות את האש, לתת לשקשוקה לנוח מכוסה 1 דקה כדי לייצב את הביצים, ולהגיש ישירות מהמחבת כשהרוטב סמיך ומבעבע קלות.','[\"1 כוס\",\"2 יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"½ יח׳\",\"1 כף\",\"1 כף\",\"¼ כוס\",\"1 שן\",\"1 כפית\",\"¼ כפית\",\"⅛ כפית\",\"¼ כפית\"]',430,'שקשוקה-04e54b20-6f9d-4b15-b73b-5ebdbfcb1e00.png','שקשוקה במחבת עם רוטב עגבניות ופלפלים וביצים מבושלות בעדינות, מתאימה לארוחה חלבית או פרווה.',8,13,9,7,1,44,'0','0','0','2','0','[]',25,'EASY','Israel',NULL,NULL,'[]');
